76 #define TRACE(...) \
77  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) { \
78  std::cout << __VA_ARGS__ << std::endl; \
79  }
80 
81 #define FAIL(...) \
82  TRACE("Failed " << __func__ << ":" << __LINE__ << ": " << __VA_ARGS__); \
83  return {};

89 enum class CpuOperation {
90  kFloat64Round,
91  kMathClz32,
92 };
93 
94 // TODO(leszeks): Add a generic mechanism for marking nodes as optionally
95 // supported.
96 bool IsSupported(CpuOperation op) {
97  switch (op) {
98  case CpuOperation::kFloat64Round:
99 #if defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32)
100  return CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SSE4_1) || CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX);
101 #elif defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM)
102  return CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ARMv8);
103 #elif defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_PPC64) || \
104  defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_S390X) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64) || \
105  defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_LOONG64) || \
106  defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_MIPS64)
107  return true;
108 #else
109 #error "V8 does not support this architecture."
110 #endif
111 
112  case CpuOperation::kMathClz32:
113 #if defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_S390X)
114  return true;
115 #elif defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM)
116  return CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ARMv8);
117 #elif defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64)
118  return CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LZCNT);
119 #elif defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32)
120  return CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB);
121 #elif defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_PPC64) || \
122  defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_LOONG64) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_MIPS64)
123  return false;
124 #else
125 #error "V8 does not support this architecture."
126 #endif
127  }
128 }

130 class FunctionContextSpecialization final : public AllStatic {
131  public:
132  static compiler::OptionalContextRef TryToRef(
133  const MaglevCompilationUnit* unit, ValueNode* context, size_t* depth) {
134  DCHECK(unit->info()->specialize_to_function_context());
135  if (Constant* n = context->TryCast<Constant>()) {
136  return n->ref().AsContext().previous(unit->broker(), depth);
137  }
138  return {};
139  }
140 };
141 
142 } // namespace
143 
144 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetParentContext(ValueNode* node) {
145  if (CreateFunctionContext* n = node->TryCast<CreateFunctionContext>()) {
146  return n->context().node();
147  }
148 
149  if (InlinedAllocation* alloc = node->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
150  return alloc->object()->get(
151  Context::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX));
152  }
153 
154  if (CallRuntime* n = node->TryCast<CallRuntime>()) {
155  switch (n->function_id()) {
156  case Runtime::kPushBlockContext:
157  case Runtime::kPushCatchContext:
158  case Runtime::kNewFunctionContext:
159  return n->context().node();
160  default:
161  break;
162  }
163  }
164 
165  return nullptr;
166 }
167 
168 // Attempts to walk up the context chain through the graph in order to reduce
169 // depth and thus the number of runtime loads.
170 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MinimizeContextChainDepth(ValueNode** context,
171  size_t* depth) {
172  while (*depth > 0) {
173  ValueNode* parent_context = TryGetParentContext(*context);
174  if (parent_context == nullptr) return;
175  *context = parent_context;
176  (*depth)--;
177  }
178 }
179 
180 void MaglevGraphBuilder::EscapeContext() {
181  ValueNode* context = GetContext();
182  if (InlinedAllocation* alloc = context->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
183  alloc->ForceEscaping();
184  }
185 }

187 class CallArguments {
188  public:
189  enum Mode {
190  kDefault,
191  kWithSpread,
192  kWithArrayLike,
193  };
194 
195  CallArguments(ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode,
196  interpreter::RegisterList reglist,
197  const InterpreterFrameState& frame, Mode mode = kDefault)
198  : receiver_mode_(receiver_mode),
199  args_(reglist.register_count()),
200  mode_(mode) {
201  for (int i = 0; i < reglist.register_count(); i++) {
202  args_[i] = frame.get(reglist[i]);
203  }
204  DCHECK_IMPLIES(args_.size() == 0,
205  receiver_mode == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
206  DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode != kDefault,
207  receiver_mode == ConvertReceiverMode::kAny);
208  DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode == kWithArrayLike, args_.size() == 2);
209  }
210 
211  explicit CallArguments(ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode)
212  : receiver_mode_(receiver_mode), args_(), mode_(kDefault) {
213  DCHECK_EQ(receiver_mode, ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
214  }
215 
216  CallArguments(ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode,
217  std::initializer_list<ValueNode*> args, Mode mode = kDefault)
218  : receiver_mode_(receiver_mode), args_(args), mode_(mode) {
219  DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode != kDefault,
220  receiver_mode == ConvertReceiverMode::kAny);
221  DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode == kWithArrayLike, args_.size() == 2);
222  CheckArgumentsAreNotConversionNodes();
223  }
224 
225  CallArguments(ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode,
226  base::SmallVector<ValueNode*, 8>&& args, Mode mode = kDefault)
227  : receiver_mode_(receiver_mode), args_(std::move(args)), mode_(mode) {
228  DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode != kDefault,
229  receiver_mode == ConvertReceiverMode::kAny);
230  DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode == kWithArrayLike, args_.size() == 2);
231  CheckArgumentsAreNotConversionNodes();
232  }
233 
234  ValueNode* receiver() const {
235  if (receiver_mode_ == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
236  return nullptr;
237  }
238  return args_[0];
239  }
240 
241  void set_receiver(ValueNode* receiver) {
242  if (receiver_mode_ == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
243  args_.insert(args_.data(), receiver);
244  receiver_mode_ = ConvertReceiverMode::kAny;
245  } else {
246  DCHECK(!receiver->properties().is_conversion());
247  args_[0] = receiver;
248  }
249  }
250 
251  ValueNode* array_like_argument() {
252  DCHECK_EQ(mode_, kWithArrayLike);
253  DCHECK_GT(count(), 0);
254  return args_[args_.size() - 1];
255  }
256 
257  size_t count() const {
258  if (receiver_mode_ == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
259  return args_.size();
260  }
261  return args_.size() - 1;
262  }
263 
264  size_t count_with_receiver() const { return count() + 1; }
265 
266  ValueNode* operator[](size_t i) const {
267  if (receiver_mode_ != ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
268  i++;
269  }
270  if (i >= args_.size()) return nullptr;
271  return args_[i];
272  }
273 
274  void set_arg(size_t i, ValueNode* node) {
275  if (receiver_mode_ != ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
276  i++;
277  }
278  DCHECK_LT(i, args_.size());
279  DCHECK(!node->properties().is_conversion());
280  args_[i] = node;
281  }
282 
283  Mode mode() const { return mode_; }
284 
285  ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode() const { return receiver_mode_; }
286 
287  void PopArrayLikeArgument() {
288  DCHECK_EQ(mode_, kWithArrayLike);
289  DCHECK_GT(count(), 0);
290  args_.pop_back();
291  }
292 
293  void PopReceiver(ConvertReceiverMode new_receiver_mode) {
294  DCHECK_NE(receiver_mode_, ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
295  DCHECK_NE(new_receiver_mode, ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
296  DCHECK_GT(args_.size(), 0); // We have at least a receiver to pop!
297  // TODO(victorgomes): Do this better!
298  for (size_t i = 0; i < args_.size() - 1; i++) {
299  args_[i] = args_[i + 1];
300  }
301  args_.pop_back();
302 
303  // If there is no non-receiver argument to become the new receiver,
304  // consider the new receiver to be known undefined.
305  receiver_mode_ = args_.empty() ? ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined
306  : new_receiver_mode;
307  }
308 
309  private:
310  ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode_;
311  base::SmallVector<ValueNode*, 8> args_;
312  Mode mode_;
313 
314  void CheckArgumentsAreNotConversionNodes() {
315 #ifdef DEBUG
316  // Arguments can leak to the interpreter frame if the call is inlined,
317  // conversions should be stored in known_node_aspects/NodeInfo.
318  for (ValueNode* arg : args_) {
319  DCHECK(!arg->properties().is_conversion());
320  }
321 #endif // DEBUG
322  }
323 };
324 
325 class V8_NODISCARD MaglevGraphBuilder::SaveCallSpeculationScope {
326  public:
327  explicit SaveCallSpeculationScope(
328  MaglevGraphBuilder* builder,
329  compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source = compiler::FeedbackSource())
330  : builder_(builder) {
331  saved_ = builder_->current_speculation_feedback_;
332  // Only set the current speculation feedback if speculation is allowed.
333  SpeculationMode mode =
334  GetSpeculationMode(builder_->broker(), feedback_source);
335  if (mode != SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
336  builder->current_speculation_feedback_ = feedback_source;
337  builder_->current_speculation_mode_ = mode;
338  } else {
339  builder->current_speculation_feedback_ = compiler::FeedbackSource();
340  builder_->current_speculation_mode_ =
341  SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation;
342  }
343  }
344  ~SaveCallSpeculationScope() {
345  builder_->current_speculation_feedback_ = saved_;
346  builder_->current_speculation_mode_ = saved_mode_;
347  }
348 
349  const compiler::FeedbackSource& value() { return saved_; }
350 
351  private:
352  MaglevGraphBuilder* builder_;
353  compiler::FeedbackSource saved_;
354  SpeculationMode saved_mode_;
355 
356  static SpeculationMode GetSpeculationMode(
357  compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker,
358  compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source) {
359  if (!feedback_source.IsValid())
360  return SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation;
361  compiler::ProcessedFeedback const& processed_feedback =
362  broker->GetFeedbackForCall(feedback_source);
363  if (processed_feedback.IsInsufficient())
364  return SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation;
365  return processed_feedback.AsCall().speculation_mode();
366  }
367 };

382 }

384 class V8_NODISCARD MaglevGraphBuilder::DeoptFrameScope {
385  public:
386  DeoptFrameScope(MaglevGraphBuilder* builder, Builtin continuation,
387  compiler::OptionalJSFunctionRef maybe_js_target = {})
388  : builder_(builder),
389  parent_(builder->current_deopt_scope_),
390  data_(DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData{
391  continuation, {}, builder->GetContext(), maybe_js_target}) {
392  builder_->current_interpreter_frame().virtual_objects().Snapshot();
393  builder_->current_deopt_scope_ = this;
394  builder_->AddDeoptUse(
395  data_.get<DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData>().context);
396  DCHECK(data_.get<DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData>()
397  .parameters.empty());
398  }
399 
400  DeoptFrameScope(MaglevGraphBuilder* builder, Builtin continuation,
401  compiler::OptionalJSFunctionRef maybe_js_target,
402  base::Vector<ValueNode* const> parameters)
403  : builder_(builder),
404  parent_(builder->current_deopt_scope_),
405  data_(DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData{
406  continuation, builder->zone()->CloneVector(parameters),
407  builder->GetContext(), maybe_js_target}) {
408  builder_->current_interpreter_frame().virtual_objects().Snapshot();
409  builder_->current_deopt_scope_ = this;
410  builder_->AddDeoptUse(
411  data_.get<DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData>().context);
412  if (parameters.size() > 0) {
413  if (InlinedAllocation* receiver =
414  parameters[0]->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
415  // We escape the first argument, since the builtin continuation call can
416  // trigger a stack iteration, which expects the receiver to be a
417  // meterialized object.
418  receiver->ForceEscaping();
419  }
420  }
421  for (ValueNode* node :
422  data_.get<DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData>().parameters) {
423  builder_->AddDeoptUse(node);
424  }
425  }
426 
427  DeoptFrameScope(MaglevGraphBuilder* builder, ValueNode* receiver)
428  : builder_(builder),
429  parent_(builder->current_deopt_scope_),
430  data_(DeoptFrame::ConstructInvokeStubFrameData{
431  *builder->compilation_unit(), builder->current_source_position_,
432  receiver, builder->GetContext()}) {
433  builder_->current_interpreter_frame().virtual_objects().Snapshot();
434  builder_->current_deopt_scope_ = this;
435  builder_->AddDeoptUse(
436  data_.get<DeoptFrame::ConstructInvokeStubFrameData>().receiver);
437  builder_->AddDeoptUse(
438  data_.get<DeoptFrame::ConstructInvokeStubFrameData>().context);
439  }
440 
441  ~DeoptFrameScope() {
442  builder_->current_deopt_scope_ = parent_;
443  // We might have cached a checkpointed frame which includes this scope;
444  // reset it just in case.
445  builder_->latest_checkpointed_frame_.reset();
446  }
447 
448  DeoptFrameScope* parent() const { return parent_; }
449 
450  bool IsLazyDeoptContinuationFrame() const {
451  if (data_.tag() != DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame) {
452  return false;
453  }
454  switch (data_.get<DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame>()
455  .builtin_id) {
456  case Builtin::kGetIteratorWithFeedbackLazyDeoptContinuation:
457  case Builtin::kCallIteratorWithFeedbackLazyDeoptContinuation:
458  case Builtin::kArrayForEachLoopLazyDeoptContinuation:
459  case Builtin::kArrayMapLoopLazyDeoptContinuation:
460  case Builtin::kGenericLazyDeoptContinuation:
461  case Builtin::kToBooleanLazyDeoptContinuation:
462  return true;
463  default:
464  return false;
465  }
466  }
467 
468  DeoptFrame::FrameData& data() { return data_; }
469  const DeoptFrame::FrameData& data() const { return data_; }
470 
471  private:
472  MaglevGraphBuilder* builder_;
473  DeoptFrameScope* parent_;
474  DeoptFrame::FrameData data_;
475 };

489 class MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label {
490  public:
491  Label(MaglevSubGraphBuilder* sub_builder, int predecessor_count)
492  : predecessor_count_(predecessor_count),
493  liveness_(
494  sub_builder->builder_->zone()->New<compiler::BytecodeLivenessState>(
495  sub_builder->compilation_unit_->register_count(),
496  sub_builder->builder_->zone())) {}
497  Label(MaglevSubGraphBuilder* sub_builder, int predecessor_count,
498  std::initializer_list<Variable*> vars)
499  : Label(sub_builder, predecessor_count) {
500  for (Variable* var : vars) {
501  liveness_->MarkRegisterLive(var->pseudo_register_.index());
502  }
503  }
504 
505  private:
506  explicit Label(MergePointInterpreterFrameState* merge_state,
507  BasicBlock* basic_block)
508  : merge_state_(merge_state), ref_(basic_block) {}
509 
510  friend class MaglevSubGraphBuilder;
511  friend class BranchBuilder;
512  MergePointInterpreterFrameState* merge_state_ = nullptr;
513  int predecessor_count_ = -1;
514  compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness_ = nullptr;
515  BasicBlockRef ref_;
516 };

545 
546 void MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::StartFallthroughBlock(
547  BasicBlock* predecessor) {
548  switch (mode()) {
549  case kBytecodeJumpTarget: {
550  auto& data = data_.bytecode_target;
551  if (data.patch_accumulator_scope &&
552  (data.patch_accumulator_scope->node_ == builder_->GetAccumulator())) {
553  SetAccumulatorInBranch(BranchType::kBranchIfTrue);
554  builder_->MergeIntoFrameState(predecessor, data.jump_target_offset);
555  SetAccumulatorInBranch(BranchType::kBranchIfFalse);
556  builder_->StartFallthroughBlock(data.fallthrough_offset, predecessor);
557  } else {
558  builder_->MergeIntoFrameState(predecessor, data.jump_target_offset);
559  builder_->StartFallthroughBlock(data.fallthrough_offset, predecessor);
560  }
561  break;
562  }
563  case kLabelJumpTarget:
564  auto& data = data_.label_target;
565  sub_builder_->MergeIntoLabel(data.jump_label, predecessor);
566  builder_->StartNewBlock(predecessor, nullptr, data.fallthrough);
567  break;
568  }
569 }
570 
571 void MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::SetAccumulatorInBranch(
572  BranchType jump_type) const {
573  DCHECK_EQ(mode(), kBytecodeJumpTarget);
574  auto& data = data_.bytecode_target;
575  if (branch_specialization_mode_ == BranchSpecializationMode::kAlwaysBoolean) {
576  builder_->SetAccumulatorInBranch(builder_->GetBooleanConstant(
577  data.patch_accumulator_scope->jump_type_ == jump_type));
578  } else if (data.patch_accumulator_scope->jump_type_ == jump_type) {
579  builder_->SetAccumulatorInBranch(
580  builder_->GetRootConstant(data.patch_accumulator_scope->root_index_));
581  } else {
582  builder_->SetAccumulatorInBranch(data.patch_accumulator_scope->node_);
583  }
584 }
585 
586 BasicBlockRef* MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::jump_target() {
587  switch (mode()) {
588  case kBytecodeJumpTarget:
589  return &builder_->jump_targets_[data_.bytecode_target.jump_target_offset];
590  case kLabelJumpTarget:
591  return &data_.label_target.jump_label->ref_;
592  }
593 }
594 
595 BasicBlockRef* MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::fallthrough() {
596  switch (mode()) {
597  case kBytecodeJumpTarget:
598  return &builder_->jump_targets_[data_.bytecode_target.fallthrough_offset];
599  case kLabelJumpTarget:
600  return &data_.label_target.fallthrough;
601  }
602 }
603 
604 BasicBlockRef* MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::true_target() {
605  return jump_type_ == BranchType::kBranchIfTrue ? jump_target()
606  : fallthrough();
607 }
608 
609 BasicBlockRef* MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::false_target() {
610  return jump_type_ == BranchType::kBranchIfFalse ? jump_target()
611  : fallthrough();
612 }
613 
614 MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::FromBool(
615  bool value) const {
616  switch (mode()) {
617  case kBytecodeJumpTarget: {
618  BranchType type_if_need_to_jump =
619  (value ? BranchType::kBranchIfTrue : BranchType::kBranchIfFalse);
620  builder_->MarkBranchDeadAndJumpIfNeeded(jump_type_ ==
621  type_if_need_to_jump);
622  return BranchResult::kDefault;
623  }
624  case kLabelJumpTarget:
625  return value ? BranchResult::kAlwaysTrue : BranchResult::kAlwaysFalse;
626  }
627 }
628 
629 template <typename ControlNodeT, typename... Args>
630 MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::Build(
631  std::initializer_list<ValueNode*> control_inputs, Args&&... args) {
632  static_assert(IsConditionalControlNode(Node::opcode_of<ControlNodeT>));
633  BasicBlock* block = builder_->FinishBlock<ControlNodeT>(
634  control_inputs, std::forward<Args>(args)..., true_target(),
635  false_target());
636  StartFallthroughBlock(block);
637  return BranchResult::kDefault;
638 }
639 
640 MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder(
641  MaglevGraphBuilder* builder, int variable_count)
642  : builder_(builder),
643  compilation_unit_(MaglevCompilationUnit::NewDummy(
644  builder->zone(), builder->compilation_unit(), variable_count, 0, 0)),
645  pseudo_frame_(*compilation_unit_, nullptr, VirtualObjectList()) {
646  // We need to set a context, since this is unconditional in the frame state,
647  // so set it to the real context.
648  pseudo_frame_.set(interpreter::Register::current_context(),
649  builder_->current_interpreter_frame().get(
650  interpreter::Register::current_context()));
651  DCHECK_NULL(pseudo_frame_.known_node_aspects());
652 }
653 
654 MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::LoopLabel
655 MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::BeginLoop(
656  std::initializer_list<Variable*> loop_vars) {
657  // Create fake liveness and loop info for the loop, with all given loop vars
658  // set to be live and assigned inside the loop.
659  compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* loop_header_liveness =
660  builder_->zone()->New<compiler::BytecodeLivenessState>(
661  compilation_unit_->register_count(), builder_->zone());
662  compiler::LoopInfo* loop_info = builder_->zone()->New<compiler::LoopInfo>(
663  -1, 0, kMaxInt, compilation_unit_->parameter_count(),
664  compilation_unit_->register_count(), builder_->zone());
665  for (Variable* var : loop_vars) {
666  loop_header_liveness->MarkRegisterLive(var->pseudo_register_.index());
667  loop_info->assignments().Add(var->pseudo_register_);
668  }
669 
670  // Finish the current block, jumping (as a fallthrough) to the loop header.
671  BasicBlockRef loop_header_ref;
672  BasicBlock* loop_predecessor =
673  builder_->FinishBlock<Jump>({}, &loop_header_ref);
674 
675  // Create a state for the loop header, with two predecessors (the above jump
676  // and the back edge), and initialise with the current state.
677  MergePointInterpreterFrameState* loop_state =
678  MergePointInterpreterFrameState::NewForLoop(
679  pseudo_frame_, builder_->graph(), *compilation_unit_, 0, 2,
680  loop_header_liveness, loop_info);
681 
682  {
683  BorrowParentKnownNodeAspectsAndVOs borrow(this);
684  loop_state->Merge(builder_, *compilation_unit_, pseudo_frame_,
685  loop_predecessor);
686  }
687 
688  // Start a new basic block for the loop.
689  DCHECK_NULL(pseudo_frame_.known_node_aspects());
690  pseudo_frame_.CopyFrom(*compilation_unit_, *loop_state);
691  MoveKnownNodeAspectsAndVOsToParent();
692 
693  builder_->ProcessMergePointPredecessors(*loop_state, loop_header_ref);
694  builder_->StartNewBlock(nullptr, loop_state, loop_header_ref);
695 
696  return LoopLabel{loop_state, loop_header_ref.block_ptr()};
697 }
698 
699 template <typename ControlNodeT, typename... Args>
700 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::GotoIfTrue(
701  Label* true_target, std::initializer_list<ValueNode*> control_inputs,
702  Args&&... args) {
703  static_assert(IsConditionalControlNode(Node::opcode_of<ControlNodeT>));
704 
705  BasicBlockRef fallthrough_ref;
706 
707  // Pass through to FinishBlock, converting Labels to BasicBlockRefs and the
708  // fallthrough label to the fallthrough ref.
709  BasicBlock* block = builder_->FinishBlock<ControlNodeT>(
710  control_inputs, std::forward<Args>(args)..., &true_target->ref_,
711  &fallthrough_ref);
712 
713  MergeIntoLabel(true_target, block);
714 
715  builder_->StartNewBlock(block, nullptr, fallthrough_ref);
716 }
717 
718 template <typename ControlNodeT, typename... Args>
719 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::GotoIfFalse(
720  Label* false_target, std::initializer_list<ValueNode*> control_inputs,
721  Args&&... args) {
722  static_assert(IsConditionalControlNode(Node::opcode_of<ControlNodeT>));
723 
724  BasicBlockRef fallthrough_ref;
725 
726  // Pass through to FinishBlock, converting Labels to BasicBlockRefs and the
727  // fallthrough label to the fallthrough ref.
728  BasicBlock* block = builder_->FinishBlock<ControlNodeT>(
729  control_inputs, std::forward<Args>(args)..., &fallthrough_ref,
730  &false_target->ref_);
731 
732  MergeIntoLabel(false_target, block);
733 
734  builder_->StartNewBlock(block, nullptr, fallthrough_ref);
735 }
736 
737 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::GotoOrTrim(Label* label) {
738  if (builder_->current_block_ == nullptr) {
739  ReducePredecessorCount(label);
740  return;
741  }
742  Goto(label);
743 }
744 
745 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Goto(Label* label) {
746  CHECK_NOT_NULL(builder_->current_block_);
747  BasicBlock* block = builder_->FinishBlock<Jump>({}, &label->ref_);
748  MergeIntoLabel(label, block);
749 }
750 
751 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::ReducePredecessorCount(
752  Label* label, unsigned num) {
753  DCHECK_GE(label->predecessor_count_, num);
754  if (num == 0) {
755  return;
756  }
757  label->predecessor_count_ -= num;
758  if (label->merge_state_ != nullptr) {
759  label->merge_state_->MergeDead(*compilation_unit_, num);
760  }
761 }
762 
763 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::EndLoop(LoopLabel* loop_label) {
764  if (builder_->current_block_ == nullptr) {
765  loop_label->merge_state_->MergeDeadLoop(*compilation_unit_);
766  return;
767  }
768 
769  BasicBlock* block =
770  builder_->FinishBlock<JumpLoop>({}, loop_label->loop_header_);
771  {
772  BorrowParentKnownNodeAspectsAndVOs borrow(this);
773  loop_label->merge_state_->MergeLoop(builder_, *compilation_unit_,
774  pseudo_frame_, block);
775  }
776  block->set_predecessor_id(loop_label->merge_state_->predecessor_count() - 1);
777 }
778 
779 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::TrimPredecessorsAndBind(
780  Label* label) {
781  int predecessors_so_far = label->merge_state_ == nullptr
782  ? 0
783  : label->merge_state_->predecessors_so_far();
784  DCHECK_LE(predecessors_so_far, label->predecessor_count_);
785  builder_->current_block_ = nullptr;
786  ReducePredecessorCount(label,
787  label->predecessor_count_ - predecessors_so_far);
788  if (predecessors_so_far == 0) return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
789  Bind(label);
790  return ReduceResult::Done();
791 }
792 
793 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Bind(Label* label) {
794  DCHECK_NULL(builder_->current_block_);
795 
796  DCHECK_NULL(pseudo_frame_.known_node_aspects());
797  pseudo_frame_.CopyFrom(*compilation_unit_, *label->merge_state_);
798  MoveKnownNodeAspectsAndVOsToParent();
799 
800  CHECK_EQ(label->merge_state_->predecessors_so_far(),
801  label->predecessor_count_);
802 
803  builder_->ProcessMergePointPredecessors(*label->merge_state_, label->ref_);
804  builder_->StartNewBlock(nullptr, label->merge_state_, label->ref_);
805 }
806 
807 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::set(Variable& var,
808  ValueNode* value) {
809  pseudo_frame_.set(var.pseudo_register_, value);
810 }
811 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::get(
812  const Variable& var) const {
813  return pseudo_frame_.get(var.pseudo_register_);
814 }
815 
816 template <typename FCond, typename FTrue, typename FFalse>
817 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Branch(
818  std::initializer_list<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable*> vars, FCond cond,
819  FTrue if_true, FFalse if_false) {
820  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label else_branch(this, 1);
821  BranchBuilder builder(builder_, this, BranchType::kBranchIfFalse,
822  &else_branch);
823  BranchResult branch_result = cond(builder);
824  if (branch_result == BranchResult::kAlwaysTrue) {
825  return if_true();
826  }
827  if (branch_result == BranchResult::kAlwaysFalse) {
828  return if_false();
829  }
830  DCHECK(branch_result == BranchResult::kDefault);
831  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label done(this, 2, vars);
832  MaybeReduceResult result_if_true = if_true();
833  CHECK(result_if_true.IsDone());
834  GotoOrTrim(&done);
835  Bind(&else_branch);
836  MaybeReduceResult result_if_false = if_false();
837  CHECK(result_if_false.IsDone());
838  if (result_if_true.IsDoneWithAbort() && result_if_false.IsDoneWithAbort()) {
839  return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
840  }
841  GotoOrTrim(&done);
842  Bind(&done);
843  return ReduceResult::Done();
844 }
845 
846 template <typename FCond, typename FTrue, typename FFalse>
847 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::Select(FCond cond, FTrue if_true,
848  FFalse if_false) {
849  MaglevSubGraphBuilder subgraph(this, 1);
850  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label else_branch(&subgraph, 1);
851  BranchBuilder builder(this, &subgraph, BranchType::kBranchIfFalse,
852  &else_branch);
853  BranchResult branch_result = cond(builder);
854  if (branch_result == BranchResult::kAlwaysTrue) {
855  return if_true();
856  }
857  if (branch_result == BranchResult::kAlwaysFalse) {
858  return if_false();
859  }
860  DCHECK(branch_result == BranchResult::kDefault);
861  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable ret_val(0);
862  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label done(&subgraph, 2, {&ret_val});
863  subgraph.set(ret_val, if_true());
864  subgraph.Goto(&done);
865  subgraph.Bind(&else_branch);
866  subgraph.set(ret_val, if_false());
867  subgraph.Goto(&done);
868  subgraph.Bind(&done);
869  return subgraph.get(ret_val);
870 }
871 
872 template <typename FCond, typename FTrue, typename FFalse>
873 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::SelectReduction(FCond cond, FTrue if_true,
874  FFalse if_false) {
875  MaglevSubGraphBuilder subgraph(this, 1);
876  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label else_branch(&subgraph, 1);
877  BranchBuilder builder(this, &subgraph, BranchType::kBranchIfFalse,
878  &else_branch);
879  BranchResult branch_result = cond(builder);
880  if (branch_result == BranchResult::kAlwaysTrue) {
881  return if_true();
882  }
883  if (branch_result == BranchResult::kAlwaysFalse) {
884  return if_false();
885  }
886  DCHECK(branch_result == BranchResult::kDefault);
887  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable ret_val(0);
888  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label done(&subgraph, 2, {&ret_val});
889  MaybeReduceResult result_if_true = if_true();
890  CHECK(result_if_true.IsDone());
891  if (result_if_true.IsDoneWithValue()) {
892  subgraph.set(ret_val, result_if_true.value());
893  }
894  subgraph.GotoOrTrim(&done);
895  subgraph.Bind(&else_branch);
896  MaybeReduceResult result_if_false = if_false();
897  CHECK(result_if_false.IsDone());
898  if (result_if_true.IsDoneWithAbort() && result_if_false.IsDoneWithAbort()) {
899  return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
900  }
901  if (result_if_false.IsDoneWithValue()) {
902  subgraph.set(ret_val, result_if_false.value());
903  }
904  subgraph.GotoOrTrim(&done);
905  subgraph.Bind(&done);
906  return subgraph.get(ret_val);
907 }
908 
909 // Known node aspects for the pseudo frame are null aside from when merging --
910 // before each merge, we should borrow the node aspects from the parent
911 // builder, and after each merge point, we should copy the node aspects back
912 // to the parent. This is so that the parent graph builder can update its own
913 // known node aspects without having to worry about this pseudo frame.
914 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::
915  TakeKnownNodeAspectsAndVOsFromParent() {
916  DCHECK_NULL(pseudo_frame_.known_node_aspects());
917  DCHECK(pseudo_frame_.virtual_objects().is_empty());
918  pseudo_frame_.set_known_node_aspects(
919  builder_->current_interpreter_frame_.known_node_aspects());
920  pseudo_frame_.set_virtual_objects(
921  builder_->current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects());
922 }
923 
924 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::
925  MoveKnownNodeAspectsAndVOsToParent() {
926  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(pseudo_frame_.known_node_aspects());
927  builder_->current_interpreter_frame_.set_known_node_aspects(
928  pseudo_frame_.known_node_aspects());
929  pseudo_frame_.clear_known_node_aspects();
930  builder_->current_interpreter_frame_.set_virtual_objects(
931  pseudo_frame_.virtual_objects());
932  pseudo_frame_.set_virtual_objects(VirtualObjectList());
933 }
934 
935 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::MergeIntoLabel(
936  Label* label, BasicBlock* predecessor) {
937  BorrowParentKnownNodeAspectsAndVOs borrow(this);
938 
939  if (label->merge_state_ == nullptr) {
940  // If there's no merge state, allocate a new one.
941  label->merge_state_ = MergePointInterpreterFrameState::New(
942  *compilation_unit_, pseudo_frame_, 0, label->predecessor_count_,
943  predecessor, label->liveness_);
944  } else {
945  // If there already is a frame state, merge.
946  label->merge_state_->Merge(builder_, *compilation_unit_, pseudo_frame_,
947  predecessor);
948  }
949 }
950 
951 MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevGraphBuilder(LocalIsolate* local_isolate,
952  MaglevCompilationUnit* compilation_unit,
953  Graph* graph,
954  MaglevCallerDetails* caller_details)
955  : local_isolate_(local_isolate),
956  compilation_unit_(compilation_unit),
957  caller_details_(caller_details),
958  graph_(graph),
959  bytecode_analysis_(bytecode().object(), zone(),
960  compilation_unit->osr_offset(), true),
961  iterator_(bytecode().object()),
962  source_position_iterator_(bytecode().SourcePositionTable(broker())),
963  allow_loop_peeling_(v8_flags.maglev_loop_peeling),
964  loop_effects_stack_(zone()),
965  decremented_predecessor_offsets_(zone()),
966  loop_headers_to_peel_(bytecode().length(), zone()),
967  current_source_position_(),
968  // Add an extra jump_target slot for the inline exit if needed.
969  jump_targets_(zone()->AllocateArray<BasicBlockRef>(
970  bytecode().length() + (is_inline() ? 1 : 0))),
971  // Overallocate merge_states_ by one to allow always looking up the
972  // next offset. This overallocated slot can also be used for the inline
973  // exit when needed.
974  merge_states_(zone()->AllocateArray<MergePointInterpreterFrameState*>(
975  bytecode().length() + 1)),
976  current_interpreter_frame_(
977  *compilation_unit_,
978  is_inline() ? caller_details->known_node_aspects
979  : compilation_unit_->zone()->New<KnownNodeAspects>(
980  compilation_unit_->zone()),
981  is_inline() ? caller_details->deopt_frame->GetVirtualObjects()
982  : VirtualObjectList()),
983  is_turbolev_(compilation_unit->info()->is_turbolev()),
984  entrypoint_(compilation_unit->is_osr()
985  ? bytecode_analysis_.osr_entry_point()
986  : 0),
987  catch_block_stack_(zone()),
988  unobserved_context_slot_stores_(zone()) {
989  memset(merge_states_, 0,
990  (bytecode().length() + 1) * sizeof(InterpreterFrameState*));
991  // Default construct basic block refs.
992  // TODO(leszeks): This could be a memset of nullptr to ..._jump_targets_.
993  for (int i = 0; i < bytecode().length(); ++i) {
994  new (&jump_targets_[i]) BasicBlockRef();
995  }
996 
997  if (is_inline()) {
998  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(caller_details);
999  DCHECK_GT(compilation_unit->inlining_depth(), 0);
1000  // The allocation/initialisation logic here relies on inline_exit_offset
1001  // being the offset one past the end of the bytecode.
1002  DCHECK_EQ(inline_exit_offset(), bytecode().length());
1003  merge_states_[inline_exit_offset()] = nullptr;
1004  new (&jump_targets_[inline_exit_offset()]) BasicBlockRef();
1005  if (caller_details->loop_effects) {
1006  loop_effects_ = caller_details->loop_effects;
1007  loop_effects_stack_.push_back(loop_effects_);
1008  }
1009  unobserved_context_slot_stores_ =
1010  caller_details->unobserved_context_slot_stores;
1011  }
1012 
1013  CHECK_IMPLIES(compilation_unit_->is_osr(), graph_->is_osr());
1014  CHECK_EQ(compilation_unit_->info()->toplevel_osr_offset() !=
1015  BytecodeOffset::None(),
1016  graph_->is_osr());
1017  if (compilation_unit_->is_osr()) {
1018  CHECK(!is_inline());
1019 
1020  // Make sure that we're at a valid OSR entrypoint.
1021  //
1022  // This is also a defense-in-depth check to make sure that we're not
1023  // compiling invalid bytecode if the OSR offset is wrong (e.g. because it
1024  // belongs to different bytecode).
1025  //
1026  // OSR'ing into the middle of a loop is currently not supported. There
1027  // should not be any issue with OSR'ing outside of loops, just we currently
1028  // dont do it...
1029  interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator it(bytecode().object());
1030  it.AdvanceTo(compilation_unit_->osr_offset().ToInt());
1031  CHECK(it.CurrentBytecodeIsValidOSREntry());
1032  CHECK_EQ(entrypoint_, it.GetJumpTargetOffset());
1033 
1034  iterator_.AdvanceTo(entrypoint_);
1035 
1036  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
1037  std::cout << "- Non-standard entrypoint @" << entrypoint_
1038  << " by OSR from @" << compilation_unit_->osr_offset().ToInt()
1039  << std::endl;
1040  }
1041  }
1042  CHECK_IMPLIES(!compilation_unit_->is_osr(), entrypoint_ == 0);
1043 
1044  CalculatePredecessorCounts();
1045 }
1046 
1047 void MaglevGraphBuilder::StartPrologue() {
1048  current_block_ = zone()->New<BasicBlock>(nullptr, zone());
1049 }
1050 
1051 BasicBlock* MaglevGraphBuilder::EndPrologue() {
1052  BasicBlock* first_block;
1053  if (!is_inline() &&
1054  (v8_flags.maglev_hoist_osr_value_phi_untagging && graph_->is_osr())) {
1055  first_block =
1056  FinishBlock<CheckpointedJump>({}, &jump_targets_[entrypoint_]);
1057  } else {
1058  first_block = FinishBlock<Jump>({}, &jump_targets_[entrypoint_]);
1059  }
1060  MergeIntoFrameState(first_block, entrypoint_);
1061  return first_block;
1062 }

1064 void MaglevGraphBuilder::SetArgument(int i, ValueNode* value) {
1065  interpreter::Register reg = interpreter::Register::FromParameterIndex(i);
1066  current_interpreter_frame_.set(reg, value);
1067 }
1068 
1069 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetArgument(int i) {
1070  DCHECK_LT(i, parameter_count());
1071  interpreter::Register reg = interpreter::Register::FromParameterIndex(i);
1072  return current_interpreter_frame_.get(reg);
1073 }
1074 
1075 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetInlinedArgument(int i) {
1076  DCHECK(is_inline());

1078  return caller_details_->arguments[i];
1079 }

1081 void MaglevGraphBuilder::InitializeRegister(interpreter::Register reg,
1082  ValueNode* value) {
1083  current_interpreter_frame_.set(
1084  reg, value ? value : AddNewNode<InitialValue>({}, reg));
1085 }
1086 
1087 void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildRegisterFrameInitialization(
1088  ValueNode* context, ValueNode* closure, ValueNode* new_target) {
1089  if (closure == nullptr &&
1090  compilation_unit_->info()->specialize_to_function_context()) {
1091  compiler::JSFunctionRef function = compiler::MakeRefAssumeMemoryFence(
1092  broker(), broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
1093  compilation_unit_->info()->toplevel_function()));
1094  closure = GetConstant(function);
1095  context = GetConstant(function.context(broker()));
1096  }
1097  InitializeRegister(interpreter::Register::current_context(), context);
1098  InitializeRegister(interpreter::Register::function_closure(), closure);
1099 
1100  EnsureType(GetContext(), NodeType::kContext);
1101  EnsureType(GetClosure(), NodeType::kJSFunction);
1102 
1103  interpreter::Register new_target_or_generator_register =
1104  bytecode().incoming_new_target_or_generator_register();
1105 
1106  int register_index = 0;
1107 
1108  if (compilation_unit_->is_osr()) {
1109  for (; register_index < register_count(); register_index++) {
1110  auto val =
1111  AddNewNode<InitialValue>({}, interpreter::Register(register_index));
1112  InitializeRegister(interpreter::Register(register_index), val);
1113  graph_->osr_values().push_back(val);
1114  }
1115  return;
1116  }
1117 
1118  // TODO(leszeks): Don't emit if not needed.
1119  ValueNode* undefined_value = GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
1120  if (new_target_or_generator_register.is_valid()) {
1121  int new_target_index = new_target_or_generator_register.index();
1122  for (; register_index < new_target_index; register_index++) {
1123  current_interpreter_frame_.set(interpreter::Register(register_index),
1124  undefined_value);
1125  }
1126  current_interpreter_frame_.set(
1127  new_target_or_generator_register,
1128  new_target ? new_target
1129  : GetRegisterInput(kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister));
1130  register_index++;
1131  }
1132  for (; register_index < register_count(); register_index++) {
1133  InitializeRegister(interpreter::Register(register_index), undefined_value);
1134  }
1135 }
1136 
1137 void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildMergeStates() {
1138  auto offset_and_info = bytecode_analysis().GetLoopInfos().begin();
1139  auto end = bytecode_analysis().GetLoopInfos().end();
1140  while (offset_and_info != end && offset_and_info->first < entrypoint_) {
1141  ++offset_and_info;
1142  }
1143  for (; offset_and_info != end; ++offset_and_info) {
1144  int offset = offset_and_info->first;
1145  const compiler::LoopInfo& loop_info = offset_and_info->second;
1146  if (loop_headers_to_peel_.Contains(offset)) {
1147  // Peeled loops are treated like normal merges at first. We will construct
1148  // the proper loop header merge state when reaching the `JumpLoop` of the
1149  // peeled iteration.
1150  continue;
1151  }
1152  const compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness = GetInLivenessFor(offset);
1153  DCHECK_NULL(merge_states_[offset]);
1154  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
1155  std::cout << "- Creating loop merge state at @" << offset << std::endl;
1156  }
1157  merge_states_[offset] = MergePointInterpreterFrameState::NewForLoop(
1158  current_interpreter_frame_, graph_, *compilation_unit_, offset,
1159  predecessor_count(offset), liveness, &loop_info);
1160  }
1161 
1162  if (bytecode().handler_table_size() > 0) {
1163  HandlerTable table(*bytecode().object());
1164  for (int i = 0; i < table.NumberOfRangeEntries(); i++) {
1165  const int offset = table.GetRangeHandler(i);
1166  const bool was_used = table.HandlerWasUsed(i);
1167  const interpreter::Register context_reg(table.GetRangeData(i));
1168  const compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness =
1169  GetInLivenessFor(offset);
1170  DCHECK_EQ(predecessor_count(offset), 0);
1171  DCHECK_NULL(merge_states_[offset]);
1172  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
1173  std::cout << "- Creating exception merge state at @" << offset
1174  << (was_used ? "" : " (never used)") << ", context register r"
1175  << context_reg.index() << std::endl;
1176  }
1177  merge_states_[offset] = MergePointInterpreterFrameState::NewForCatchBlock(
1178  *compilation_unit_, liveness, offset, was_used, context_reg, graph_);
1179  }
1180  }
1181 }
1182 
1183 namespace {
1184 
1185 template <int index, interpreter::OperandType... operands>
1186 struct GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper;
1187 
1188 // Terminal cases
1189 template <int index>
1190 struct GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<index> {
1191  static std::pair<interpreter::Register, int> GetResultLocationAndSize(
1192  const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
1193  // TODO(leszeks): This should probably actually be "UNREACHABLE" but we have
1194  // lazy deopt info for interrupt budget updates at returns, not for actual
1195  // lazy deopts, but just for stack iteration purposes.
1196  return {interpreter::Register::invalid_value(), 0};
1197  }
1198  static bool HasOutputRegisterOperand() { return false; }
1199 };
1200 
1201 template <int index, interpreter::OperandType... operands>
1202 struct GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<index, interpreter::OperandType::kRegOut,
1203  operands...> {
1204  static std::pair<interpreter::Register, int> GetResultLocationAndSize(
1205  const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
1206  // We shouldn't have any other output operands than this one.
1207  return {iterator.GetRegisterOperand(index), 1};
1208  }
1209  static bool HasOutputRegisterOperand() { return true; }
1210 };
1211 
1212 template <int index, interpreter::OperandType... operands>
1213 struct GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1214  index, interpreter::OperandType::kRegOutPair, operands...> {
1215  static std::pair<interpreter::Register, int> GetResultLocationAndSize(
1216  const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
1217  // We shouldn't have any other output operands than this one.
1218  return {iterator.GetRegisterOperand(index), 2};
1219  }
1220  static bool HasOutputRegisterOperand() { return true; }
1221 };
1222 
1223 template <int index, interpreter::OperandType... operands>
1224 struct GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1225  index, interpreter::OperandType::kRegOutTriple, operands...> {
1226  static std::pair<interpreter::Register, int> GetResultLocationAndSize(
1227  const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
1228  // We shouldn't have any other output operands than this one.
1229  DCHECK(!(GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1230  index + 1, operands...>::HasOutputRegisterOperand()));
1231  return {iterator.GetRegisterOperand(index), 3};
1232  }
1233  static bool HasOutputRegisterOperand() { return true; }
1234 };
1235 
1236 // We don't support RegOutList for lazy deopts.
1237 template <int index, interpreter::OperandType... operands>
1238 struct GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1239  index, interpreter::OperandType::kRegOutList, operands...> {
1240  static std::pair<interpreter::Register, int> GetResultLocationAndSize(
1241  const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
1242  interpreter::RegisterList list = iterator.GetRegisterListOperand(index);
1243  return {list.first_register(), list.register_count()};
1244  }
1245  static bool HasOutputRegisterOperand() { return true; }
1246 };
1247 
1248 // Induction case.
1249 template <int index, interpreter::OperandType operand,
1250  interpreter::OperandType... operands>
1251 struct GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<index, operand, operands...> {
1252  static std::pair<interpreter::Register, int> GetResultLocationAndSize(
1253  const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
1254  return GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1255  index + 1, operands...>::GetResultLocationAndSize(iterator);
1256  }
1257  static bool HasOutputRegisterOperand() {
1258  return GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1259  index + 1, operands...>::HasOutputRegisterOperand();
1260  }
1261 };
1262 
1263 template <interpreter::Bytecode bytecode,
1264  interpreter::ImplicitRegisterUse implicit_use,
1265  interpreter::OperandType... operands>
1266 std::pair<interpreter::Register, int> GetResultLocationAndSizeForBytecode(
1267  const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
1268  // We don't support output registers for implicit registers.
1269  DCHECK(!interpreter::BytecodeOperands::WritesImplicitRegister(implicit_use));
1270  if (interpreter::BytecodeOperands::WritesAccumulator(implicit_use)) {
1271  // If we write the accumulator, we shouldn't also write an output register.
1272  DCHECK(!(GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1273  0, operands...>::HasOutputRegisterOperand()));
1274  return {interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator(), 1};
1275  }
1276 
1277  // Use template magic to output a the appropriate GetRegisterOperand call and
1278  // size for this bytecode.
1279  return GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1280  0, operands...>::GetResultLocationAndSize(iterator);
1281 }
1282 
1283 } // namespace
1284 
1285 std::pair<interpreter::Register, int>
1286 MaglevGraphBuilder::GetResultLocationAndSize() const {
1287  using Bytecode = interpreter::Bytecode;
1288  using OperandType = interpreter::OperandType;
1289  using ImplicitRegisterUse = interpreter::ImplicitRegisterUse;
1290  Bytecode bytecode = iterator_.current_bytecode();
1291  // TODO(leszeks): Only emit these cases for bytecodes we know can lazy deopt.
1292  switch (bytecode) {
1293 #define CASE(Name, ...) \
1294  case Bytecode::k##Name: \
1295  return GetResultLocationAndSizeForBytecode<Bytecode::k##Name, \
1296  __VA_ARGS__>(iterator_);
1297  BYTECODE_LIST(CASE, CASE)
1298 #undef CASE
1299  }
1300  UNREACHABLE();
1301 }
1302 
1303 #ifdef DEBUG
1304 bool MaglevGraphBuilder::HasOutputRegister(interpreter::Register reg) const {
1305  interpreter::Bytecode bytecode = iterator_.current_bytecode();
1306  if (reg == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator()) {
1307  return interpreter::Bytecodes::WritesAccumulator(bytecode);
1308  }
1309  for (int i = 0; i < interpreter::Bytecodes::NumberOfOperands(bytecode); ++i) {
1310  if (interpreter::Bytecodes::IsRegisterOutputOperandType(
1311  interpreter::Bytecodes::GetOperandType(bytecode, i))) {
1312  interpreter::Register operand_reg = iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(i);
1313  int operand_range = iterator_.GetRegisterOperandRange(i);
1314  if (base::IsInRange(reg.index(), operand_reg.index(),
1315  operand_reg.index() + operand_range)) {
1316  return true;
1317  }
1318  }
1319  }
1320  return false;
1321 }
1322 #endif
1323 
1324 DeoptFrame* MaglevGraphBuilder::AddInlinedArgumentsToDeoptFrame(
1325  DeoptFrame* deopt_frame, const MaglevCompilationUnit* unit,
1326  ValueNode* closure, base::Vector<ValueNode*> args) {
1327  // Only create InlinedArgumentsDeoptFrame if we have a mismatch between
1328  // formal parameter and arguments count.
1329  if (static_cast<int>(args.size()) != unit->parameter_count()) {
1330  deopt_frame = zone()->New<InlinedArgumentsDeoptFrame>(
1331  *unit, BytecodeOffset(iterator_.current_offset()), closure, args,
1332  deopt_frame);
1333  AddDeoptUse(closure);
1334  for (ValueNode* arg : deopt_frame->as_inlined_arguments().arguments()) {
1335  AddDeoptUse(arg);
1336  }
1337  }
1338  return deopt_frame;
1339 }
1340 
1341 DeoptFrame* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetDeoptFrameForEagerCall(
1342  const MaglevCompilationUnit* unit, ValueNode* closure,
1343  base::Vector<ValueNode*> args) {
1344  // The parent resumes after the call, which is roughly equivalent to a lazy
1345  // deopt. Use the helper function directly so that we can mark the
1346  // accumulator as dead (since it'll be overwritten by this function's
1347  // return value anyway).
1348  // TODO(leszeks): This is true for our current set of
1349  // inlinings/continuations, but there might be cases in the future where it
1350  // isn't. We may need to store the relevant overwritten register in
1351  // LazyDeoptFrameScope.
1352  DCHECK(
1353  interpreter::Bytecodes::WritesAccumulator(iterator_.current_bytecode()) ||
1354  interpreter::Bytecodes::ClobbersAccumulator(
1355  iterator_.current_bytecode()));
1356  DeoptFrame* deopt_frame = zone()->New<DeoptFrame>(
1357  GetDeoptFrameForLazyDeoptHelper(interpreter::Register::invalid_value(), 0,
1358  current_deopt_scope_, true));
1359  return AddInlinedArgumentsToDeoptFrame(deopt_frame, unit, closure, args);
1360 }
1361 
1362 DeoptFrame* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetCallerDeoptFrame() {
1363  if (!is_inline()) return nullptr;
1364  return caller_details_->deopt_frame;
1365 }
1366 
1367 DeoptFrame MaglevGraphBuilder::GetLatestCheckpointedFrame() {
1368  if (in_prologue_) {
1369  return GetDeoptFrameForEntryStackCheck();
1370  }
1371  if (!latest_checkpointed_frame_) {
1372  current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects().Snapshot();
1373  latest_checkpointed_frame_.emplace(InterpretedDeoptFrame(
1374  *compilation_unit_,
1375  zone()->New<CompactInterpreterFrameState>(
1376  *compilation_unit_, GetInLiveness(), current_interpreter_frame_),
1377  GetClosure(), BytecodeOffset(iterator_.current_offset()),
1378  current_source_position_, GetCallerDeoptFrame()));
1379 
1380  latest_checkpointed_frame_->as_interpreted().frame_state()->ForEachValue(
1381  *compilation_unit_,
1382  [&](ValueNode* node, interpreter::Register) { AddDeoptUse(node); });
1383  AddDeoptUse(latest_checkpointed_frame_->as_interpreted().closure());
1384 
1385  // Skip lazy deopt builtin continuations.
1386  const DeoptFrameScope* deopt_scope = current_deopt_scope_;
1387  while (deopt_scope != nullptr &&
1388  deopt_scope->IsLazyDeoptContinuationFrame()) {
1389  deopt_scope = deopt_scope->parent();
1390  }
1391 
1392  if (deopt_scope != nullptr) {
1393  // Support exactly one eager deopt builtin continuation. This can be
1394  // expanded in the future if necessary.
1395  DCHECK_NULL(deopt_scope->parent());
1396  DCHECK_EQ(deopt_scope->data().tag(),
1397  DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame);
1398 #ifdef DEBUG
1399  if (deopt_scope->data().tag() ==
1400  DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame) {
1401  const DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData& frame =
1402  deopt_scope->data().get<DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData>();
1403  if (frame.maybe_js_target) {
1404  int stack_parameter_count =
1405  Builtins::GetStackParameterCount(frame.builtin_id);
1406  DCHECK_EQ(stack_parameter_count, frame.parameters.length());
1407  } else {
1408  CallInterfaceDescriptor descriptor =
1409  Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(frame.builtin_id);
1410  DCHECK_EQ(descriptor.GetParameterCount(), frame.parameters.length());
1411  }
1412  }
1413 #endif
1414 
1415  // Wrap the above frame in the scope frame.
1416  latest_checkpointed_frame_.emplace(
1417  deopt_scope->data(),
1418  zone()->New<DeoptFrame>(*latest_checkpointed_frame_));
1419  }
1420  }
1421  return *latest_checkpointed_frame_;
1422 }
1423 
1424 DeoptFrame MaglevGraphBuilder::GetDeoptFrameForLazyDeopt(
1425  interpreter::Register result_location, int result_size) {
1426  return GetDeoptFrameForLazyDeoptHelper(result_location, result_size,
1427  current_deopt_scope_, false);
1428 }
1429 
1430 DeoptFrame MaglevGraphBuilder::GetDeoptFrameForLazyDeoptHelper(
1431  interpreter::Register result_location, int result_size,
1432  DeoptFrameScope* scope, bool mark_accumulator_dead) {
1433  if (scope == nullptr) {
1434  compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness =
1435  zone()->New<compiler::BytecodeLivenessState>(*GetOutLiveness(), zone());
1436  // Remove result locations from liveness.
1437  if (result_location == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator()) {
1438  DCHECK_EQ(result_size, 1);
1439  liveness->MarkAccumulatorDead();
1440  mark_accumulator_dead = false;
1441  } else {
1442  DCHECK(!result_location.is_parameter());
1443  for (int i = 0; i < result_size; i++) {
1444  liveness->MarkRegisterDead(result_location.index() + i);
1445  }
1446  }
1447  // Explicitly drop the accumulator if needed.
1448  if (mark_accumulator_dead && liveness->AccumulatorIsLive()) {
1449  liveness->MarkAccumulatorDead();
1450  }
1451  current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects().Snapshot();
1452  InterpretedDeoptFrame ret(
1453  *compilation_unit_,
1454  zone()->New<CompactInterpreterFrameState>(*compilation_unit_, liveness,
1455  current_interpreter_frame_),
1456  GetClosure(), BytecodeOffset(iterator_.current_offset()),
1457  current_source_position_, GetCallerDeoptFrame());
1458  ret.frame_state()->ForEachValue(
1459  *compilation_unit_, [this](ValueNode* node, interpreter::Register reg) {
1460  // Receiver and closure values have to be materialized, even if
1461  // they don't otherwise escape.
1462  if (reg == interpreter::Register::receiver() ||
1463  reg == interpreter::Register::function_closure()) {
1464  node->add_use();
1465  } else {
1466  AddDeoptUse(node);
1467  }
1468  });
1469  AddDeoptUse(ret.closure());
1470  return ret;
1471  }
1472 
1473  // Currently only support builtin continuations for bytecodes that write to
1474  // the accumulator
1475  DCHECK(interpreter::Bytecodes::WritesOrClobbersAccumulator(
1476  iterator_.current_bytecode()));
1477 
1478 #ifdef DEBUG
1479  if (scope->data().tag() == DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame) {
1480  const DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData& frame =
1481  current_deopt_scope_->data()
1482  .get<DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData>();
1483  if (frame.maybe_js_target) {
1484  int stack_parameter_count =
1485  Builtins::GetStackParameterCount(frame.builtin_id);
1486  // The deopt input value is passed by the deoptimizer, so shouldn't be a
1487  // parameter here.
1488  DCHECK_EQ(stack_parameter_count, frame.parameters.length() + 1);
1489  } else {
1490  CallInterfaceDescriptor descriptor =
1491  Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(frame.builtin_id);
1492  // The deopt input value is passed by the deoptimizer, so shouldn't be a
1493  // parameter here.
1494  DCHECK_EQ(descriptor.GetParameterCount(), frame.parameters.length() + 1);
1495  // The deopt input value is passed on the stack.
1496  DCHECK_GT(descriptor.GetStackParameterCount(), 0);
1497  }
1498  }
1499 #endif
1500 
1501  // Mark the accumulator dead in parent frames since we know that the
1502  // continuation will write it.
1503  return DeoptFrame(scope->data(),
1504  zone()->New<DeoptFrame>(GetDeoptFrameForLazyDeoptHelper(
1505  result_location, result_size, scope->parent(),
1506  scope->data().tag() ==
1507  DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame)));
1508 }
1509 
1510 InterpretedDeoptFrame MaglevGraphBuilder::GetDeoptFrameForEntryStackCheck() {
1511  if (entry_stack_check_frame_) return *entry_stack_check_frame_;
1512  DCHECK_EQ(iterator_.current_offset(), entrypoint_);
1513  DCHECK(!is_inline());
1514  entry_stack_check_frame_.emplace(
1515  *compilation_unit_,
1516  zone()->New<CompactInterpreterFrameState>(
1517  *compilation_unit_,
1518  GetInLivenessFor(graph_->is_osr() ? bailout_for_entrypoint() : 0),
1519  current_interpreter_frame_),
1520  GetClosure(), BytecodeOffset(bailout_for_entrypoint()),
1521  current_source_position_, nullptr);
1522 
1523  (*entry_stack_check_frame_)
1524  .frame_state()
1525  ->ForEachValue(
1526  *compilation_unit_,
1527  [&](ValueNode* node, interpreter::Register) { AddDeoptUse(node); });
1528  AddDeoptUse((*entry_stack_check_frame_).closure());
1529  return *entry_stack_check_frame_;
1530 }
1531 
1532 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetTaggedValue(
1533  ValueNode* value, UseReprHintRecording record_use_repr_hint) {
1534  if (V8_LIKELY(record_use_repr_hint == UseReprHintRecording::kRecord)) {
1535  RecordUseReprHintIfPhi(value, UseRepresentation::kTagged);
1536  }
1537 
1538  ValueRepresentation representation =
1539  value->properties().value_representation();
1540  if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kTagged) return value;
1541 
1542  if (Int32Constant* as_int32_constant = value->TryCast<Int32Constant>();
1543  as_int32_constant && Smi::IsValid(as_int32_constant->value())) {
1544  return GetSmiConstant(as_int32_constant->value());
1545  }
1546 
1547  NodeInfo* node_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(value);
1548  auto& alternative = node_info->alternative();
1549 
1550  if (ValueNode* alt = alternative.tagged()) {
1551  return alt;
1552  }
1553 
1554  // This is called when converting inputs in AddNewNode. We might already have
1555  // an empty type for `value` here. Make sure we don't add unsafe conversion
1556  // nodes in that case by checking for the empty node type explicitly.
1557  // TODO(marja): The checks can be removed after we're able to bail out
1558  // earlier.
1559  switch (representation) {
1560  case ValueRepresentation::kInt32: {
1561  if (!IsEmptyNodeType(node_info->type()) &&
1562  NodeTypeIsSmi(node_info->type())) {
1563  return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiTagInt32>({value}));
1564  }
1565  return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<Int32ToNumber>({value}));
1566  }
1567  case ValueRepresentation::kUint32: {
1568  if (!IsEmptyNodeType(node_info->type()) &&
1569  NodeTypeIsSmi(node_info->type())) {
1570  return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiTagUint32>({value}));
1571  }
1572  return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<Uint32ToNumber>({value}));
1573  }
1574  case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64: {
1575  return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<Float64ToTagged>(
1576  {value}, Float64ToTagged::ConversionMode::kCanonicalizeSmi));
1577  }
1578  case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64: {
1579  return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<HoleyFloat64ToTagged>(
1580  {value}, HoleyFloat64ToTagged::ConversionMode::kForceHeapNumber));
1581  }
1582 
1583  case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
1584  if (!IsEmptyNodeType(node_info->type()) &&
1585  NodeTypeIsSmi(node_info->type())) {
1586  return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiTagIntPtr>({value}));
1587  }
1588  return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<IntPtrToNumber>({value}));
1589 
1590  case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
1591  UNREACHABLE();
1592  }
1593  UNREACHABLE();
1594 }
1595 
1596 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::GetSmiValue(
1597  ValueNode* value, UseReprHintRecording record_use_repr_hint) {
1598  if (V8_LIKELY(record_use_repr_hint == UseReprHintRecording::kRecord)) {
1599  RecordUseReprHintIfPhi(value, UseRepresentation::kTagged);
1600  }
1601 
1602  NodeInfo* node_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(value);
1603 
1604  ValueRepresentation representation =
1605  value->properties().value_representation();
1606  if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kTagged) {
1607  return BuildCheckSmi(value, !value->Is<Phi>());
1608  }
1609 
1610  auto& alternative = node_info->alternative();
1611 
1612  if (ValueNode* alt = alternative.tagged()) {
1613  // HoleyFloat64ToTagged does not canonicalize Smis by default, since it can
1614  // be expensive. If we are reading a Smi value, we should try to
1615  // canonicalize now.
1616  if (HoleyFloat64ToTagged* conversion_node =
1617  alt->TryCast<HoleyFloat64ToTagged>()) {
1618  conversion_node->SetMode(
1619  HoleyFloat64ToTagged::ConversionMode::kCanonicalizeSmi);
1620  }
1621  return BuildCheckSmi(alt, !value->Is<Phi>());
1622  }
1623 
1624  switch (representation) {
1625  case ValueRepresentation::kInt32: {
1626  if (NodeTypeIsSmi(node_info->type())) {
1627  return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiTagInt32>({value}));
1628  }
1629  return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<CheckedSmiTagInt32>({value}));
1630  }
1631  case ValueRepresentation::kUint32: {
1632  if (NodeTypeIsSmi(node_info->type())) {
1633  return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiTagUint32>({value}));
1634  }
1635  return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<CheckedSmiTagUint32>({value}));
1636  }
1637  case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64: {
1638  return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<CheckedSmiTagFloat64>({value}));
1639  }
1640  case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64: {
1641  return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<CheckedSmiTagFloat64>({value}));
1642  }
1643  case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
1644  return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<CheckedSmiTagIntPtr>({value}));
1645  case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
1646  UNREACHABLE();
1647  }
1648  UNREACHABLE();
1649 }
1650 
1651 namespace {
1652 CheckType GetCheckType(NodeType type) {
1653  return NodeTypeIs(type, NodeType::kAnyHeapObject)
1654  ? CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck
1655  : CheckType::kCheckHeapObject;
1656 }
1657 } // namespace
1658 
1659 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetInternalizedString(
1660  interpreter::Register reg) {
1661  ValueNode* node = current_interpreter_frame_.get(reg);
1662  NodeType old_type;
1663  if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kInternalizedString, &old_type)) return node;
1664  NodeInfo* known_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(node);
1665  if (known_info->alternative().checked_value()) {
1666  node = known_info->alternative().checked_value();
1667  if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kInternalizedString, &old_type)) return node;
1668  }
1669 
1670  if (!NodeTypeIs(old_type, NodeType::kString)) {
1671  known_info->IntersectType(NodeType::kString);
1672  }
1673 
1674  // This node may unwrap ThinStrings.
1675  ValueNode* maybe_unwrapping_node =
1676  AddNewNode<CheckedInternalizedString>({node}, GetCheckType(old_type));
1677  known_info->alternative().set_checked_value(maybe_unwrapping_node);
1678 
1679  current_interpreter_frame_.set(reg, maybe_unwrapping_node);
1680  return maybe_unwrapping_node;
1681 }
1682 
1683 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetTruncatedInt32ForToNumber(
1684  ValueNode* value, NodeType allowed_input_type,
1685  TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type) {
1686  RecordUseReprHintIfPhi(value, UseRepresentation::kTruncatedInt32);
1687 
1688  ValueRepresentation representation =
1689  value->properties().value_representation();
1690  if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kInt32) return value;
1691  if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kUint32) {
1692  // This node is cheap (no code gen, just a bitcast), so don't cache it.
1693  return AddNewNode<TruncateUint32ToInt32>({value});
1694  }
1695 
1696  // Process constants first to avoid allocating NodeInfo for them.
1697  switch (value->opcode()) {
1698  case Opcode::kConstant: {
1699  compiler::ObjectRef object = value->Cast<Constant>()->object();
1700  if (!object.IsHeapNumber()) break;
1701  int32_t truncated_value = DoubleToInt32(object.AsHeapNumber().value());
1702  if (!Smi::IsValid(truncated_value)) break;
1703  return GetInt32Constant(truncated_value);
1704  }
1705  case Opcode::kSmiConstant:
1706  return GetInt32Constant(value->Cast<SmiConstant>()->value().value());
1707  case Opcode::kRootConstant: {
1708  Tagged<Object> root_object =
1709  local_isolate_->root(value->Cast<RootConstant>()->index());
1710  if (!IsOddball(root_object, local_isolate_)) break;
1711  int32_t truncated_value =
1712  DoubleToInt32(Cast<Oddball>(root_object)->to_number_raw());
1713  // All oddball ToNumber truncations are valid Smis.
1714  DCHECK(Smi::IsValid(truncated_value));
1715  return GetInt32Constant(truncated_value);
1716  }
1717  case Opcode::kFloat64Constant: {
1718  int32_t truncated_value =
1719  DoubleToInt32(value->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value().get_scalar());
1720  if (!Smi::IsValid(truncated_value)) break;
1721  return GetInt32Constant(truncated_value);
1722  }
1723 
1724  // We could emit unconditional eager deopts for other kinds of constant, but
1725  // it's not necessary, the appropriate checking conversion nodes will deopt.
1726  default:
1727  break;
1728  }
1729 
1730  NodeInfo* node_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(value);
1731  auto& alternative = node_info->alternative();
1732 
1733  // If there is an int32_alternative, then that works as a truncated value
1734  // too.
1735  if (ValueNode* alt = alternative.int32()) {
1736  return alt;
1737  }
1738  if (ValueNode* alt = alternative.truncated_int32_to_number()) {
1739  return alt;
1740  }
1741 
1742  switch (representation) {
1743  case ValueRepresentation::kTagged: {
1744  NodeType old_type;
1745  EnsureType(value, allowed_input_type, &old_type);
1746  if (NodeTypeIsSmi(old_type)) {
1747  // Smi untagging can be cached as an int32 alternative, not just a
1748  // truncated alternative.
1749  return alternative.set_int32(BuildSmiUntag(value));
1750  }
1751  if (allowed_input_type == NodeType::kSmi) {
1752  return alternative.set_int32(AddNewNode<CheckedSmiUntag>({value}));
1753  }
1754  if (NodeTypeIs(old_type, allowed_input_type)) {
1755  return alternative.set_truncated_int32_to_number(
1756  AddNewNode<TruncateNumberOrOddballToInt32>({value},
1757  conversion_type));
1758  }
1759  return alternative.set_truncated_int32_to_number(
1760  AddNewNode<CheckedTruncateNumberOrOddballToInt32>({value},
1761  conversion_type));
1762  }
1763  case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
1764  // Ignore conversion_type for HoleyFloat64, and treat them like Float64.
1765  // ToNumber of undefined is anyway a NaN, so we'll simply truncate away
1766  // the NaN-ness of the hole, and don't need to do extra oddball checks so
1767  // we can ignore the hint (though we'll miss updating the feedback).
1768  case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64: {
1769  return alternative.set_truncated_int32_to_number(
1770  AddNewNode<TruncateFloat64ToInt32>({value}));
1771  }
1772 
1773  case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr: {
1774  // This is not an efficient implementation, but this only happens in
1775  // corner cases.
1776  ValueNode* value_to_number = AddNewNode<IntPtrToNumber>({value});
1777  return alternative.set_truncated_int32_to_number(
1778  AddNewNode<TruncateNumberOrOddballToInt32>(
1779  {value_to_number}, TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber));
1780  }
1781  case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
1782  case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
1783  UNREACHABLE();
1784  }
1785  UNREACHABLE();
1786 }
1787 
1788 std::optional<int32_t> MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetInt32Constant(
1789  ValueNode* value) {
1790  switch (value->opcode()) {
1791  case Opcode::kInt32Constant:
1792  return value->Cast<Int32Constant>()->value();
1793  case Opcode::kUint32Constant: {
1794  uint32_t uint32_value = value->Cast<Uint32Constant>()->value();
1795  if (uint32_value <= INT32_MAX) {
1796  return static_cast<int32_t>(uint32_value);
1797  }
1798  return {};
1799  }
1800  case Opcode::kSmiConstant:
1801  return value->Cast<SmiConstant>()->value().value();
1802  case Opcode::kFloat64Constant: {
1803  double double_value =
1804  value->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value().get_scalar();
1805  if (!IsInt32Double(double_value)) return {};
1806  return FastD2I(value->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value().get_scalar());
1807  }
1808  default:
1809  break;
1810  }
1811  if (auto c = TryGetConstantAlternative(value)) {
1812  return TryGetInt32Constant(*c);
1813  }
1814  return {};
1815 }
1816 
1817 std::optional<uint32_t> MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetUint32Constant(
1818  ValueNode* value) {
1819  switch (value->opcode()) {
1820  case Opcode::kInt32Constant: {
1821  int32_t int32_value = value->Cast<Int32Constant>()->value();
1822  if (int32_value >= 0) {
1823  return static_cast<uint32_t>(int32_value);
1824  }
1825  return {};
1826  }
1827  case Opcode::kUint32Constant:
1828  return value->Cast<Uint32Constant>()->value();
1829  case Opcode::kSmiConstant: {
1830  int32_t smi_value = value->Cast<SmiConstant>()->value().value();
1831  if (smi_value >= 0) {
1832  return static_cast<uint32_t>(smi_value);
1833  }
1834  return {};
1835  }
1836  case Opcode::kFloat64Constant: {
1837  double double_value =
1838  value->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value().get_scalar();
1839  if (!IsUint32Double(double_value)) return {};
1840  return FastD2UI(value->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value().get_scalar());
1841  }
1842  default:
1843  break;
1844  }
1845  if (auto c = TryGetConstantAlternative(value)) {
1846  return TryGetUint32Constant(*c);
1847  }
1848  return {};
1849 }
1850 
1851 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetInt32(ValueNode* value,
1852  bool can_be_heap_number) {
1853  RecordUseReprHintIfPhi(value, UseRepresentation::kInt32);
1854 
1855  ValueRepresentation representation =
1856  value->properties().value_representation();
1857  if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kInt32) return value;
1858 
1859  // Process constants first to avoid allocating NodeInfo for them.
1860  if (auto cst = TryGetInt32Constant(value)) {
1861  return GetInt32Constant(cst.value());
1862  }
1863  // We could emit unconditional eager deopts for other kinds of constant, but
1864  // it's not necessary, the appropriate checking conversion nodes will deopt.
1865 
1866  NodeInfo* node_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(value);
1867  auto& alternative = node_info->alternative();
1868 
1869  if (ValueNode* alt = alternative.int32()) {
1870  return alt;
1871  }
1872 
1873  switch (representation) {
1874  case ValueRepresentation::kTagged: {
1875  if (can_be_heap_number && !CheckType(value, NodeType::kSmi)) {
1876  return alternative.set_int32(AddNewNode<CheckedNumberToInt32>({value}));
1877  }
1878  return alternative.set_int32(BuildSmiUntag(value));
1879  }
1880  case ValueRepresentation::kUint32: {
1881  if (!IsEmptyNodeType(GetType(value)) && node_info->is_smi()) {
1882  return alternative.set_int32(
1883  AddNewNode<TruncateUint32ToInt32>({value}));
1884  }
1885  return alternative.set_int32(AddNewNode<CheckedUint32ToInt32>({value}));
1886  }
1887  case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
1888  // The check here will also work for the hole NaN, so we can treat
1889  // HoleyFloat64 as Float64.
1890  case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64: {
1891  return alternative.set_int32(
1892  AddNewNode<CheckedTruncateFloat64ToInt32>({value}));
1893  }
1894 
1895  case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
1896  return alternative.set_int32(AddNewNode<CheckedIntPtrToInt32>({value}));
1897 
1898  case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
1899  UNREACHABLE();
1900  }
1901  UNREACHABLE();
1902 }
1903 
1904 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1905 std::optional<double> MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetHoleyFloat64Constant(
1906  ValueNode* value) {
1907  if (value->opcode() == Opcode::kRootConstant) {
1908  Tagged<Object> root_object =
1909  local_isolate_->root(value->Cast<RootConstant>()->index());
1910  if (IsOddball(root_object)) {
1911  return Cast<Oddball>(root_object)->to_number_raw();
1912  }
1913  }
1914  return TryGetFloat64Constant(value,
1915  TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball);
1916 }
1917 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1918 
1919 std::optional<double> MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetFloat64Constant(
1920  ValueNode* value, TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type) {
1921  switch (value->opcode()) {
1922  case Opcode::kConstant: {
1923  compiler::ObjectRef object = value->Cast<Constant>()->object();
1924  if (object.IsHeapNumber()) {
1925  return object.AsHeapNumber().value();
1926  }
1927  // Oddballs should be RootConstants.
1928  DCHECK(!IsOddball(*object.object()));
1929  return {};
1930  }
1931  case Opcode::kInt32Constant:
1932  return value->Cast<Int32Constant>()->value();
1933  case Opcode::kSmiConstant:
1934  return value->Cast<SmiConstant>()->value().value();
1935  case Opcode::kFloat64Constant:
1936  return value->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value().get_scalar();
1937  case Opcode::kRootConstant: {
1938  Tagged<Object> root_object =
1939  local_isolate_->root(value->Cast<RootConstant>()->index());
1940  if (conversion_type == TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrBoolean &&
1941  IsBoolean(root_object)) {
1942  return Cast<Oddball>(root_object)->to_number_raw();
1943  }
1944  if (conversion_type == TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball &&
1945  IsOddball(root_object)) {
1946 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1947  if (IsUndefined(root_object)) {
1948  // We use the undefined nan and silence it to produce the same result
1949  // as a computation from non-constants would.
1950  auto ud = Float64::FromBits(kUndefinedNanInt64);
1951  return ud.to_quiet_nan().get_scalar();
1952  }
1953 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1954  return Cast<Oddball>(root_object)->to_number_raw();
1955  }
1956  if (IsHeapNumber(root_object)) {
1957  return Cast<HeapNumber>(root_object)->value();
1958  }
1959  return {};
1960  }
1961  default:
1962  break;
1963  }
1964  if (auto c = TryGetConstantAlternative(value)) {
1965  return TryGetFloat64Constant(*c, conversion_type);
1966  }
1967  return {};
1968 }
1969 
1970 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetFloat64(ValueNode* value) {
1971  RecordUseReprHintIfPhi(value, UseRepresentation::kFloat64);
1972  return GetFloat64ForToNumber(value, NodeType::kNumber,
1973  TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber);
1974 }
1975 
1976 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1977 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetHoleyFloat64(ValueNode* value,
1978  bool convert_hole_to_undefined) {
1979  ValueRepresentation representation =
1980  value->properties().value_representation();
1981  if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64 &&
1982  !convert_hole_to_undefined) {
1983  return value;
1984  }
1985 
1986  // Process constants first to avoid allocating NodeInfo for them.
1987  if (auto cst = TryGetHoleyFloat64Constant(value)) {
1988  return GetFloat64Constant(cst.value());
1989  }
1990 
1991  NodeInfo* node_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(value);
1992 
1993  if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kFloat64) {
1994  // We need to silence NaNs, because we start interpreting some bit patterns
1995  // differently.
1996  return AddNewNode<HoleyFloat64ToMaybeNanFloat64>({value});
1997  } else if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) {
1998  DCHECK(convert_hole_to_undefined);
1999  if (!IsEmptyNodeType(node_info->type()) &&
2000  NodeTypeIs(node_info->type(), NodeType::kNumberOrBoolean)) {
2001  // We don't have holes, so we don't need to convert anything.
2002  return value;
2003  }
2004  return AddNewNode<ConvertHoleNanToUndefinedNan>({value});
2005  } else if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kTagged) {
2006  return AddNewNode<CheckedNumberOrOddballToHoleyFloat64>({value});
2007  } else if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kInt32) {
2008  auto& alternative = node_info->alternative();
2009  return alternative.set_float64(AddNewNode<ChangeInt32ToFloat64>({value}));
2010  }
2011 
2012  UNREACHABLE();
2013 }
2014 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
2015 
2016 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetFloat64ForToNumber(
2017  ValueNode* value, NodeType allowed_input_type,
2018  TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type) {
2019  ValueRepresentation representation =
2020  value->properties().value_representation();
2021  if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kFloat64) return value;
2022 
2023  // Process constants first to avoid allocating NodeInfo for them.
2024  if (auto cst = TryGetFloat64Constant(value, conversion_type)) {
2025  return GetFloat64Constant(cst.value());
2026  }
2027  // We could emit unconditional eager deopts for other kinds of constant, but
2028  // it's not necessary, the appropriate checking conversion nodes will deopt.
2029 
2030  NodeInfo* node_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(value);
2031  auto& alternative = node_info->alternative();
2032 
2033  if (ValueNode* alt = alternative.float64()) {
2034  return alt;
2035  }
2036 
2037  // This is called when converting inputs in AddNewNode. We might already have
2038  // an empty type for `value` here. Make sure we don't add unsafe conversion
2039  // nodes in that case by checking for the empty node type explicitly.
2040  // TODO(marja): The checks can be removed after we're able to bail out
2041  // earlier.
2042  switch (representation) {
2043  case ValueRepresentation::kTagged: {
2044  auto combined_type = IntersectType(allowed_input_type, node_info->type());
2045  if (!IsEmptyNodeType(node_info->type()) &&
2046  NodeTypeIs(combined_type, NodeType::kSmi)) {
2047  // Get the float64 value of a Smi value its int32 representation.
2048  return GetFloat64(GetInt32(value));
2049  }
2050  if (!IsEmptyNodeType(node_info->type()) &&
2051  NodeTypeIs(combined_type, NodeType::kNumber)) {
2052  // Number->Float64 conversions are exact alternatives, so they can
2053  // also become the canonical float64_alternative.
2054  return alternative.set_float64(BuildNumberOrOddballToFloat64(
2055  value, NodeType::kNumber,
2056  TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber));
2057  }
2058  if (!IsEmptyNodeType(node_info->type()) &&
2059  NodeTypeIs(combined_type, NodeType::kNumberOrOddball)) {
2060  // NumberOrOddball->Float64 conversions are not exact alternatives,
2061  // since they lose the information that this is an oddball, so they
2062  // can only become the canonical float64_alternative if they are a
2063  // known number (and therefore not oddball).
2064  return BuildNumberOrOddballToFloat64(value, combined_type,
2065  conversion_type);
2066  }
2067  // The type is impossible. We could generate an unconditional deopt here,
2068  // but it's too invasive. So we just generate a check which will always
2069  // deopt.
2070  return BuildNumberOrOddballToFloat64(value, allowed_input_type,
2071  conversion_type);
2072  }
2073  case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
2074  return alternative.set_float64(AddNewNode<ChangeInt32ToFloat64>({value}));
2075  case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
2076  return alternative.set_float64(
2077  AddNewNode<ChangeUint32ToFloat64>({value}));
2078  case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64: {
2079  switch (allowed_input_type) {
2080  case NodeType::kSmi:
2081  case NodeType::kNumber:
2082  case NodeType::kNumberOrBoolean:
2083  // Number->Float64 conversions are exact alternatives, so they can
2084  // also become the canonical float64_alternative. The HoleyFloat64
2085  // representation can represent undefined but no other oddballs, so
2086  // booleans cannot occur here and kNumberOrBoolean can be grouped with
2087  // kNumber.
2088  return alternative.set_float64(
2089  AddNewNode<CheckedHoleyFloat64ToFloat64>({value}));
2090  case NodeType::kNumberOrOddball:
2091  // NumberOrOddball->Float64 conversions are not exact alternatives,
2092  // since they lose the information that this is an oddball, so they
2093  // cannot become the canonical float64_alternative.
2094  return AddNewNode<HoleyFloat64ToMaybeNanFloat64>({value});
2095  default:
2096  UNREACHABLE();
2097  }
2098  }
2099  case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
2100  return alternative.set_float64(
2101  AddNewNode<ChangeIntPtrToFloat64>({value}));
2102  case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
2103  UNREACHABLE();
2104  }
2105  UNREACHABLE();
2106 }
2107 
2108 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetHoleyFloat64ForToNumber(
2109  ValueNode* value, NodeType allowed_input_type,
2110  TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type) {
2111  RecordUseReprHintIfPhi(value, UseRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64);
2112  ValueRepresentation representation =
2113  value->properties().value_representation();
2114  // Ignore the hint for
2115  if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) return value;
2116  return GetFloat64ForToNumber(value, allowed_input_type, conversion_type);
2117 }
