8316 namespace {
8317 void ForceEscapeIfAllocation(ValueNode* value) {
8318  if (InlinedAllocation* alloc = value->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
8319  alloc->ForceEscaping();
8320  }
8321 }
8322 } // namespace
8323 
8324 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInlineFunction(
8325  SourcePosition call_site_position, ValueNode* context, ValueNode* function,
8326  ValueNode* new_target) {
8327  DCHECK(is_inline());
8328  DCHECK_GT(caller_details_->arguments.size(), 0);
8329 
8330  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared =
8331  compilation_unit_->shared_function_info();
8332  compiler::BytecodeArrayRef bytecode = compilation_unit_->bytecode();
8333  compiler::FeedbackVectorRef feedback = compilation_unit_->feedback();
8334 
8335  if (v8_flags.maglev_print_inlined &&
8336  TopLevelFunctionPassMaglevPrintFilter() &&
8337  (v8_flags.print_maglev_code || v8_flags.print_maglev_graph ||
8338  v8_flags.print_maglev_graphs ||
8339  v8_flags.trace_maglev_inlining_verbose)) {
8340  std::cout << "== Inlining " << Brief(*shared.object()) << std::endl;
8341  BytecodeArray::Disassemble(bytecode.object(), std::cout);
8342  if (v8_flags.maglev_print_feedback) {
8343  i::Print(*feedback.object(), std::cout);
8344  }
8345  } else if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building ||
8346  v8_flags.trace_maglev_inlining) {
8347  std::cout << "== Inlining " << shared.object() << std::endl;
8348  }
8349 
8350  graph()->inlined_functions().push_back(
8351  OptimizedCompilationInfo::InlinedFunctionHolder(
8352  shared.object(), bytecode.object(), call_site_position));
8353  if (feedback.object()->invocation_count_before_stable(kRelaxedLoad) >
8354  v8_flags.invocation_count_for_early_optimization) {
8355  compilation_unit_->info()->set_could_not_inline_all_candidates();
8356  }
8357  inlining_id_ = static_cast<int>(graph()->inlined_functions().size() - 1);
8358 
8359  DCHECK_NE(inlining_id_, SourcePosition::kNotInlined);
8360  current_source_position_ = SourcePosition(
8361  compilation_unit_->shared_function_info().StartPosition(), inlining_id_);
8362 
8363  // Manually create the prologue of the inner function graph, so that we
8364  // can manually set up the arguments.
8365  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current_block_);
8366 
8367  // Set receiver.
8368  SetArgument(0, caller_details_->arguments[0]);
8369 
8370  // The inlined function could call a builtin that iterates the frame, the
8371  // receiver needs to have been materialized.
8372  // TODO(victorgomes): Can we relax this requirement? Maybe we can allocate the
8373  // object lazily? This is also only required if the inlined function is not a
8374  // leaf (ie. it calls other functions).
8375  ForceEscapeIfAllocation(caller_details_->arguments[0]);
8376 
8377  // Set remaining arguments.
8378  RootConstant* undefined_constant =
8379  GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
8380  int args_count = static_cast<int>(caller_details_->arguments.size()) - 1;
8381  int formal_parameter_count = compilation_unit_->parameter_count() - 1;
8382  for (int i = 0; i < formal_parameter_count; i++) {
8383  ValueNode* arg_value =
8384  i < args_count ? caller_details_->arguments[i + 1] : undefined_constant;
8385  SetArgument(i + 1, arg_value);
8386  }
8387 
8388  inlined_new_target_ = new_target;
8389 
8390  BuildRegisterFrameInitialization(context, function, new_target);
8391  BuildMergeStates();
8392  EndPrologue();
8393  in_prologue_ = false;
8394 
8395  // Build the inlined function body.
8396  BuildBody();
8397 
8398  // All returns in the inlined body jump to a merge point one past the bytecode
8399  // length (i.e. at offset bytecode.length()). If there isn't one already,
8400  // create a block at this fake offset and have it jump out of the inlined
8401  // function, into a new block that we create which resumes execution of the
8402  // outer function.
8403  if (!current_block_) {
8404  // If we don't have a merge state at the inline_exit_offset, then there is
8405  // no control flow that reaches the end of the inlined function, either
8406  // because of infinite loops or deopts
8407  if (merge_states_[inline_exit_offset()] == nullptr) {
8408  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8409  std::cout << "== Finished inlining (abort) " << shared.object()
8410  << std::endl;
8411  }
8412  return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
8413  }
8414 
8415  ProcessMergePoint(inline_exit_offset(), /*preserve_kna*/ false);
8416  StartNewBlock(inline_exit_offset(), /*predecessor*/ nullptr);
8417  }
8418 
8419  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8420  std::cout << "== Finished inlining " << shared.object() << std::endl;
8421  }
8422 
8423  // Pull the returned accumulator value out of the inlined function's final
8424  // merged return state.
8425  return current_interpreter_frame_.accumulator();
8426 }
8427 
8428 #define TRACE_INLINING(...) \
8429  do { \
8430  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_inlining) \
8431  StdoutStream{} << __VA_ARGS__ << std::endl; \
8432  } while (false)
8433 
8434 #define TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE(...) \
8435  TRACE_INLINING(" cannot inline " << shared << ": " << __VA_ARGS__)
8436 
8437 bool MaglevGraphBuilder::CanInlineCall(compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
8438  float call_frequency) {
8439  if (graph()->total_inlined_bytecode_size() >
8440  max_inlined_bytecode_size_cumulative()) {
8441  compilation_unit_->info()->set_could_not_inline_all_candidates();
8442  TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("maximum inlined bytecode size");
8443  return false;
8444  }
8445  // TODO(olivf): This is a temporary stopgap to prevent infinite recursion when
8446  // inlining, because we currently excempt small functions from some of the
8447  // negative heuristics. We should refactor these heuristics and make sure they
8448  // make sense in the presence of (mutually) recursive inlining. Please do
8449  // *not* return true before this check.
8450  if (inlining_depth() > v8_flags.max_maglev_hard_inline_depth) {
8451  TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("inlining depth ("
8452  << inlining_depth() << ") >= hard-max-depth ("
8453  << v8_flags.max_maglev_hard_inline_depth << ")");
8454  return false;
8455  }
8456  if (compilation_unit_->shared_function_info().equals(shared)) {
8457  TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("direct recursion");
8458  return false;
8459  }
8460  SharedFunctionInfo::Inlineability inlineability =
8461  shared.GetInlineability(CodeKind::MAGLEV, broker());
8462  if (inlineability != SharedFunctionInfo::Inlineability::kIsInlineable) {
8463  TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE(inlineability);
8464  return false;
8465  }
8466  // TODO(victorgomes): Support NewTarget/RegisterInput in inlined functions.
8467  compiler::BytecodeArrayRef bytecode = shared.GetBytecodeArray(broker());
8468  if (bytecode.incoming_new_target_or_generator_register().is_valid()) {
8469  TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("use unsupported NewTargetOrGenerator register");
8470  return false;
8471  }
8472  if (call_frequency < min_inlining_frequency()) {
8473  TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("call frequency (" << call_frequency
8474  << ") < minimum threshold ("
8475  << min_inlining_frequency() << ")");
8476  return false;
8477  }
8478  if (bytecode.length() > max_inlined_bytecode_size()) {
8479  TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("big function, size ("
8480  << bytecode.length() << ") >= max-size ("
8481  << max_inlined_bytecode_size() << ")");
8482  return false;
8483  }
8484  return true;
8485 }
8486 
8487 bool MaglevGraphBuilder::TopLevelFunctionPassMaglevPrintFilter() {
8488  return compilation_unit_->GetTopLevelCompilationUnit()
8489  ->shared_function_info()
8490  .object()
8491  ->PassesFilter(v8_flags.maglev_print_filter);
8492 }
8493 
8494 bool MaglevGraphBuilder::ShouldEagerInlineCall(
8495  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared) {
8496  compiler::BytecodeArrayRef bytecode = shared.GetBytecodeArray(broker());
8497  if (bytecode.length() < max_inlined_bytecode_size_small()) {
8498  TRACE_INLINING(" greedy inlining "
8499  << shared << ": small function, skipping max-depth");
8500  return true;
8501  }
8502  return false;
8503 }
8504 
8505 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildInlineCall(
8506  ValueNode* context, ValueNode* function, ValueNode* new_target,
8507 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
8508  JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle,
8509 #endif
8510  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
8511  compiler::FeedbackCellRef feedback_cell, CallArguments& args,
8512  const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
8513  DCHECK_EQ(args.mode(), CallArguments::kDefault);
8514  if (!feedback_cell.feedback_vector(broker())) {
8515  // TODO(verwaest): Soft deopt instead?
8516  TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("it has not been compiled/run with feedback yet");
8517  return {};
8518  }
8519 
8520  float feedback_frequency = 0.0f;
8521  if (feedback_source.IsValid()) {
8522  compiler::ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
8523  broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(feedback_source);
8524  feedback_frequency =
8525  feedback.IsInsufficient() ? 0.0f : feedback.AsCall().frequency();
8526  }
8527  float call_frequency = feedback_frequency * GetCurrentCallFrequency();
8528 
8529  if (!CanInlineCall(shared, call_frequency)) return {};
8530  if (ShouldEagerInlineCall(shared)) {
8531  return BuildEagerInlineCall(context, function, new_target, shared,
8532  feedback_cell, args, call_frequency);
8533  }
8534 
8535  // Should we inline call?
8536  if (inlining_depth() > max_inline_depth()) {
8537  TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("inlining depth (" << inlining_depth()
8538  << ") >= max-depth ("
8539  << max_inline_depth() << ")");
8540  return {};
8541  }
8542 
8543  compiler::BytecodeArrayRef bytecode = shared.GetBytecodeArray(broker());
8544  if (!is_non_eager_inlining_enabled()) {
8545  graph()->add_inlined_bytecode_size(bytecode.length());
8546  return BuildEagerInlineCall(context, function, new_target, shared,
8547  feedback_cell, args, call_frequency);
8548  }
8549 
8550  TRACE_INLINING(" considering " << shared << " for inlining");
8551  auto arguments = GetArgumentsAsArrayOfValueNodes(shared, args);
8552  auto generic_call = BuildCallKnownJSFunction(context, function, new_target,
8553 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
8554  dispatch_handle,
8555 #endif
8556  shared, arguments);
8557 
8558  // Note: We point to the generic call exception handler instead of
8559  // jump_targets_ because the former contains a BasicBlockRef that is
8560  // guaranteed to be updated correctly upon exception block creation.
8561  // BuildLoopForPeeling might reset the BasicBlockRef in jump_targets_. If this
8562  // happens, inlined calls within the peeled loop would incorrectly point to
8563  // the loop's exception handler instead of the original call's.
8564  CatchBlockDetails catch_details = GetTryCatchBlockForNonEagerInlining(
8565  generic_call->exception_handler_info());
8566  catch_details.deopt_frame_distance++;
8567  float score = call_frequency / bytecode.length();
8568  MaglevCallSiteInfo* call_site = zone()->New<MaglevCallSiteInfo>(
8569  MaglevCallerDetails{
8570  arguments, &generic_call->lazy_deopt_info()->top_frame(),
8571  known_node_aspects().Clone(zone()), loop_effects_,
8572  unobserved_context_slot_stores_, catch_details, IsInsideLoop(),
8573  /* is_eager_inline */ false, call_frequency},
8574  generic_call, feedback_cell, score);
8575  graph()->inlineable_calls().push_back(call_site);
8576  return generic_call;
8577 }
8578 
8579 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildEagerInlineCall(
8580  ValueNode* context, ValueNode* function, ValueNode* new_target,
8581  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
8582  compiler::FeedbackCellRef feedback_cell, CallArguments& args,
8583  float call_frequency) {
8584  DCHECK_EQ(args.mode(), CallArguments::kDefault);
8585 
8586  // Merge catch block state if needed.
8587  CatchBlockDetails catch_block_details = GetCurrentTryCatchBlock();
8588  if (catch_block_details.ref &&
8589  catch_block_details.exception_handler_was_used) {
8590  if (IsInsideTryBlock()) {
8591  // Merge the current state into the handler state.
8592  GetCatchBlockFrameState()->MergeThrow(
8593  this, compilation_unit_,
8594  *current_interpreter_frame_.known_node_aspects(),
8595  current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects());
8596  }
8597  catch_block_details.deopt_frame_distance++;
8598  }
8599 
8600  // Create a new compilation unit.
8601  MaglevCompilationUnit* inner_unit = MaglevCompilationUnit::NewInner(
8602  zone(), compilation_unit_, shared, feedback_cell);
8603 
8604  // Propagate details.
8605  auto arguments_vector = GetArgumentsAsArrayOfValueNodes(shared, args);
8606  DeoptFrame* deopt_frame =
8607  GetDeoptFrameForEagerCall(inner_unit, function, arguments_vector);
8608  MaglevCallerDetails* caller_details = zone()->New<MaglevCallerDetails>(
8609  arguments_vector, deopt_frame,
8610  current_interpreter_frame_.known_node_aspects(), loop_effects_,
8611  unobserved_context_slot_stores_, catch_block_details, IsInsideLoop(),
8612  /* is_eager_inline */ true, call_frequency);
8613 
8614  // Create a new graph builder for the inlined function.
8615  MaglevGraphBuilder inner_graph_builder(local_isolate_, inner_unit, graph_,
8616  caller_details);
8617 
8618  // Set the inner graph builder to build in the current block.
8619  inner_graph_builder.current_block_ = current_block_;
8620 
8621  // Build inline function.
8622  ReduceResult result = inner_graph_builder.BuildInlineFunction(
8623  current_source_position_, context, function, new_target);
8624 
8625  // Prapagate back (or reset) builder state.
8626  unobserved_context_slot_stores_ =
8627  inner_graph_builder.unobserved_context_slot_stores_;
8628  latest_checkpointed_frame_.reset();
8629  ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
8630 
8631  if (result.IsDoneWithAbort()) {
8632  DCHECK_NULL(inner_graph_builder.current_block_);
8633  current_block_ = nullptr;
8634  return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
8635  }
8636 
8637  // Propagate frame information back to the caller.
8638  current_interpreter_frame_.set_known_node_aspects(
8639  inner_graph_builder.current_interpreter_frame_.known_node_aspects());
8640  current_interpreter_frame_.set_virtual_objects(
8641  inner_graph_builder.current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects());
8642  current_for_in_state.receiver_needs_map_check =
8643  inner_graph_builder.current_for_in_state.receiver_needs_map_check;
8644 
8645  // Resume execution using the final block of the inner builder.
8646  current_block_ = inner_graph_builder.current_block_;
8647 
8648  DCHECK(result.IsDoneWithValue());
8649  return result;
8650 }
8651 
8652 namespace {
8653 
8654 bool CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker,
8655  const PossibleMaps& maps,
8656  ElementsKind* kind_return) {
8657  DCHECK_NE(0, maps.size());
8658  *kind_return = maps.at(0).elements_kind();
8659  for (compiler::MapRef map : maps) {
8660  if (!map.supports_fast_array_iteration(broker) ||
8661  !UnionElementsKindUptoSize(kind_return, map.elements_kind())) {
8662  return false;
8663  }
8664  }
8665  return true;
8666 }
8667 
8668 } // namespace
8669 
8670 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceArrayIsArray(
8671  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
8672  if (args.count() == 0) return GetBooleanConstant(false);
8673 
8674  ValueNode* node = args[0];
8675 
8676  if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kJSArray)) {
8677  return GetBooleanConstant(true);
8678  }
8679 
8680  auto node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(node);
8681  if (node_info && node_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
8682  bool has_array_map = false;
8683  bool has_proxy_map = false;
8684  bool has_other_map = false;
8685  for (compiler::MapRef map : node_info->possible_maps()) {
8686  InstanceType type = map.instance_type();
8687  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSArray(type)) {
8688  has_array_map = true;
8689  } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSProxy(type)) {
8690  has_proxy_map = true;
8691  } else {
8692  has_other_map = true;
8693  }
8694  }
8695  if ((has_array_map ^ has_other_map) && !has_proxy_map) {
8696  if (has_array_map) node_info->IntersectType(NodeType::kJSArray);
8697  return GetBooleanConstant(has_array_map);
8698  }
8699  }
8700 
8701  // TODO(verwaest): Add a node that checks the instance type.
8702  return {};
8703 }
8704 
8705 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceArrayForEach(
8706  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
8707  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
8708 
8709  ValueNode* receiver = args.receiver();
8710  if (!receiver) return {};
8711 
8712  if (args.count() < 1) {
8713  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8714  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.forEach - not enough "
8715  "arguments"
8716  << std::endl;
8717  }
8718  return {};
8719  }
8720 
8721  auto node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(receiver);
8722  if (!node_info || !node_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
8723  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8724  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.forEach - receiver "
8725  "map is unknown"
8726  << std::endl;
8727  }
8728  return {};
8729  }
8730 
8731  ElementsKind elements_kind;
8732  if (!CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(broker(), node_info->possible_maps(),
8733  &elements_kind)) {
8734  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8735  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.forEach - doesn't "
8736  "support fast array iteration or incompatible maps"
8737  << std::endl;
8738  }
8739  return {};
8740  }
8741 
8742  // TODO(leszeks): May only be needed for holey elements kinds.
8743  if (!broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
8744  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8745  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.forEach - invalidated "
8746  "no elements protector"
8747  << std::endl;
8748  }
8749  return {};
8750  }
8751 
8752  ValueNode* callback = args[0];
8753  if (!callback->is_tagged()) {
8754  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8755  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.forEach - callback is "
8756  "untagged value"
8757  << std::endl;
8758  }
8759  return {};
8760  }
8761 
8762  auto get_lazy_deopt_scope =
8763  [this](compiler::JSFunctionRef target, ValueNode* receiver,
8764  ValueNode* callback, ValueNode* this_arg, ValueNode* index_int32,
8765  ValueNode* next_index_int32, ValueNode* original_length) {
8766  return DeoptFrameScope(
8767  this, Builtin::kArrayForEachLoopLazyDeoptContinuation, target,
8768  base::VectorOf<ValueNode*>({receiver, callback, this_arg,
8769  next_index_int32, original_length}));
8770  };
8771 
8772  auto get_eager_deopt_scope =
8773  [this](compiler::JSFunctionRef target, ValueNode* receiver,
8774  ValueNode* callback, ValueNode* this_arg, ValueNode* index_int32,
8775  ValueNode* next_index_int32, ValueNode* original_length) {
8776  return DeoptFrameScope(
8777  this, Builtin::kArrayForEachLoopEagerDeoptContinuation, target,
8778  base::VectorOf<ValueNode*>({receiver, callback, this_arg,
8779  next_index_int32, original_length}));
8780  };
8781 
8782  MaybeReduceResult builtin_result = TryReduceArrayIteratingBuiltin(
8783  "Array.prototype.forEach", target, args, get_eager_deopt_scope,
8784  get_lazy_deopt_scope);
8785  if (builtin_result.IsFail() || builtin_result.IsDoneWithAbort()) {
8786  return builtin_result;
8787  }
8788  DCHECK(builtin_result.IsDoneWithoutValue());
8789  return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
8790 }
8791 
8792 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceArrayMap(
8793  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
8794  if (!is_turbolev()) {
8795  return {};
8796  }
8797 
8798  if (!broker()->dependencies()->DependOnArraySpeciesProtector()) {
8799  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8800  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.map - invalidated "
8801  "array species protector"
8802  << std::endl;
8803  }
8804  return {};
8805  }
8806 
8807  compiler::NativeContextRef native_context = broker()->target_native_context();
8808  compiler::MapRef holey_smi_map =
8809  native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(broker(), HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS);
8810  compiler::MapRef holey_map =
8811  native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(broker(), HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
8812  compiler::MapRef holey_double_map =
8813  native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(broker(), HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS);
8814 
8815  ValueNode* result_array = nullptr;
8816 
8817  // We don't need to check the "array constructor inlining" protector (probably
8818  // Turbofan wouldn't need either for the Array.p.map case, but it does
8819  // anyway). CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin allows only fast mode maps, and if
8820  // at runtime we encounter a dictionary mode map, we will deopt. If the
8821  // feedback contains dictionary mode maps to start with, we won't even lower
8822  // Array.prototype.map here, so there's no risk for a deopt loop.
8823 
8824  // We always inline the Array ctor here, even if Turbofan doesn't. Since the
8825  // top frame cannot be deopted because of the allocation, we don't need a
8826  // DeoptFrameScope here.
8827 
8828  auto initial_callback = [this, &result_array,
8829  holey_smi_map](ValueNode* length_smi) {
8830  ValueNode* elements = AddNewNode<CreateFastArrayElements>(
8831  {length_smi}, AllocationType::kYoung);
8832  VirtualObject* array;
8833  GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(
8834  array, CreateJSArray(holey_smi_map, holey_smi_map.instance_size(),
8835  length_smi));
8836  array->set(JSArray::kElementsOffset, elements);
8837  result_array = BuildInlinedAllocation(array, AllocationType::kYoung);
8838  return ReduceResult::Done();
8839  };
8840 
8841  auto process_element_callback = [this, &holey_map, &holey_double_map,
8842  &result_array](ValueNode* index_int32,
8843  ValueNode* element) {
8844  AddNewNode<TransitionAndStoreArrayElement>(
8845  {result_array, index_int32, element}, holey_map, holey_double_map);
8846  };
8847 
8848  auto get_lazy_deopt_scope = [this, &result_array](
8849  compiler::JSFunctionRef target,
8850  ValueNode* receiver, ValueNode* callback,
8851  ValueNode* this_arg, ValueNode* index_int32,
8852  ValueNode* next_index_int32,
8853  ValueNode* original_length) {
8854  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(result_array);
8855  return DeoptFrameScope(
8856  this, Builtin::kArrayMapLoopLazyDeoptContinuation, target,
8857  base::VectorOf<ValueNode*>({receiver, callback, this_arg, result_array,
8858  index_int32, original_length}));
8859  };
8860 
8861  auto get_eager_deopt_scope = [this, &result_array](
8862  compiler::JSFunctionRef target,
8863  ValueNode* receiver, ValueNode* callback,
8864  ValueNode* this_arg, ValueNode* index_int32,
8865  ValueNode* next_index_int32,
8866  ValueNode* original_length) {
8867  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(result_array);
8868  return DeoptFrameScope(
8869  this, Builtin::kArrayMapLoopEagerDeoptContinuation, target,
8870  base::VectorOf<ValueNode*>({receiver, callback, this_arg, result_array,
8871  next_index_int32, original_length}));
8872  };
8873 
8874  MaybeReduceResult builtin_result = TryReduceArrayIteratingBuiltin(
8875  "Array.prototype.map", target, args, get_eager_deopt_scope,
8876  get_lazy_deopt_scope, initial_callback, process_element_callback);
8877  if (builtin_result.IsFail() || builtin_result.IsDoneWithAbort()) {
8878  return builtin_result;
8879  }
8880  DCHECK(builtin_result.IsDoneWithoutValue());
8881 
8882  // If the result was not fail or abort, the initial callback has successfully
8883  // created the array which we can return now.
8884  DCHECK(result_array);
8885  return result_array;
8886 }
8887 
8888 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceArrayIteratingBuiltin(
8889  const char* name, compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args,
8890  GetDeoptScopeCallback get_eager_deopt_scope,
8891  GetDeoptScopeCallback get_lazy_deopt_scope,
8892  const std::optional<InitialCallback>& initial_callback,
8893  const std::optional<ProcessElementCallback>& process_element_callback) {
8894  DCHECK_EQ(initial_callback.has_value(), process_element_callback.has_value());
8895 
8896  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
8897 
8898  ValueNode* receiver = args.receiver();
8899  if (!receiver) return {};
8900 
8901  if (args.count() < 1) {
8902  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8903  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce " << name << " - not enough arguments"
8904  << std::endl;
8905  }
8906  return {};
8907  }
8908 
8909  auto node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(receiver);
8910  if (!node_info || !node_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
8911  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8912  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce " << name
8913  << " - receiver map is unknown" << std::endl;
8914  }
8915  return {};
8916  }
8917 
8918  ElementsKind elements_kind;
8919  if (!CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(broker(), node_info->possible_maps(),
8920  &elements_kind)) {
8921  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8922  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce " << name
8923  << " - doesn't support fast array iteration or incompatible"
8924  << " maps" << std::endl;
8925  }
8926  return {};
8927  }
8928 
8929  // TODO(leszeks): May only be needed for holey elements kinds.
8930  if (!broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
8931  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8932  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce " << name
8933  << " - invalidated no elements protector" << std::endl;
8934  }
8935  return {};
8936  }
8937 
8938  ValueNode* callback = args[0];
8939  if (!callback->is_tagged()) {
8940  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8941  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce " << name
8942  << " - callback is untagged value" << std::endl;
8943  }
8944  return {};
8945  }
8946 
8947  ValueNode* this_arg =
8948  args.count() > 1 ? args[1] : GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
8949 
8950  ValueNode* original_length = BuildLoadJSArrayLength(receiver);
8951 
8952  if (initial_callback) {
8953  RETURN_IF_ABORT((*initial_callback)(original_length));
8954  }
8955 
8956  // Elide the callable check if the node is known callable.
8957  EnsureType(callback, NodeType::kCallable, [&](NodeType old_type) {
8958  // ThrowIfNotCallable is wrapped in a lazy_deopt_scope to make sure the
8959  // exception has the right call stack.
8960  const DeoptFrameScope& lazy_deopt_scope = get_lazy_deopt_scope(
8961  target, receiver, callback, this_arg, GetSmiConstant(0),
8962  GetSmiConstant(0), original_length);
8963  AddNewNode<ThrowIfNotCallable>({callback});
8964  });
8965 
8966  ValueNode* original_length_int32 = GetInt32(original_length);
8967 
8968  // Remember the receiver map set before entering the loop the call.
8969  bool receiver_maps_were_unstable = node_info->possible_maps_are_unstable();
8970  PossibleMaps receiver_maps_before_loop(node_info->possible_maps());
8971 
8972  // Create a sub graph builder with two variables (index and length).
8973  MaglevSubGraphBuilder sub_builder(this, 2);
8974  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable var_index(0);
8975  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable var_length(1);
8976 
8977  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label loop_end(&sub_builder, 1);
8978 
8979  // ```
8980  // index = 0
8981  // bind loop_header
8982  // ```
8983  sub_builder.set(var_index, GetSmiConstant(0));
8984  sub_builder.set(var_length, original_length);
8985  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::LoopLabel loop_header =
8986  sub_builder.BeginLoop({&var_index, &var_length});
8987 
8988  // Reset known state that is cleared by BeginLoop, but is known to be true on
8989  // the first iteration, and will be re-checked at the end of the loop.
8990 
8991  // Reset the known receiver maps if necessary.
8992  if (receiver_maps_were_unstable) {
8993  node_info->SetPossibleMaps(receiver_maps_before_loop,
8994  receiver_maps_were_unstable,
8995  // Node type is monotonic, no need to reset it.
8996  NodeType::kUnknown, broker());
8997  known_node_aspects().any_map_for_any_node_is_unstable = true;
8998  } else {
8999  DCHECK_EQ(node_info->possible_maps().size(),
9000  receiver_maps_before_loop.size());
9001  }
9002  // Reset the cached loaded array length to the length var.
9003  RecordKnownProperty(receiver, broker()->length_string(),
9004  sub_builder.get(var_length), false,
9005  compiler::AccessMode::kLoad);
9006 
9007  // ```
9008  // if (index_int32 < length_int32)
9009  // fallthrough
9010  // else
9011  // goto end
9012  // ```
9013  Phi* index_tagged = sub_builder.get(var_index)->Cast<Phi>();
9014  EnsureType(index_tagged, NodeType::kSmi);
9015  ValueNode* index_int32 = GetInt32(index_tagged);
9016 
9017  sub_builder.GotoIfFalse<BranchIfInt32Compare>(
9018  &loop_end, {index_int32, original_length_int32}, Operation::kLessThan);
9019 
9020  // ```
9021  // next_index = index + 1
9022  // ```
9023  ValueNode* next_index_int32 = nullptr;
9024  {
9025  // Eager deopt scope for index increment overflow.
9026  // TODO(pthier): In practice this increment can never overflow, as the max
9027  // possible array length is less than int32 max value. Add a new
9028  // Int32Increment that asserts no overflow instead of deopting.
9029  DeoptFrameScope eager_deopt_scope =
9030  get_eager_deopt_scope(target, receiver, callback, this_arg, index_int32,
9031  index_int32, original_length);
9032  next_index_int32 = AddNewNode<Int32IncrementWithOverflow>({index_int32});
9033  EnsureType(next_index_int32, NodeType::kSmi);
9034  }
9035  // TODO(leszeks): Assert Smi.
9036 
9037  // ```
9038  // element = array.elements[index]
9039  // ```
9040  ValueNode* elements = BuildLoadElements(receiver);
9041  ValueNode* element;
9042  if (IsDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
9043  element = BuildLoadFixedDoubleArrayElement(elements, index_int32);
9044  } else {
9045  element = BuildLoadFixedArrayElement(elements, index_int32);
9046  }
9047 
9048  std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> skip_call;
9049  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
9050  // ```
9051  // if (element is hole) goto skip_call
9052  // ```
9053  skip_call.emplace(
9054  &sub_builder, 2,
9055  std::initializer_list<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable*>{&var_length});
9056  if (elements_kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
9057  sub_builder.GotoIfTrue<BranchIfFloat64IsHole>(&*skip_call, {element});
9058  } else {
9059  sub_builder.GotoIfTrue<BranchIfRootConstant>(&*skip_call, {element},
9060  RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
9061  }
9062  }
9063 
9064  // ```
9065  // callback(this_arg, element, array)
9066  // ```
9067  MaybeReduceResult result;
9068  {
9069  const DeoptFrameScope& lazy_deopt_scope =
9070  get_lazy_deopt_scope(target, receiver, callback, this_arg, index_int32,
9071  next_index_int32, original_length);
9072  CallArguments call_args =
9073  args.count() < 2
9074  ? CallArguments(ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined,
9075  {element, index_tagged, receiver})
9076  : CallArguments(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny,
9077  {this_arg, element, index_tagged, receiver});
9078 
9079  SaveCallSpeculationScope saved(this);
9080  result = ReduceCall(callback, call_args, saved.value());
9081  }
9082 
9083  // ```
9084  // index = next_index
9085  // jump loop_header
9086  // ```
9087  DCHECK_IMPLIES(result.IsDoneWithAbort(), current_block_ == nullptr);
9088 
9089  // No need to finish the loop if this code is unreachable.
9090  if (!result.IsDoneWithAbort()) {
9091  if (process_element_callback) {
9092  ValueNode* value = result.value();
9093  (*process_element_callback)(index_int32, value);
9094  }
9095 
9096  // If any of the receiver's maps were unstable maps, we have to re-check the
9097  // maps on each iteration, in case the callback changed them. That said, we
9098  // know that the maps are valid on the first iteration, so we can rotate the
9099  // check to _after_ the callback, and then elide it if the receiver maps are
9100  // still known to be valid (i.e. the known maps after the call are contained
9101  // inside the known maps before the call).
9102  bool recheck_maps_after_call = receiver_maps_were_unstable;
9103  if (recheck_maps_after_call) {
9104  // No need to recheck maps if there are known maps...
9105  if (auto receiver_info_after_call =
9106  known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(receiver)) {
9107  // ... and those known maps are equal to, or a subset of, the maps
9108  // before the call.
9109  if (receiver_info_after_call &&
9110  receiver_info_after_call->possible_maps_are_known()) {
9111  recheck_maps_after_call = !receiver_maps_before_loop.contains(
9112  receiver_info_after_call->possible_maps());
9113  }
9114  }
9115  }
9116 
9117  // Make sure to finish the loop if we eager deopt in the map check or index
9118  // check.
9119  const DeoptFrameScope& eager_deopt_scope =
9120  get_eager_deopt_scope(target, receiver, callback, this_arg, index_int32,
9121  next_index_int32, original_length);
9122 
9123  if (recheck_maps_after_call) {
9124  // Build the CheckMap manually, since we're doing it with already known
9125  // maps rather than feedback, and we don't need to update known node
9126  // aspects or types since we're at the end of the loop anyway.
9127  bool emit_check_with_migration = std::any_of(
9128  receiver_maps_before_loop.begin(), receiver_maps_before_loop.end(),
9129  [](compiler::MapRef map) { return map.is_migration_target(); });
9130  if (emit_check_with_migration) {
9131  AddNewNode<CheckMapsWithMigration>({receiver},
9132  receiver_maps_before_loop,
9133  CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck);
9134  } else {
9135  AddNewNode<CheckMaps>({receiver}, receiver_maps_before_loop,
9136  CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck);
9137  }
9138  }
9139 
9140  // Check if the index is still in bounds, in case the callback changed the
9141  // length.
9142  ValueNode* current_length = BuildLoadJSArrayLength(receiver);
9143  sub_builder.set(var_length, current_length);
9144 
9145  // Reference compare the loaded length against the original length. If this
9146  // is the same value node, then we didn't have any side effects and didn't
9147  // clear the cached length.
9148  if (current_length != original_length) {
9149  RETURN_IF_ABORT(
9150  TryBuildCheckInt32Condition(original_length_int32, current_length,
9151  AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual,
9152  DeoptimizeReason::kArrayLengthChanged));
9153  }
9154  }
9155 
9156  if (skip_call.has_value()) {
9157  sub_builder.GotoOrTrim(&*skip_call);
9158  sub_builder.Bind(&*skip_call);
9159  }
9160 
9161  sub_builder.set(var_index, next_index_int32);
9162  sub_builder.EndLoop(&loop_header);
9163 
9164  // ```
9165  // bind end
9166  // ```
9167  sub_builder.Bind(&loop_end);
9168 
9169  return ReduceResult::Done();
9170 }
9171 
9172 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceArrayIteratorPrototypeNext(
9173  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9174  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
9175 
9176  ValueNode* receiver = args.receiver();
9177  if (!receiver) return {};
9178 
9179  if (!receiver->Is<InlinedAllocation>()) return {};
9180  VirtualObject* iterator = receiver->Cast<InlinedAllocation>()->object();
9181  if (!iterator->map().IsJSArrayIteratorMap()) {
9182  FAIL("iterator is not a JS array iterator object");
9183  }
9184 
9185  ValueNode* iterated_object =
9186  iterator->get(JSArrayIterator::kIteratedObjectOffset);
9187  ElementsKind elements_kind;
9188  base::SmallVector<compiler::MapRef, 4> maps;
9189  if (iterated_object->Is<InlinedAllocation>()) {
9190  VirtualObject* array = iterated_object->Cast<InlinedAllocation>()->object();
9191  // TODO(victorgomes): Remove this once we track changes in the inlined
9192  // allocated object.
9193  if (iterated_object->Cast<InlinedAllocation>()->IsEscaping()) {
9194  FAIL("allocation is escaping, map could have been changed");
9195  }
9196  // TODO(victorgomes): This effectively disable the optimization for `for-of`
9197  // loops. We need to figure it out a way to re-enable this.
9198  if (IsInsideLoop()) {
9199  FAIL("we're inside a loop, iterated object map could change");
9200  }
9201  auto map = array->map();
9202  if (!map.supports_fast_array_iteration(broker())) {
9203  FAIL("no fast array iteration support");
9204  }
9205  elements_kind = map.elements_kind();
9206  maps.push_back(map);
9207  } else {
9208  auto node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(iterated_object);
9209  if (!node_info || !node_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
9210  FAIL("iterated object is unknown");
9211  }
9212  if (!CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(broker(), node_info->possible_maps(),
9213  &elements_kind)) {
9214  FAIL("no fast array iteration support or incompatible maps");
9215  }
9216  for (auto map : node_info->possible_maps()) {
9217  maps.push_back(map);
9218  }
9219  }
9220 
9221  // TODO(victorgomes): Support typed arrays.
9222  if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
9223  FAIL("no typed arrays support");
9224  }
9225 
9226  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind) &&
9227  !broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
9228  FAIL("no elements protector");
9229  }
9230 
9231  // Load the [[NextIndex]] from the {iterator}.
9232  // We can assume index and length fit in Uint32.
9233  ValueNode* index =
9234  BuildLoadTaggedField(receiver, JSArrayIterator::kNextIndexOffset);
9235  ValueNode* uint32_index;
9236  GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(uint32_index, GetUint32ElementIndex(index));
9237  ValueNode* uint32_length;
9238  GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(uint32_length,
9239  GetUint32ElementIndex(BuildLoadJSArrayLength(
9240  iterated_object, IsFastElementsKind(elements_kind)
9241  ? NodeType::kSmi
9242  : NodeType::kNumber)));
9243 
9244  // Check next index is below length
9245  MaglevSubGraphBuilder subgraph(this, 2);
9246  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable is_done(0);
9247  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable ret_value(1);
9248  RETURN_IF_ABORT(subgraph.Branch(
9249  {&is_done, &ret_value},
9250  [&](auto& builder) {
9251  return BuildBranchIfUint32Compare(builder, Operation::kLessThan,
9252  uint32_index, uint32_length);
9253  },
9254  [&] {
9255  ValueNode* int32_index = GetInt32(uint32_index);
9256  subgraph.set(is_done, GetBooleanConstant(false));
9257  DCHECK(
9258  iterator->get(JSArrayIterator::kKindOffset)->Is<Int32Constant>());
9259  IterationKind iteration_kind = static_cast<IterationKind>(
9260  iterator->get(JSArrayIterator::kKindOffset)
9261  ->Cast<Int32Constant>()
9262  ->value());
9263  if (iteration_kind == IterationKind::kKeys) {
9264  subgraph.set(ret_value, index);
9265  } else {
9266  ValueNode* value;
9267  GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(
9268  value,
9269  TryBuildElementLoadOnJSArrayOrJSObject(
9270  iterated_object, int32_index, base::VectorOf(maps),
9271  elements_kind, KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOBAndHoles));
9272  if (iteration_kind == IterationKind::kEntries) {
9273  ValueNode* key_value_array;
9274  GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(key_value_array,
9275  BuildAndAllocateKeyValueArray(index, value));
9276  subgraph.set(ret_value, key_value_array);
9277  } else {
9278  subgraph.set(ret_value, value);
9279  }
9280  }
9281  // Add 1 to index
9282  ValueNode* next_index = AddNewNode<Int32AddWithOverflow>(
9283  {int32_index, GetInt32Constant(1)});
9284  EnsureType(next_index, NodeType::kSmi);
9285  // Update [[NextIndex]]
9286  BuildStoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(receiver, next_index,
9287  JSArrayIterator::kNextIndexOffset,
9288  StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
9289  return ReduceResult::Done();
9290  },
9291  [&] {
9292  // Index is greater or equal than length.
9293  subgraph.set(is_done, GetBooleanConstant(true));
9294  subgraph.set(ret_value, GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
9295  if (!IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
9296  // Mark the {iterator} as exhausted by setting the [[NextIndex]] to a
9297  // value that will never pass the length check again (aka the maximum
9298  // value possible for the specific iterated object). Note that this is
9299  // different from what the specification says, which is changing the
9300  // [[IteratedObject]] field to undefined, but that makes it difficult
9301  // to eliminate the map checks and "length" accesses in for..of loops.
9302  //
9303  // This is not necessary for JSTypedArray's, since the length of those
9304  // cannot change later and so if we were ever out of bounds for them
9305  // we will stay out-of-bounds forever.
9306  BuildStoreTaggedField(receiver, GetFloat64Constant(kMaxUInt32),
9307  JSArrayIterator::kNextIndexOffset,
9308  StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
9309  }
9310  return ReduceResult::Done();
9311  }));
9312 
9313  // Allocate result object and return.
9314  compiler::MapRef map =
9315  broker()->target_native_context().iterator_result_map(broker());
9316  VirtualObject* iter_result = CreateJSIteratorResult(
9317  map, subgraph.get(ret_value), subgraph.get(is_done));
9318  ValueNode* allocation =
9319  BuildInlinedAllocation(iter_result, AllocationType::kYoung);
9320  return allocation;
9321 }

9327  if (!CheckType(receiver, NodeType::kJSReceiver)) {
9328  return {};

9330  return BuildAndAllocateJSArrayIterator(receiver, IterationKind::kEntries);
9331 }

9353 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceStringFromCharCode(
9354  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9355  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
9356  if (args.count() != 1) return {};
9357  return AddNewNode<BuiltinStringFromCharCode>({GetTruncatedInt32ForToNumber(
9358  args[0], NodeType::kNumberOrOddball,
9359  TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball)});

9361 
9362 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceConstantStringAt(
9363  ValueNode* receiver, ValueNode* index, StringAtOOBMode oob_mode) {
9364  auto constant_receiver = TryGetConstant(receiver);
9365  if (!constant_receiver) return {};
9366  if (!constant_receiver->IsString()) {
9367  return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kNotAString);
9368  }
9369  compiler::StringRef string = constant_receiver->AsString();
9370  auto maybe_constant_index = TryGetInt32Constant(index);
9371  if (!maybe_constant_index) return {};
9372  int32_t constant_index = *maybe_constant_index;
9373 
9374  if (static_cast<uint32_t>(constant_index) >= string.length()) {
9375  switch (oob_mode) {
9376  case StringAtOOBMode::kElement:
9377  // For element access, a negative index triggers a named lookup rather
9378  // than an element lookup; when this is the case, we shouldn't be trying
9379  // to optimize an elements access at all, so deopt.
9380  if (constant_index < 0) {
9381  return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds);
9382  }
9383  // Otherwise, this is hole-like access, so guard against elements on the
9384  // prototype to return undefined.
9385  if (broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
9386  return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
9387  }
9388  // If the no elements protector is invalidated, unconditionally deopt.
9389  // This shouldn't trigger a deopt look because the feedback should
9390  // transition to megamorphic.
9391  return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds);
9392  case StringAtOOBMode::kCharAt: {
9393  // OOB for charAt is always the empty string.
9394  return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kempty_string);
9395  }
9396  }
9397  UNREACHABLE();
9398  }
9399 
9400  if (std::optional<uint16_t> value =
9401  string.GetChar(broker(), constant_index)) {
9402  return GetConstantSingleCharacterStringFromCode(*value);
9403  }
9404  return {};
9405 }
9406 
9407 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceStringPrototypeCharAt(
9408  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9409  if (!CanSpeculateCall({SpeculationMode::kDisallowBoundsCheckSpeculation})) {
9410  return {};
9411  }
9412 
9413  ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
9414  ValueNode* index;
9415  if (args.count() == 0) {
9416  // Index is the undefined object. ToIntegerOrInfinity(undefined) = 0.
9417  index = GetInt32Constant(0);
9418  } else {
9419  index = GetInt32ElementIndex(args[0]);
9420  }
9421  // Any other argument is ignored.
9422 
9423  RETURN_IF_DONE(
9424  TryReduceConstantStringAt(receiver, index, StringAtOOBMode::kCharAt));
9425 
9426  // Ensure that {receiver} is actually a String.
9427  RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckString(receiver));
9428  // And index is below length.
9429  ValueNode* length = BuildLoadStringLength(receiver);
9430 
9431  auto GetCharAt = [&]() -> ValueNode* {
9432  bool is_seq_one_byte =
9433  v8_flags.specialize_code_for_one_byte_seq_strings &&
9434  NodeTypeIs(GetType(receiver), NodeType::kSeqOneByteString);
9435  if (is_seq_one_byte) {
9436  return AddNewNode<SeqOneByteStringAt>({receiver, index});
9437  } else {
9438  return AddNewNode<StringAt>({receiver, index});
9439  }
9440  };
9441  if (current_speculation_mode_ ==
9442  SpeculationMode::kDisallowBoundsCheckSpeculation) {
9443  return Select(
9444  [&](auto& builder) {
9445  // Do unsafe conversions of length and index into uint32, to do an
9446  // unsigned comparison. The index might actually be a negative signed
9447  // value, but this "unsafe" cast will still work, converting it into a
9448  // large unsigned value which compares greater than the length.
9449  return BuildBranchIfUint32Compare(
9450  builder, Operation::kLessThan,
9451  AddNewNode<UnsafeInt32ToUint32>({index}),
9452  AddNewNode<UnsafeInt32ToUint32>({length}));
9453  },
9454  [&]() -> ValueNode* { return GetCharAt(); },
9455  [&]() { return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kempty_string); });
9456  }
9457 
9458  DCHECK_EQ(current_speculation_mode_, SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation);
9459  RETURN_IF_ABORT(TryBuildCheckInt32Condition(
9460  index, length, AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThan,
9461  DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds));
9462  return GetCharAt();
9463 }
9464 
9465 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceStringPrototypeCharCodeAt(
9466  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9467  if (!CanSpeculateCall({SpeculationMode::kDisallowBoundsCheckSpeculation})) {
9468  return {};
9469  }
9470  ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
9471  ValueNode* index;
9472  if (args.count() == 0) {
9473  // Index is the undefined object. ToIntegerOrInfinity(undefined) = 0.
9474  index = GetInt32Constant(0);
9475  } else {
9476  index = GetInt32ElementIndex(args[0]);
9477  }
9478  // Any other argument is ignored.
9479 
9480  // Try to constant-fold if receiver and index are constant
9481  if (auto cst = TryGetConstant(receiver)) {
9482  if (cst->IsString() && index->Is<Int32Constant>()) {
9483  compiler::StringRef str = cst->AsString();
9484  int idx = index->Cast<Int32Constant>()->value();
9485  if (idx >= 0 && static_cast<uint32_t>(idx) < str.length()) {
9486  if (std::optional<uint16_t> value = str.GetChar(broker(), idx)) {
9487  return GetSmiConstant(*value);
9488  }
9489  }
9490  }
9491  }
9492 
9493  // Ensure that {receiver} is actually a String.
9494  RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckString(receiver));
9495  // And index is below length.
9496  ValueNode* length = BuildLoadStringLength(receiver);
9497  auto GetCharCodeAt = [&]() -> ValueNode* {
9498  bool is_seq_one_byte =
9499  v8_flags.specialize_code_for_one_byte_seq_strings &&
9500  NodeTypeIs(GetType(receiver), NodeType::kSeqOneByteString);
9501  if (is_seq_one_byte) {
9502  return AddNewNode<BuiltinSeqOneByteStringCharCodeAt>({receiver, index});
9503  } else {
9504  return AddNewNode<BuiltinStringPrototypeCharCodeOrCodePointAt>(
9505  {receiver, index},
9506  BuiltinStringPrototypeCharCodeOrCodePointAt::kCharCodeAt);
9507  }
9508  };
9509 
9510  if (current_speculation_mode_ ==
9511  SpeculationMode::kDisallowBoundsCheckSpeculation) {
9512  return Select(
9513  [&](auto& builder) {
9514  // Do unsafe conversions of length and index into uint32, to do an
9515  // unsigned comparison. The index might actually be a negative signed
9516  // value, but this "unsafe" cast will still work, converting it into a
9517  // large unsigned value which compares greater than the length.
9518  return BuildBranchIfUint32Compare(
9519  builder, Operation::kLessThan,
9520  AddNewNode<UnsafeInt32ToUint32>({index}),
9521  AddNewNode<UnsafeInt32ToUint32>({length}));
9522  },
9523  [&]() -> ValueNode* { return GetCharCodeAt(); },
9524  [&]() { return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kNanValue); });
9525  }
9526 
9527  RETURN_IF_ABORT(TryBuildCheckInt32Condition(
9528  index, length, AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThan,
9529  DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds));
9530  return GetCharCodeAt();
9531 }
9532 
9533 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceStringPrototypeCodePointAt(
9534  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9535  if (!CanSpeculateCall({SpeculationMode::kDisallowBoundsCheckSpeculation})) {
9536  return {};
9537  }
9538  ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
9539  ValueNode* index;
9540  if (args.count() == 0) {
9541  // Index is the undefined object. ToIntegerOrInfinity(undefined) = 0.
9542  index = GetInt32Constant(0);
9543  } else {
9544  index = GetInt32ElementIndex(args[0]);
9545  }
9546  // Any other argument is ignored.
9547  // Ensure that {receiver} is actually a String.
9548  RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckString(receiver));
9549  // And index is below length.
9550  ValueNode* length = BuildLoadStringLength(receiver);
9551 
9552  auto GetCodePointAt = [&]() -> ValueNode* {
9553  bool is_seq_one_byte =
9554  v8_flags.specialize_code_for_one_byte_seq_strings &&
9555  NodeTypeIs(GetType(receiver), NodeType::kSeqOneByteString);
9556  if (is_seq_one_byte) {
9557  // For one-byte strings, codePointAt == charCodeAt, since there are no
9558  // surrogate pairs.
9559  return AddNewNode<BuiltinSeqOneByteStringCharCodeAt>({receiver, index});
9560  } else {
9561  return AddNewNode<BuiltinStringPrototypeCharCodeOrCodePointAt>(
9562  {receiver, index},
9563  BuiltinStringPrototypeCharCodeOrCodePointAt::kCodePointAt);
9564  }
9565  };
9566 
9567  if (current_speculation_mode_ ==
9568  SpeculationMode::kDisallowBoundsCheckSpeculation) {
9569  return Select(
9570  [&](auto& builder) {
9571  // Do unsafe conversions of length and index into uint32, to do an
9572  // unsigned comparison. The index might actually be a negative signed
9573  // value, but this "unsafe" cast will still work, converting it into a
9574  // large unsigned value which compares greater than the length.
9575  return BuildBranchIfUint32Compare(
9576  builder, Operation::kLessThan,
9577  AddNewNode<UnsafeInt32ToUint32>({index}),
9578  AddNewNode<UnsafeInt32ToUint32>({length}));
9579  },
9580  [&]() -> ValueNode* { return GetCodePointAt(); },
9581  [&]() { return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue); });
9582  }
9583 
9584  RETURN_IF_ABORT(TryBuildCheckInt32Condition(
9585  index, length, AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThan,
9586  DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds));
9587  return GetCodePointAt();
9588 }
9589 
9590 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceStringPrototypeIterator(
9591  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9592  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
9593  ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
9594  // Ensure that {receiver} is actually a String.
9595  RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckString(receiver));
9596  compiler::MapRef map =
9597  broker()->target_native_context().initial_string_iterator_map(broker());
9598  VirtualObject* string_iterator = CreateJSStringIterator(map, receiver);
9599  ValueNode* allocation =
9600  BuildInlinedAllocation(string_iterator, AllocationType::kYoung);
9601  return allocation;
9602 }

9605 
9606 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceStringPrototypeLocaleCompareIntl(
9607  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9608  if (args.count() < 1 || args.count() > 3) return {};
9609 
9610  LocalFactory* factory = local_isolate()->factory();
9611  compiler::ObjectRef undefined_ref = broker()->undefined_value();
9612 
9613  DirectHandle<Object> locales_handle;
9614  ValueNode* locales_node = nullptr;
9615  if (args.count() > 1) {
9616  compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_locales = TryGetConstant(args[1]);
9617  if (!maybe_locales) return {};
9618  compiler::HeapObjectRef locales = maybe_locales.value();
9619  if (locales.equals(undefined_ref)) {
9620  locales_handle = factory->undefined_value();
9621  locales_node = GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
9622  } else {
9623  if (!locales.IsString()) return {};
9624  compiler::StringRef sref = locales.AsString();
9625  std::optional<Handle<String>> maybe_locales_handle =
9626  sref.ObjectIfContentAccessible(broker());
9627  if (!maybe_locales_handle) return {};
9628  locales_handle = *maybe_locales_handle;
9629  locales_node = args[1];
9630  }
9631  } else {
9632  locales_handle = factory->undefined_value();
9633  locales_node = GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
9634  }
9635 
9636  if (args.count() > 2) {
9637  compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_options = TryGetConstant(args[2]);
9638  if (!maybe_options) return {};
9639  if (!maybe_options.value().equals(undefined_ref)) return {};
9640  }
9641 
9642  DCHECK(!locales_handle.is_null());
9643  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(locales_node);
9644 
9645  if (Intl::CompareStringsOptionsFor(local_isolate(), locales_handle,
9646  factory->undefined_value()) !=
9647  Intl::CompareStringsOptions::kTryFastPath) {
9648  return {};
9649  }
9650  return BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kStringFastLocaleCompare>(
9651  {GetConstant(target),
9652  GetTaggedValue(GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver())),
9653  GetTaggedValue(args[0]), GetTaggedValue(locales_node)});
9654 }
9655 
9656 #endif // V8_INTL_SUPPORT

9675 template <typename LoadNode>
9676 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildLoadDataView(
9677  const CallArguments& args, ExternalArrayType type) {
9678  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
9679  if (!broker()->dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
9680  // TODO(victorgomes): Add checks whether the array has been detached.
9681  return {};
9682  }
9683  // TODO(victorgomes): Add data view to known types.
9684  ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
9685  AddNewNode<CheckInstanceType>({receiver}, CheckType::kCheckHeapObject,
9686  JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE, JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE);
9687  // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE too.
9688  ValueNode* offset =
9689  args[0] ? GetInt32ElementIndex(args[0]) : GetInt32Constant(0);
9690  AddNewNode<CheckJSDataViewBounds>({receiver, offset}, type);
9691  ValueNode* is_little_endian = args[1] ? args[1] : GetBooleanConstant(false);
9692  return AddNewNode<LoadNode>({receiver, offset, is_little_endian}, type);
9693 }

9695 template <typename StoreNode, typename Function>
9696 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildStoreDataView(
9697  const CallArguments& args, ExternalArrayType type, Function&& getValue) {
9698  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
9699  if (!broker()->dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
9700  // TODO(victorgomes): Add checks whether the array has been detached.
9701  return {};
9702  }
9703  // TODO(victorgomes): Add data view to known types.
9704  ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
9705  AddNewNode<CheckInstanceType>({receiver}, CheckType::kCheckHeapObject,
9706  JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE, JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE);
9707  // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE too.
9708  ValueNode* offset =
9709  args[0] ? GetInt32ElementIndex(args[0]) : GetInt32Constant(0);
9710  AddNewNode<CheckJSDataViewBounds>({receiver, offset},
9711  ExternalArrayType::kExternalFloat64Array);
9712  ValueNode* value = getValue(args[1]);
9713  ValueNode* is_little_endian = args[2] ? args[2] : GetBooleanConstant(false);
9714  AddNewNode<StoreNode>({receiver, offset, value, is_little_endian}, type);
9715  return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
9716 }

9774 namespace {
9775 bool AllOfInstanceTypesUnsafe(const PossibleMaps& maps,
9776  std::function<bool(InstanceType)> f) {
9777  auto instance_type = [f](compiler::MapRef map) {
9778  return f(map.instance_type());
9779  };
9780  return std::all_of(maps.begin(), maps.end(), instance_type);
9781 }
9782 bool AllOfInstanceTypesAre(const PossibleMaps& maps, InstanceType type) {
9783  CHECK(!InstanceTypeChecker::IsString(type));
9784  return AllOfInstanceTypesUnsafe(
9785  maps, [type](InstanceType other) { return type == other; });
9786 }
9787 } // namespace
9788 
9789 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceDatePrototypeGetField(
9790  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args,
9791  JSDate::FieldIndex field_index) {
9792  DCHECK_LT(field_index, JSDate::kFirstUncachedField);
9793  if (!v8_flags.maglev_inline_date_accessors) return {};
9794  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
9795 
9796  if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
9797  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
9798  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Date.prototype.GetXXX - no receiver"
9799  << std::endl;
9800  }
9801  return {};
9802  }
9803 
9804  ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
9805  const NodeInfo* receiver_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(receiver);
9806  // If the map set is not found, then we don't know anything about the map of
9807  // the receiver, so bail.
9808  if (!receiver_info || !receiver_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
9809  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
9810  std::cout
9811  << " ! Failed to reduce Date.prototype.GetXXX - unknown receiver map"
9812  << std::endl;
9813  }
9814  return {};
9815  }
9816 
9817  const PossibleMaps& possible_receiver_maps = receiver_info->possible_maps();
9818  // If the set of possible maps is empty, then there's no possible map for this
9819  // receiver, therefore this path is unreachable at runtime. We're unlikely to
9820  // ever hit this case, BuildCheckMaps should already unconditionally deopt,
9821  // but check it in case another checking operation fails to statically
9822  // unconditionally deopt.
9823  if (possible_receiver_maps.is_empty()) {
9824  // TODO(leszeks): Add an unreachable assert here.
9825  return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
9826  }
9827 
9828  if (!AllOfInstanceTypesAre(possible_receiver_maps, JS_DATE_TYPE)) {
9829  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
9830  std::cout
9831  << " ! Failed to reduce Date.prototype.GetXXX - wrong receiver maps "
9832  << std::endl;
9833  }
9834  return {};
9835  }
9836 
9837  if (!broker()
9838  ->dependencies()
9839  ->DependOnNoDateTimeConfigurationChangeProtector()) {
9840  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
9841  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Date.prototype.GetXXX - "
9842  "NoDateTimeConfigurationChangeProtector invalidated"
9843  << std::endl;
9844  }
9845  return {};
9846  }
9847 
9848  int field_offset = JSDate::kYearOffset + field_index * kTaggedSize;
9849  ValueNode* field_value = BuildLoadTaggedField(receiver, field_offset);
9850  return field_value;
9851 }

9882 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceFunctionPrototypeCall(
9883  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9884  // We can't reduce Function#call when there is no receiver function.
9885  if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {

9887  }

9895 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceFunctionPrototypeApply(
9896  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9897  compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_receiver;
9898  if (current_speculation_feedback_.IsValid()) {
9899  const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& processed_feedback =
9900  broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(current_speculation_feedback_);
9901  DCHECK_EQ(processed_feedback.kind(), compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kCall);
9902  const compiler::CallFeedback& call_feedback = processed_feedback.AsCall();
9903  if (call_feedback.call_feedback_content() ==
9904  CallFeedbackContent::kReceiver) {
9905  maybe_receiver = call_feedback.target();
9906  }
9907  }
9908  return TryReduceFunctionPrototypeApplyCallWithReceiver(
9909  maybe_receiver, args, current_speculation_feedback_);

9914 template <size_t MaxKindCount, typename KindsToIndexFunc>
9915 bool CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(
9916  compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker, const PossibleMaps& possible_maps,
9917  std::array<SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>, MaxKindCount>& map_kinds,
9918  KindsToIndexFunc&& elements_kind_to_index, int* unique_kind_count,
9919  bool is_loading) {
9920  uint8_t kind_bitmap = 0;
9921  for (compiler::MapRef map : possible_maps) {
9922  if (!map.supports_fast_array_resize(broker)) {
9923  return false;
9924  }
9925  ElementsKind kind = map.elements_kind();
9926  if (is_loading && kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
9927  return false;
9928  }
9929  // Group maps by elements kind, using the provided function to translate
9930  // elements kinds to indices.
9931  // kind_bitmap is used to get the unique kinds (predecessor count for the
9932  // next block).
9933  uint8_t kind_index = elements_kind_to_index(kind);
9934  kind_bitmap |= 1 << kind_index;
9935  map_kinds[kind_index].push_back(map);
9936  }
9937 
9938  *unique_kind_count = base::bits::CountPopulation(kind_bitmap);
9939  DCHECK_GE(*unique_kind_count, 1);
9940  return true;
9941 }
9942 
9943 } // namespace
9944 
9945 template <typename MapKindsT, typename IndexToElementsKindFunc,
9946  typename BuildKindSpecificFunc>
9947 MaybeReduceResult
9948 MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildJSArrayBuiltinMapSwitchOnElementsKind(
9949  ValueNode* receiver, const MapKindsT& map_kinds,
9950  MaglevSubGraphBuilder& sub_graph,
9951  std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label>& do_return,
9952  int unique_kind_count, IndexToElementsKindFunc&& index_to_elements_kind,
9953  BuildKindSpecificFunc&& build_kind_specific) {
9954  // TODO(pthier): Support map packing.
9955  DCHECK(!V8_MAP_PACKING_BOOL);
9956  ValueNode* receiver_map =
9957  BuildLoadTaggedField(receiver, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
9958  int emitted_kind_checks = 0;
9959  bool any_successful = false;
9960  for (size_t kind_index = 0; kind_index < map_kinds.size(); kind_index++) {
9961  const auto& maps = map_kinds[kind_index];
9962  // Skip kinds we haven't observed.
9963  if (maps.empty()) continue;
9964  ElementsKind kind = index_to_elements_kind(kind_index);
9965  // Create branches for all but the last elements kind. We don't need
9966  // to check the maps of the last kind, as all possible maps have already
9967  // been checked when the property (builtin name) was loaded.
9968  if (++emitted_kind_checks < unique_kind_count) {
9969  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label check_next_map(&sub_graph, 1);
9970  std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> do_push;
9971  if (maps.size() > 1) {
9972  do_push.emplace(&sub_graph, static_cast<int>(maps.size()));
9973  for (size_t map_index = 1; map_index < maps.size(); map_index++) {
9974  sub_graph.GotoIfTrue<BranchIfReferenceEqual>(
9975  &*do_push, {receiver_map, GetConstant(maps[map_index])});
9976  }
9977  }
9978  sub_graph.GotoIfFalse<BranchIfReferenceEqual>(
9979  &check_next_map, {receiver_map, GetConstant(maps[0])});
9980  if (do_push.has_value()) {
9981  sub_graph.Goto(&*do_push);
9982  sub_graph.Bind(&*do_push);
9983  }
9984  if (!build_kind_specific(kind).IsDoneWithAbort()) {
9985  any_successful = true;
9986  }
9987  DCHECK(do_return.has_value());
9988  sub_graph.GotoOrTrim(&*do_return);
9989  sub_graph.Bind(&check_next_map);
9990  } else {
9991  if (!build_kind_specific(kind).IsDoneWithAbort()) {
9992  any_successful = true;
9993  }
9994  if (do_return.has_value()) {
9995  sub_graph.GotoOrTrim(&*do_return);
9996  }
9997  }
9998  }
9999  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!any_successful, !current_block_);
10000  return any_successful ? ReduceResult::Done() : ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
10001 }
10002 
10003 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceMapPrototypeGet(
10004  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
10005  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
10006  if (!is_turbolev()) {
10007  // TODO(dmercadier): consider also doing this lowering for Maglev. This is
10008  // currently not done, because to be efficient, this lowering would need to
10009  // inline FindOrderedHashMapEntryInt32Key (cf
10010  // turboshaft/machine-lowering-reducer-inl.h), which might be a bit too
10011  // low-level for Maglev.
10012  return {};
10013  }
10014 
10015  if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
10016  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
10017  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Map.prototype.Get - no receiver"
10018  << std::endl;
10019  }
10020  return {};
10021  }
10022  if (args.count() != 1) {
10023  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
10024  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Map.prototype.Get - invalid "
10025  "argument count"
10026  << std::endl;
10027  }
10028  return {};
10029  }
10030 
10031  ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
10032  const NodeInfo* receiver_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(receiver);
10033  // If the map set is not found, then we don't know anything about the map of
10034  // the receiver, so bail.
10035  if (!receiver_info || !receiver_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
10036  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
10037  std::cout
10038  << " ! Failed to reduce Map.prototype.Get - unknown receiver map"
10039  << std::endl;
10040  }
10041  return {};
10042  }
10043 
10044  const PossibleMaps& possible_receiver_maps = receiver_info->possible_maps();
10045  // If the set of possible maps is empty, then there's no possible map for this
10046  // receiver, therefore this path is unreachable at runtime. We're unlikely to
10047  // ever hit this case, BuildCheckMaps should already unconditionally deopt,
10048  // but check it in case another checking operation fails to statically
10049  // unconditionally deopt.
10050  if (possible_receiver_maps.is_empty()) {
10051  // TODO(leszeks): Add an unreachable assert here.
10052  return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
10053  }
10054 
10055  if (!AllOfInstanceTypesAre(possible_receiver_maps, JS_MAP_TYPE)) {
10056  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
10057  std::cout
10058  << " ! Failed to reduce Map.prototype.Get - wrong receiver maps "
10059  << std::endl;
10060  }
10061  return {};
10062  }
10063 
10064  ValueNode* key = args[0];
10065  ValueNode* table = BuildLoadTaggedField(receiver, JSCollection::kTableOffset);
10066 
10067  ValueNode* entry;
10068  auto key_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(key);
10069  if (key_info && key_info->alternative().int32()) {
10070  entry = AddNewNode<MapPrototypeGetInt32Key>(
10071  {table, key_info->alternative().int32()});
10072  } else {
10073  entry = AddNewNode<MapPrototypeGet>({table, key});
10074  }
10075 
10076  return entry;
10077 }

10090  if (args.count() != 1) {

10109  // If the set of possible maps is empty, then there's no possible map for this

10111  // ever hit this case, BuildCheckMaps should already unconditionally deopt,
10112  // but check it in case another checking operation fails to statically
10113  // unconditionally deopt.
10114  if (possible_receiver_maps.is_empty()) {
