10133 
10134 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceArrayPrototypePush(
10135  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
10136  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
10137  // We can't reduce Function#call when there is no receiver function.
10138  if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
10139  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
10140  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.push - no receiver"
10141  << std::endl;
10142  }
10143  return {};
10144  }
10145  // TODO(pthier): Support multiple arguments.
10146  if (args.count() != 1) {
10147  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
10148  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.push - invalid "
10149  "argument count"
10150  << std::endl;
10151  }
10152  return {};
10153  }
10154  ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
10155 
10156  auto node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(receiver);
10157  // If the map set is not found, then we don't know anything about the map of
10158  // the receiver, so bail.
10159  if (!node_info || !node_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
10160  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
10161  std::cout
10162  << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.push - unknown receiver map"
10163  << std::endl;
10164  }
10165  return {};
10166  }
10167 
10168  const PossibleMaps& possible_maps = node_info->possible_maps();
10169  // If the set of possible maps is empty, then there's no possible map for this
10170  // receiver, therefore this path is unreachable at runtime. We're unlikely to
10171  // ever hit this case, BuildCheckMaps should already unconditionally deopt,
10172  // but check it in case another checking operation fails to statically
10173  // unconditionally deopt.
10174  if (possible_maps.is_empty()) {
10175  // TODO(leszeks): Add an unreachable assert here.
10176  return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
10177  }
10178 
10179  if (!broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
10180  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
10181  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.push - "
10182  "NoElementsProtector invalidated"
10183  << std::endl;
10184  }
10185  return {};
10186  }
10187 
10188  // Check that inlining resizing array builtins is supported and group maps
10189  // by elements kind.
10190  std::array<SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>, 3> map_kinds = {
10191  SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>(zone()),
10192  SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>(zone()),
10193  SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>(zone())};
10194  // Function to group maps by elements kind, ignoring packedness. Packedness
10195  // doesn't matter for push().
10196  // Kinds we care about are all paired in the first 6 values of ElementsKind,
10197  // so we can use integer division to truncate holeyness.
10198  auto elements_kind_to_index = [&](ElementsKind kind) {
10199  static_assert(kFastElementsKindCount <= 6);
10200  static_assert(kFastElementsKindPackedToHoley == 1);
10201  return static_cast<uint8_t>(kind) / 2;
10202  };
10203  auto index_to_elements_kind = [&](uint8_t kind_index) {
10204  return static_cast<ElementsKind>(kind_index * 2);
10205  };
10206  int unique_kind_count;
10207  if (!CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(broker(), possible_maps, map_kinds,
10208  elements_kind_to_index, &unique_kind_count,
10209  false)) {
10210  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
10211  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.push - Map doesn't "
10212  "support fast resizing"
10213  << std::endl;
10214  }
10215  return {};
10216  }
10217 
10218  MaglevSubGraphBuilder sub_graph(this, 0);
10219 
10220  std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> do_return;
10221  if (unique_kind_count > 1) {
10222  do_return.emplace(&sub_graph, unique_kind_count);
10223  }
10224 
10225  ValueNode* old_array_length_smi;
10226  GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(old_array_length_smi,
10227  GetSmiValue(BuildLoadJSArrayLength(receiver)));
10228  ValueNode* old_array_length =
10229  AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiUntag>({old_array_length_smi});
10230  ValueNode* new_array_length_smi =
10231  AddNewNode<CheckedSmiIncrement>({old_array_length_smi});
10232 
10233  ValueNode* elements_array = BuildLoadElements(receiver);
10234  ValueNode* elements_array_length = BuildLoadFixedArrayLength(elements_array);
10235 
10236  auto build_array_push = [&](ElementsKind kind) {
10237  ValueNode* value;
10238  GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(value, ConvertForStoring(args[0], kind));
10239 
10240  ValueNode* writable_elements_array = AddNewNode<MaybeGrowFastElements>(
10241  {elements_array, receiver, old_array_length, elements_array_length},
10242  kind);
10243 
10244  AddNewNode<StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier>({receiver, new_array_length_smi},
10245  JSArray::kLengthOffset,
10246  StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
10247 
10248  // Do the store
10249  if (IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)) {
10250  BuildStoreFixedDoubleArrayElement(writable_elements_array,
10251  old_array_length, value);
10252  } else {
10253  DCHECK(IsSmiElementsKind(kind) || IsObjectElementsKind(kind));
10254  BuildStoreFixedArrayElement(writable_elements_array, old_array_length,
10255  value);
10256  }
10257  return ReduceResult::Done();
10258  };
10259 
10260  RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildJSArrayBuiltinMapSwitchOnElementsKind(
10261  receiver, map_kinds, sub_graph, do_return, unique_kind_count,
10262  index_to_elements_kind, build_array_push));
10263 
10264  if (do_return.has_value()) {
10265  sub_graph.Bind(&*do_return);
10266  }
10267  RecordKnownProperty(receiver, broker()->length_string(), new_array_length_smi,
10268  false, compiler::AccessMode::kStore);
10269  return new_array_length_smi;
10270 }
10271 
10272 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceArrayPrototypePop(
10273  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
10274  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
10275  // We can't reduce Function#call when there is no receiver function.
10276  if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
10277  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
10278  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.pop - no receiver"
10279  << std::endl;
10280  }
10281  return {};
10282  }
10283 
10284  ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
10285 
10286  auto node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(receiver);
10287  // If the map set is not found, then we don't know anything about the map of
10288  // the receiver, so bail.
10289  if (!node_info || !node_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
10290  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
10291  std::cout
10292  << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.pop - unknown receiver map"
10293  << std::endl;
10294  }
10295  return {};
10296  }
10297 
10298  const PossibleMaps& possible_maps = node_info->possible_maps();
10299 
10300  // If the set of possible maps is empty, then there's no possible map for this
10301  // receiver, therefore this path is unreachable at runtime. We're unlikely to
10302  // ever hit this case, BuildCheckMaps should already unconditionally deopt,
10303  // but check it in case another checking operation fails to statically
10304  // unconditionally deopt.
10305  if (possible_maps.is_empty()) {
10306  // TODO(leszeks): Add an unreachable assert here.
10307  return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
10308  }
10309 
10310  if (!broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
10311  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
10312  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.pop - "
10313  "NoElementsProtector invalidated"
10314  << std::endl;
10315  }
10316  return {};
10317  }
10318 
10319  constexpr int max_kind_count = 4;
10320  std::array<SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>, max_kind_count> map_kinds = {
10321  SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>(zone()),
10322  SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>(zone()),
10323  SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>(zone()),
10324  SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>(zone())};
10325  // Smi and Object elements kinds are treated as identical for pop, so we can
10326  // group them together without differentiation.
10327  // ElementsKind is mapped to an index in the 4 element array using:
10328  // - Bit 2 (Only set for double in the fast element range) is mapped to bit
10329  // 1)
10330  // - Bit 0 (packedness)
10331  // The complete mapping:
10332  // +-------+----------------------------------------------+
10333  // | Index | ElementsKinds |
10334  // +-------+----------------------------------------------+
10335  // | 0 | PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS and PACKED_ELEMENTS |
10336  // | 1 | HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENETS and HOLEY_ELEMENTS |
10337  // | 2 | PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS |
10338  // | 3 | HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS |
10339  // +-------+----------------------------------------------+
10340  auto elements_kind_to_index = [&](ElementsKind kind) {
10341  uint8_t kind_int = static_cast<uint8_t>(kind);
10342  uint8_t kind_index = ((kind_int & 0x4) >> 1) | (kind_int & 0x1);
10343  DCHECK_LT(kind_index, max_kind_count);
10344  return kind_index;
10345  };
10346  auto index_to_elements_kind = [&](uint8_t kind_index) {
10347  uint8_t kind_int;
10348  kind_int = ((kind_index & 0x2) << 1) | (kind_index & 0x1);
10349  return static_cast<ElementsKind>(kind_int);
10350  };
10351 
10352  int unique_kind_count;
10353  if (!CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(broker(), possible_maps, map_kinds,
10354  elements_kind_to_index, &unique_kind_count,
10355  true)) {
10356  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
10357  std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.pop - Map doesn't "
10358  "support fast resizing"
10359  << std::endl;
10360  }
10361  return {};
10362  }
10363 
10364  MaglevSubGraphBuilder sub_graph(this, 2);
10365  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable var_value(0);
10366  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable var_new_array_length(1);
10367 
10368  std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> do_return =
10369  std::make_optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label>(
10370  &sub_graph, unique_kind_count + 1,
10371  std::initializer_list<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable*>{
10372  &var_value, &var_new_array_length});
10373  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label empty_array(&sub_graph, 1);
10374 
10375  ValueNode* old_array_length_smi;
10376  GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(old_array_length_smi,
10377  GetSmiValue(BuildLoadJSArrayLength(receiver)));
10378 
10379  // If the array is empty, skip the pop and return undefined.
10380  sub_graph.GotoIfTrue<BranchIfReferenceEqual>(
10381  &empty_array, {old_array_length_smi, GetSmiConstant(0)});
10382 
10383  ValueNode* elements_array = BuildLoadElements(receiver);
10384  ValueNode* new_array_length_smi =
10385  AddNewNode<CheckedSmiDecrement>({old_array_length_smi});
10386  ValueNode* new_array_length =
10387  AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiUntag>({new_array_length_smi});
10388  sub_graph.set(var_new_array_length, new_array_length_smi);
10389 
10390  auto build_array_pop = [&](ElementsKind kind) {
10391  // Handle COW if needed.
10392  ValueNode* writable_elements_array =
10393  IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(kind)
10394  ? AddNewNode<EnsureWritableFastElements>({elements_array, receiver})
10395  : elements_array;
10396 
10397  // Store new length.
10398  AddNewNode<StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier>({receiver, new_array_length_smi},
10399  JSArray::kLengthOffset,
10400  StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
10401 
10402  // Load the value and store the hole in it's place.
10403  ValueNode* value;
10404  if (IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)) {
10405  value = BuildLoadFixedDoubleArrayElement(writable_elements_array,
10406  new_array_length);
10407  BuildStoreFixedDoubleArrayElement(
10408  writable_elements_array, new_array_length,
10409  GetFloat64Constant(Float64::FromBits(kHoleNanInt64)));
10410  } else {
10411  DCHECK(IsSmiElementsKind(kind) || IsObjectElementsKind(kind));
10412  value =
10413  BuildLoadFixedArrayElement(writable_elements_array, new_array_length);
10414  BuildStoreFixedArrayElement(writable_elements_array, new_array_length,
10415  GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTheHoleValue));
10416  }
10417 
10418  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
10419  value = AddNewNode<ConvertHoleToUndefined>({value});
10420  }
10421  sub_graph.set(var_value, value);
10422  return ReduceResult::Done();
10423  };
10424 
10425  RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildJSArrayBuiltinMapSwitchOnElementsKind(
10426  receiver, map_kinds, sub_graph, do_return, unique_kind_count,
10427  index_to_elements_kind, build_array_pop));
10428 
10429  sub_graph.Bind(&empty_array);
10430  sub_graph.set(var_new_array_length, GetSmiConstant(0));
10431  sub_graph.set(var_value, GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
10432  sub_graph.Goto(&*do_return);
10433 
10434  sub_graph.Bind(&*do_return);
10435  RecordKnownProperty(receiver, broker()->length_string(),
10436  sub_graph.get(var_new_array_length), false,
10437  compiler::AccessMode::kStore);
10438  return sub_graph.get(var_value);
10439 }
10440 
10441 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceFunctionPrototypeHasInstance(
10442  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
10443  // We can't reduce Function#hasInstance when there is no receiver function.
10444  if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
10445  return {};
10446  }
10447  if (args.count() != 1) {
10448  return {};
10449  }
10450  compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_receiver_constant =
10451  TryGetConstant(args.receiver());
10452  if (!maybe_receiver_constant) {
10453  return {};
10454  }
10455  compiler::HeapObjectRef receiver_object = maybe_receiver_constant.value();
10456  if (!receiver_object.IsJSObject() ||
10457  !receiver_object.map(broker()).is_callable()) {
10458  return {};
10459  }
10460  return BuildOrdinaryHasInstance(args[0], receiver_object.AsJSObject(),
10461  nullptr);
10462 }
10463 
10464 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty(
10465  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
10466  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
10467  if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
10468  return {};
10469  }
10470 
10471  // We can constant-fold the {receiver.hasOwnProperty(name)} builtin call to
10472  // the {True} node in this case:
10473 
10474  // for (name in receiver) {
10475  // if (receiver.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
10476  // ...
10477  // }
10478  // }
10479 
10480  if (args.count() != 1 || args[0] != current_for_in_state.key) {
10481  return {};
10482  }
10483  ValueNode* receiver = args.receiver();
10484  if (receiver == current_for_in_state.receiver) {
10485  if (current_for_in_state.receiver_needs_map_check) {
10486  auto* receiver_map =
10487  BuildLoadTaggedField(receiver, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
10488  AddNewNode<CheckDynamicValue>(
10489  {receiver_map, current_for_in_state.cache_type},
10490  DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMapDynamic);
10491  current_for_in_state.receiver_needs_map_check = false;
10492  }
10493  return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTrueValue);
10494  }
10495 
10496  // We can also optimize for this case below:
10497 
10498  // receiver(is a heap constant with fast map)
10499  // ^
10500  // | object(all keys are enumerable)
10501  // | ^
10502  // | |
10503  // | JSForInNext
10504  // | ^
10505  // +----+ |
10506  // | |
10507  // JSCall[hasOwnProperty]
10508 
10509  // We can replace the {JSCall} with several internalized string
10510  // comparisons.
10511 
10512  compiler::OptionalMapRef maybe_receiver_map;
10513  compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef receiver_ref = TryGetConstant(receiver);
10514  if (receiver_ref.has_value()) {
10515  compiler::HeapObjectRef receiver_object = receiver_ref.value();
10516  compiler::MapRef receiver_map = receiver_object.map(broker());
10517  maybe_receiver_map = receiver_map;
10518  } else {
10519  NodeInfo* known_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(receiver);
10520  if (known_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
10521  compiler::ZoneRefSet<Map> possible_maps = known_info->possible_maps();
10522  if (possible_maps.size() == 1) {
10523  compiler::MapRef receiver_map = *(possible_maps.begin());
10524  maybe_receiver_map = receiver_map;
10525  }
10526  }
10527  }
10528  if (!maybe_receiver_map.has_value()) return {};
10529 
10530  compiler::MapRef receiver_map = maybe_receiver_map.value();
10531  InstanceType instance_type = receiver_map.instance_type();
10532  int const nof = receiver_map.NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
10533  // We set a heuristic value to limit the compare instructions number.
10534  if (nof > 4 || IsSpecialReceiverInstanceType(instance_type) ||
10535  receiver_map.is_dictionary_map()) {
10536  return {};
10537  }
10538  RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckMaps(receiver, base::VectorOf({receiver_map})));
10539  // Replace builtin call with several internalized string comparisons.
10540  MaglevSubGraphBuilder sub_graph(this, 1);
10541  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable var_result(0);
10542  MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label done(
10543  &sub_graph, nof + 1,
10544  std::initializer_list<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable*>{&var_result});
10545  const compiler::DescriptorArrayRef descriptor_array =
10546  receiver_map.instance_descriptors(broker());
10547  for (InternalIndex key_index : InternalIndex::Range(nof)) {
10548  compiler::NameRef receiver_key =
10549  descriptor_array.GetPropertyKey(broker(), key_index);
10550  ValueNode* lhs = GetConstant(receiver_key);
10551  sub_graph.set(var_result, GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTrueValue));
10552  sub_graph.GotoIfTrue<BranchIfReferenceEqual>(&done, {lhs, args[0]});
10553  }
10554  sub_graph.set(var_result, GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kFalseValue));
10555  sub_graph.Goto(&done);
10556  sub_graph.Bind(&done);
10557  return sub_graph.get(var_result);
10558 }
10559 
10560 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceGetProto(ValueNode* object) {
10561  NodeInfo* info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(object);
10562  if (!info || !info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
10563  return {};
10564  }
10565  auto& possible_maps = info->possible_maps();
10566  if (possible_maps.is_empty()) {
10567  return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
10568  }
10569  auto it = possible_maps.begin();
10570  compiler::MapRef map = *it;
10571  if (IsSpecialReceiverInstanceType(map.instance_type())) {
10572  return {};
10573  }
10574  DCHECK(!map.IsPrimitiveMap() && map.IsJSReceiverMap());
10575  compiler::HeapObjectRef proto = map.prototype(broker());
10576  ++it;
10577  for (; it != possible_maps.end(); ++it) {
10578  map = *it;
10579  if (IsSpecialReceiverInstanceType(map.instance_type()) ||
10580  !proto.equals(map.prototype(broker()))) {
10581  return {};
10582  }
10583  DCHECK(!map.IsPrimitiveMap() && map.IsJSReceiverMap());
10584  }
10585  return GetConstant(proto);
10586 }
10587 
10588 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceObjectPrototypeGetProto(
10589  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
10590  if (args.count() != 0) return {};
10591  return TryReduceGetProto(args.receiver());
10592 }
10593 
10594 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceObjectGetPrototypeOf(
10595  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
10596  if (args.count() != 1) return {};
10597  return TryReduceGetProto(args[0]);
10598 }
10599

10609 
10610 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceNumberParseInt(
10611  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
10612  if (args.count() == 0) {
10613  return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kNanValue);
10614  }
10615  if (args.count() != 1) {
10616  if (RootConstant* root_cst = args[1]->TryCast<RootConstant>()) {
10617  if (root_cst->index() != RootIndex::kUndefinedValue) {
10618  return {};
10619  }
10620  } else if (SmiConstant* smi_cst = args[1]->TryCast<SmiConstant>()) {
10621  if (smi_cst->value().value() != 10 && smi_cst->value().value() != 0) {
10622  return {};
10623  }
10624  } else {
10625  return {};
10626  }
10627  }
10628 
10629  ValueNode* arg = args[0];
10630 
10631  switch (arg->value_representation()) {
10632  case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
10633  case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
10634  case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
10635  return arg;
10636  case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
10637  switch (CheckTypes(arg, {NodeType::kSmi})) {
10638  case NodeType::kSmi:
10639  return arg;
10640  default:
10641  // TODO(verwaest): Support actually parsing strings, converting
10642  // doubles to ints, ...
10643  return {};
10644  }
10645  case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
10646  case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
10647  return {};
10648  }
10649 }
10650 
10651 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceMathAbs(
10652  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
10653  if (args.count() == 0) {
10654  return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kNanValue);
10655  }
10656  ValueNode* arg = args[0];
10657 
10658  switch (arg->value_representation()) {
10659  case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
10660  case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
10661  // TODO(388844115): Rename IntPtr to make it clear it's non-negative.
10662  return arg;
10663  case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
10664  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
10665  return AddNewNode<Int32AbsWithOverflow>({arg});
10666  case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
10667  switch (CheckTypes(arg, {NodeType::kSmi, NodeType::kNumberOrOddball})) {
10668  case NodeType::kSmi:
10669  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
10670  return AddNewNode<Int32AbsWithOverflow>({arg});
10671  case NodeType::kNumberOrOddball:
10672  return AddNewNode<Float64Abs>({GetHoleyFloat64ForToNumber(
10673  arg, NodeType::kNumberOrOddball,
10674  TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball)});
10675  // TODO(verwaest): Add support for ToNumberOrNumeric and deopt.
10676  default:
10677  break;
10678  }
10679  break;
10680  case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
10681  case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
10682  return AddNewNode<Float64Abs>({arg});
10683  }
10684  return {};
10685 }

10696 
10697 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::DoTryReduceMathRound(
10698  CallArguments& args, Float64Round::Kind kind) {
10699  if (args.count() == 0) {
10700  return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kNanValue);
10701  }
10702  ValueNode* arg = args[0];
10703  auto arg_repr = arg->value_representation();
10704  if (arg_repr == ValueRepresentation::kInt32 ||
10705  arg_repr == ValueRepresentation::kUint32 ||
10706  arg_repr == ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr) {
10707  return arg;
10708  }
10709  if (CheckType(arg, NodeType::kSmi)) return arg;
10710  if (!IsSupported(CpuOperation::kFloat64Round)) {
10711  return {};
10712  }
10713  if (arg_repr == ValueRepresentation::kFloat64 ||
10714  arg_repr == ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) {
10715  return AddNewNode<Float64Round>({arg}, kind);
10716  }
10717  DCHECK_EQ(arg_repr, ValueRepresentation::kTagged);
10718  if (CheckType(arg, NodeType::kNumberOrOddball)) {
10719  return AddNewNode<Float64Round>(
10720  {GetHoleyFloat64ForToNumber(
10721  arg, NodeType::kNumberOrOddball,
10722  TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball)},
10723  kind);
10724  }
10725  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
10726  DeoptFrameScope continuation_scope(this, Float64Round::continuation(kind));
10727  ToNumberOrNumeric* conversion =
10728  AddNewNode<ToNumberOrNumeric>({arg}, Object::Conversion::kToNumber);
10729  ValueNode* float64_value = AddNewNode<UncheckedNumberOrOddballToFloat64>(
10730  {conversion}, TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber);
10731  return AddNewNode<Float64Round>({float64_value}, kind);
10732 }
10733 
10734 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceArrayConstructor(
10735  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
10736  return TryReduceConstructArrayConstructor(target, args);
10737 }
10738 
10739 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceMathClz32(
10740  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
10741  if (args.count() < 1) {
10742  return GetInt32Constant(32);
10743  }
10744 
10745  if (!IsSupported(CpuOperation::kMathClz32)) {
10746  return {};
10747  }
10748 
10749  ValueNode* arg = args[0];
10750  auto arg_repr = arg->value_representation();
10751  if (arg_repr == ValueRepresentation::kInt32 ||
10752  arg_repr == ValueRepresentation::kUint32 ||
10753  arg_repr == ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr) {
10754  return AddNewNode<Int32CountLeadingZeros>({arg});
10755  }
10756  if (arg_repr == ValueRepresentation::kFloat64 ||
10757  arg_repr == ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) {
10758  if (IsSupported(CpuOperation::kFloat64Round)) {
10759  return AddNewNode<Float64CountLeadingZeros>({arg});
10760  }
10761  return {};
10762  }
10763  DCHECK_EQ(arg_repr, ValueRepresentation::kTagged);
10764  if (CheckType(arg, NodeType::kSmi)) {
10765  return AddNewNode<SmiCountLeadingZeros>({arg});
10766  }
10767 
10768  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) {
10769  return {};
10770  }
10771  DeoptFrameScope continuation_scope(this,
10772  Float64CountLeadingZeros::continuation());
10773  ToNumberOrNumeric* conversion =
10774  AddNewNode<ToNumberOrNumeric>({arg}, Object::Conversion::kToNumber);
10775  ValueNode* float64_value = AddNewNode<UncheckedNumberOrOddballToFloat64>(
10776  {conversion}, TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber);
10777  return AddNewNode<Float64CountLeadingZeros>({float64_value});
10778 }

10780 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceStringConstructor(
10781  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
10782  if (args.count() == 0) {
10783  return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kempty_string);
10784  }
10785 
10786  return BuildToString(args[0], ToString::kConvertSymbol);
10787 }
10788 
10789 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceMathPow(
10790  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
10791  if (args.count() < 2) {
10792  // For < 2 args, we'll be calculating Math.Pow(arg[0], undefined), which is
10793  // ToNumber(arg[0]) ** NaN == NaN. So we can just return NaN.
10794  // However, if there is a single argument and it's tagged, we have to call
10795  // ToNumber on it before returning NaN, for side effects. This call could
10796  // lazy deopt, which would mean we'd need a continuation to actually set
10797  // the NaN return value... it's easier to just bail out, this should be
10798  // an uncommon case anyway.
10799  if (args.count() == 1 && args[0]->properties().is_tagged()) {
10800  return {};
10801  }
10802  return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kNanValue);
10803  }
10804  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
10805  // If both arguments are tagged, it is cheaper to call Math.Pow builtin,
10806  // instead of Float64Exponentiate, since we are still making a call and we
10807  // don't need to unbox both inputs. See https://crbug.com/1393643.
10808  if (args[0]->properties().is_tagged() && args[1]->properties().is_tagged()) {
10809  // The Math.pow call will be created in CallKnownJSFunction reduction.
10810  return {};
10811  }
10812  ValueNode* left = GetHoleyFloat64ForToNumber(
10813  args[0], NodeType::kNumber, TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber);
10814  ValueNode* right = GetHoleyFloat64ForToNumber(
10815  args[1], NodeType::kNumber, TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber);
10816  return AddNewNode<Float64Exponentiate>({left, right});
10817 }
10818 
10819 #define MATH_UNARY_IEEE_BUILTIN_REDUCER(MathName, ExtName, EnumName) \
10820  MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduce##MathName( \
10821  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) { \
10822  if (args.count() < 1) { \
10823  return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kNanValue); \
10824  } \
10825  if (!CanSpeculateCall()) { \
10826  ValueRepresentation rep = args[0]->properties().value_representation(); \
10827  if (rep == ValueRepresentation::kTagged || \
10828  rep == ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) { \
10829  return {}; \
10830  } \
10831  } \
10832  ValueNode* value = \
10833  GetFloat64ForToNumber(args[0], NodeType::kNumber, \
10834  TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber); \
10835  return AddNewNode<Float64Ieee754Unary>( \
10836  {value}, Float64Ieee754Unary::Ieee754Function::k##EnumName); \
10837  }
10838 
10839 IEEE_754_UNARY_LIST(MATH_UNARY_IEEE_BUILTIN_REDUCER)
10840 #undef MATH_UNARY_IEEE_BUILTIN_REDUCER
10841 
10842 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceBuiltin(
10843  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
10844  CallArguments& args, const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
10845  if (args.mode() != CallArguments::kDefault) {
10846  // TODO(victorgomes): Maybe inline the spread stub? Or call known function
10847  // directly if arguments list is an array.
10848  return {};
10849  }
10850  SaveCallSpeculationScope speculate(this, feedback_source);
10851  if (!shared.HasBuiltinId()) return {};
10852  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
10853  std::cout << " ! Trying to reduce builtin "
10854  << Builtins::name(shared.builtin_id()) << std::endl;
10855  }
10856  switch (shared.builtin_id()) {
10857 #define CASE(Name, ...) \
10858  case Builtin::k##Name: \
10859  return TryReduce##Name(target, args);
10860  MAGLEV_REDUCED_BUILTIN(CASE)
10861 #undef CASE
10862  default:
10863  // TODO(v8:7700): Inline more builtins.
10864  return {};
10865  }
10866 }
10867 
10868 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetConvertReceiver(
10869  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, const CallArguments& args) {
10870  if (shared.native() || shared.language_mode() == LanguageMode::kStrict) {
10871  if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
10872  return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
10873  } else {
10874  return args.receiver();
10875  }
10876  }
10877  if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
10878  return GetConstant(
10879  broker()->target_native_context().global_proxy_object(broker()));
10880  }
10881  ValueNode* receiver = args.receiver();
10882  if (CheckType(receiver, NodeType::kJSReceiver)) return receiver;
10883  if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant =
10884  TryGetConstant(receiver)) {
10885  compiler::HeapObjectRef constant = maybe_constant.value();
10886  if (constant.IsNullOrUndefined()) {
10887  return GetConstant(
10888  broker()->target_native_context().global_proxy_object(broker()));
10889  }
10890  }
10891  return AddNewNode<ConvertReceiver>(
10892  {receiver}, broker()->target_native_context(), args.receiver_mode());
10893 }
10894 
10895 base::Vector<ValueNode*> MaglevGraphBuilder::GetArgumentsAsArrayOfValueNodes(
10896  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, const CallArguments& args) {
10897  // TODO(victorgomes): Investigate if we can avoid this copy.
10898  int arg_count = static_cast<int>(args.count());
10899  auto arguments = zone()->AllocateVector<ValueNode*>(arg_count + 1);
10900  arguments[0] = GetConvertReceiver(shared, args);
10901  for (int i = 0; i < arg_count; i++) {
10902  arguments[i + 1] = args[i];
10903  }
10904  return arguments;
10905 }
10906 
10907 template <typename CallNode, typename... Args>
10908 CallNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::AddNewCallNode(const CallArguments& args,
10909  Args&&... extra_args) {
10910  size_t input_count = args.count_with_receiver() + CallNode::kFixedInputCount;
10911  return AddNewNode<CallNode>(
10912  input_count,
10913  [&](CallNode* call) {
10914  int arg_index = 0;
10915  call->set_arg(arg_index++,
10916  GetTaggedValue(GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver())));
10917  for (size_t i = 0; i < args.count(); ++i) {
10918  call->set_arg(arg_index++, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
10919  }
10920  },
10921  std::forward<Args>(extra_args)...);
10922 }
10923 
10924 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildGenericCall(ValueNode* target,
10925  Call::TargetType target_type,
10926  const CallArguments& args) {
10927  // TODO(victorgomes): We do not collect call feedback from optimized/inlined
10928  // calls. In order to be consistent, we don't pass the feedback_source to the
10929  // IR, so that we avoid collecting for generic calls as well. We might want to
10930  // revisit this in the future.
10931  switch (args.mode()) {
10932  case CallArguments::kDefault:
10933  return AddNewCallNode<Call>(args, args.receiver_mode(), target_type,
10934  GetTaggedValue(target),
10935  GetTaggedValue(GetContext()));
10936  case CallArguments::kWithSpread:
10937  DCHECK_EQ(args.receiver_mode(), ConvertReceiverMode::kAny);
10938  return AddNewCallNode<CallWithSpread>(args, GetTaggedValue(target),
10939  GetTaggedValue(GetContext()));
10940  case CallArguments::kWithArrayLike:
10941  DCHECK_EQ(args.receiver_mode(), ConvertReceiverMode::kAny);
10942  // We don't use AddNewCallNode here, because the number of required
10943  // arguments is known statically.
10944  return AddNewNode<CallWithArrayLike>(
10945  {target, GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver()), args[0],
10946  GetContext()});
10947  }
10948 }
10949 
10950 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCallSelf(
10951  ValueNode* context, ValueNode* function, ValueNode* new_target,
10952  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, CallArguments& args) {
10953  ValueNode* receiver = GetConvertReceiver(shared, args);
10954  size_t input_count = args.count() + CallSelf::kFixedInputCount;
10955  graph()->set_has_recursive_calls(true);
10956  DCHECK_EQ(
10957  compilation_unit_->info()->toplevel_compilation_unit()->parameter_count(),
10958  shared.internal_formal_parameter_count_with_receiver_deprecated());
10959  return AddNewNode<CallSelf>(
10960  input_count,
10961  [&](CallSelf* call) {
10962  for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(args.count()); i++) {
10963  call->set_arg(i, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
10964  }
10965  },
10966  compilation_unit_->info()->toplevel_compilation_unit()->parameter_count(),
10967  GetTaggedValue(function), GetTaggedValue(context),
10968  GetTaggedValue(receiver), GetTaggedValue(new_target));
10969 }

10971 bool MaglevGraphBuilder::TargetIsCurrentCompilingUnit(
10972  compiler::JSFunctionRef target) {
10973  if (compilation_unit_->info()->specialize_to_function_context()) {
10974  return target.object().equals(
10975  compilation_unit_->info()->toplevel_function());
10976  }
10977  return target.object()->shared() ==
10978  compilation_unit_->info()->toplevel_function()->shared();
10979 }
10980 
10981 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceCallForApiFunction(
10982  compiler::FunctionTemplateInfoRef api_callback,
10983  compiler::OptionalSharedFunctionInfoRef maybe_shared, CallArguments& args) {
10984  if (args.mode() != CallArguments::kDefault) {
10985  // TODO(victorgomes): Maybe inline the spread stub? Or call known function
10986  // directly if arguments list is an array.
10987  return {};
10988  }
10989  // Check if the function has an associated C++ code to execute.
10990  compiler::OptionalObjectRef maybe_callback_data =
10991  api_callback.callback_data(broker());
10992  if (!maybe_callback_data.has_value()) {
10993  // TODO(ishell): consider generating "return undefined" for empty function
10994  // instead of failing.
10995  return {};
10996  }
10997 
10998  size_t input_count = args.count() + CallKnownApiFunction::kFixedInputCount;
10999  ValueNode* receiver;
11000  if (maybe_shared.has_value()) {
11001  receiver = GetConvertReceiver(maybe_shared.value(), args);
11002  } else {
11003  receiver = args.receiver();
11004  CHECK_NOT_NULL(receiver);
11005  }
11006 
11007  CallKnownApiFunction::Mode mode =
11008  broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoProfilingProtector()
11009  ? (v8_flags.maglev_inline_api_calls
11010  ? CallKnownApiFunction::kNoProfilingInlined
11011  : CallKnownApiFunction::kNoProfiling)
11012  : CallKnownApiFunction::kGeneric;
11013 
11014  return AddNewNode<CallKnownApiFunction>(
11015  input_count,
11016  [&](CallKnownApiFunction* call) {
11017  for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(args.count()); i++) {
11018  call->set_arg(i, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
11019  }
11020  },
11021  mode, api_callback, GetTaggedValue(GetContext()),
11022  GetTaggedValue(receiver));
11023 }
11024 
11025 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildCallKnownApiFunction(
11026  compiler::JSFunctionRef function, compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
11027  CallArguments& args) {
11028  compiler::OptionalFunctionTemplateInfoRef maybe_function_template_info =
11029  shared.function_template_info(broker());
11030  if (!maybe_function_template_info.has_value()) {
11031  // Not an Api function.
11032  return {};
11033  }
11034 
11035  // See if we can optimize this API call.
11036  compiler::FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info =
11037  maybe_function_template_info.value();
11038 
11039  compiler::HolderLookupResult api_holder;
11040  if (function_template_info.accept_any_receiver() &&
11041  function_template_info.is_signature_undefined(broker())) {
11042  // We might be able to optimize the API call depending on the
11043  // {function_template_info}.
11044  // If the API function accepts any kind of {receiver}, we only need to
11045  // ensure that the {receiver} is actually a JSReceiver at this point,
11046  // and also pass that as the {holder}. There are two independent bits
11047  // here:
11048  //
11049  // a. When the "accept any receiver" bit is set, it means we don't
11050  // need to perform access checks, even if the {receiver}'s map
11051  // has the "needs access check" bit set.
11052  // b. When the {function_template_info} has no signature, we don't
11053  // need to do the compatible receiver check, since all receivers
11054  // are considered compatible at that point, and the {receiver}
11055  // will be pass as the {holder}.
11056 
11057  api_holder =
11058  compiler::HolderLookupResult{CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver};
11059  } else {
11060  // Try to infer API holder from the known aspects of the {receiver}.
11061  api_holder =
11062  TryInferApiHolderValue(function_template_info, args.receiver());
11063  }
11064 
11065  switch (api_holder.lookup) {
11066  case CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver:
11067  case CallOptimization::kHolderFound:
11068  return TryReduceCallForApiFunction(function_template_info, shared, args);
11069 
11070  case CallOptimization::kHolderNotFound:
11071  break;
11072  }
11073 
11074  // We don't have enough information to eliminate the access check
11075  // and/or the compatible receiver check, so use the generic builtin
11076  // that does those checks dynamically. This is still significantly
11077  // faster than the generic call sequence.
11078  Builtin builtin_name;
11079  // TODO(ishell): create no-profiling versions of kCallFunctionTemplate
11080  // builtins and use them here based on DependOnNoProfilingProtector()
11081  // dependency state.
11082  if (function_template_info.accept_any_receiver()) {
11083  DCHECK(!function_template_info.is_signature_undefined(broker()));
11084  builtin_name = Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckCompatibleReceiver;
11085  } else if (function_template_info.is_signature_undefined(broker())) {
11086  builtin_name = Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckAccess;
11087  } else {
11088  builtin_name =
11089  Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckAccessAndCompatibleReceiver;
11090  }
11091 
11092  // The CallFunctionTemplate builtin requires the {receiver} to be
11093  // an actual JSReceiver, so make sure we do the proper conversion
11094  // first if necessary.
11095  ValueNode* receiver = GetConvertReceiver(shared, args);
11096  int kContext = 1;
11097  int kFunctionTemplateInfo = 1;
11098  int kArgc = 1;
11099  return AddNewNode<CallBuiltin>(
11100  kFunctionTemplateInfo + kArgc + kContext + args.count_with_receiver(),
11101  [&](CallBuiltin* call_builtin) {
11102  int arg_index = 0;
11103  call_builtin->set_arg(arg_index++, GetConstant(function_template_info));
11104  call_builtin->set_arg(
11105  arg_index++,
11106  GetInt32Constant(JSParameterCount(static_cast<int>(args.count()))));
11107 
11108  call_builtin->set_arg(arg_index++, GetTaggedValue(receiver));
11109  for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(args.count()); i++) {
11110  call_builtin->set_arg(arg_index++, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
11111  }
11112  },
11113  builtin_name, GetTaggedValue(GetContext()));
11114 }
11115 
11116 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildCallKnownJSFunction(
11117  compiler::JSFunctionRef function, ValueNode* new_target,
11118  CallArguments& args, const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
11119  // Don't inline CallFunction stub across native contexts.
11120  if (function.native_context(broker()) != broker()->target_native_context()) {
11121  return {};
11122  }
11123  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared = function.shared(broker());
11124  RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildCallKnownApiFunction(function, shared, args));
11125 
11126  ValueNode* closure = GetConstant(function);
11127  compiler::ContextRef context = function.context(broker());
11128  ValueNode* context_node = GetConstant(context);
11129  MaybeReduceResult res;
11130  if (MaglevIsTopTier() && TargetIsCurrentCompilingUnit(function) &&
11131  !graph_->is_osr()) {
11132  DCHECK(!shared.HasBuiltinId());
11133  res = BuildCallSelf(context_node, closure, new_target, shared, args);
11134  } else {
11135  res = TryBuildCallKnownJSFunction(
11136  context_node, closure, new_target,
11137 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
11138  function.dispatch_handle(),
11139 #endif
11140  shared, function.raw_feedback_cell(broker()), args, feedback_source);
11141  }
11142  return res;
11143 }
11144 
11145 CallKnownJSFunction* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCallKnownJSFunction(
11146  ValueNode* context, ValueNode* function, ValueNode* new_target,
11147 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
11148  JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle,
11149 #endif
11150  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
11151  compiler::FeedbackCellRef feedback_cell, CallArguments& args,
11152  const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
11153  ValueNode* receiver = GetConvertReceiver(shared, args);
11154  size_t input_count = args.count() + CallKnownJSFunction::kFixedInputCount;
11155  return AddNewNode<CallKnownJSFunction>(
11156  input_count,
11157  [&](CallKnownJSFunction* call) {
11158  for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(args.count()); i++) {
11159  call->set_arg(i, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
11160  }
11161  },
11162 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
11163  dispatch_handle,
11164 #endif
11165  shared, GetTaggedValue(function), GetTaggedValue(context),
11166  GetTaggedValue(receiver), GetTaggedValue(new_target));
11167 }
11168 
11169 CallKnownJSFunction* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCallKnownJSFunction(
11170  ValueNode* context, ValueNode* function, ValueNode* new_target,
11171 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
11172  JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle,
11173 #endif
11174  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
11175  base::Vector<ValueNode*> arguments) {
11176  DCHECK_GT(arguments.size(), 0);
11177  constexpr int kSkipReceiver = 1;
11178  int argcount_without_receiver =
11179  static_cast<int>(arguments.size()) - kSkipReceiver;
11180  size_t input_count =
11181  argcount_without_receiver + CallKnownJSFunction::kFixedInputCount;
11182  return AddNewNode<CallKnownJSFunction>(
11183  input_count,
11184  [&](CallKnownJSFunction* call) {
11185  for (int i = 0; i < argcount_without_receiver; i++) {
11186  call->set_arg(i, GetTaggedValue(arguments[i + kSkipReceiver]));
11187  }
11188  },
11189 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
11190  dispatch_handle,
11191 #endif
11192  shared, GetTaggedValue(function), GetTaggedValue(context),
11193  GetTaggedValue(arguments[0]), GetTaggedValue(new_target));
11194 }
11195 
11196 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildCallKnownJSFunction(
11197  ValueNode* context, ValueNode* function, ValueNode* new_target,
11198 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
11199  JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle,
11200 #endif
11201  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
11202  compiler::FeedbackCellRef feedback_cell, CallArguments& args,
11203  const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
11204  if (v8_flags.maglev_inlining) {
11205  RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildInlineCall(context, function, new_target,
11206 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
11207  dispatch_handle,
11208 #endif
11209  shared, feedback_cell, args,
11210  feedback_source));
11211  }
11212  return BuildCallKnownJSFunction(context, function, new_target,
11213 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
11214  dispatch_handle,
11215 #endif
11216  shared, feedback_cell, args, feedback_source);
11217 }
11218 
11219 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckValueByReference(
11220  ValueNode* node, compiler::HeapObjectRef ref, DeoptimizeReason reason) {
11221  DCHECK(!ref.IsSmi());
11222  DCHECK(!ref.IsHeapNumber());
11223 
11224  if (!IsInstanceOfNodeType(ref.map(broker()), GetType(node), broker())) {
11225  return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(reason);
11226  }
11227  if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant = TryGetConstant(node)) {
11228  if (maybe_constant.value().equals(ref)) {
11229  return ReduceResult::Done();
11230  }
11231  return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(reason);
11232  }
11233  AddNewNode<CheckValue>({node}, ref, reason);
11234  SetKnownValue(node, ref, StaticTypeForConstant(broker(), ref));
11235 
11236  return ReduceResult::Done();
11237 }
11238 
11239 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckNumericalValueOrByReference(
11240  ValueNode* node, compiler::ObjectRef ref, DeoptimizeReason reason) {
11241  if (ref.IsHeapObject() && !ref.IsHeapNumber()) {
11242  return BuildCheckValueByReference(node, ref.AsHeapObject(), reason);
11243  }
11244  return BuildCheckNumericalValue(node, ref, reason);
11245 }
11246 
11247 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckInternalizedStringValueOrByReference(
11248  ValueNode* node, compiler::HeapObjectRef ref, DeoptimizeReason reason) {
11249  if (!IsConstantNode(node->opcode()) && ref.IsInternalizedString()) {
11250  if (!IsInstanceOfNodeType(ref.map(broker()), GetType(node), broker())) {
11251  return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(reason);
11252  }
11253  AddNewNode<CheckValueEqualsString>({node}, ref.AsInternalizedString(),
11254  reason);
11255  SetKnownValue(node, ref, NodeType::kString);
11256  return ReduceResult::Done();
11257  }
11258  return BuildCheckValueByReference(node, ref, reason);
11259 }
11260 
11261 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckNumericalValue(
11262  ValueNode* node, compiler::ObjectRef ref, DeoptimizeReason reason) {
11263  DCHECK(ref.IsSmi() || ref.IsHeapNumber());
11264  if (ref.IsSmi()) {
11265  int ref_value = ref.AsSmi();
11266  if (IsConstantNode(node->opcode())) {
11267  if (node->Is<SmiConstant>() &&
11268  node->Cast<SmiConstant>()->value().value() == ref_value) {
11269  return ReduceResult::Done();
11270  }
11271  if (node->Is<Int32Constant>() &&
11272  node->Cast<Int32Constant>()->value() == ref_value) {
11273  return ReduceResult::Done();
11274  }
11275  return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(reason);
11276  }
11277  if (NodeTypeIs(GetType(node), NodeType::kAnyHeapObject)) {
11278  return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(reason);
11279  }
11280  AddNewNode<CheckValueEqualsInt32>({node}, ref_value, reason);
11281  } else {
11282  DCHECK(ref.IsHeapNumber());
11283  Float64 ref_value = Float64::FromBits(ref.AsHeapNumber().value_as_bits());
11284  DCHECK(!ref_value.is_hole_nan());
11285  if (node->Is<Float64Constant>()) {
11286  Float64 f64 = node->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value();
11287  DCHECK(!f64.is_hole_nan());
11288  if (f64 == ref_value) {
11289  return ReduceResult::Done();
11290  }
11291  return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(reason);
11292  } else if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef constant =
11293  TryGetConstant(node)) {
11294  if (constant.value().IsHeapNumber()) {
11295  Float64 f64 =
11296  Float64::FromBits(constant.value().AsHeapNumber().value_as_bits());
11297  DCHECK(!f64.is_hole_nan());
11298  if (f64 == ref_value) {
11299  return ReduceResult::Done();
11300  }
11301  }
11302  return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(reason);
11303  }
11304  if (!NodeTypeIs(NodeType::kNumber, GetType(node))) {
11305  return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(reason);
11306  }
11307  AddNewNode<CheckFloat64SameValue>({node}, ref_value, reason);
11308  }
11309 
11310  SetKnownValue(node, ref, NodeType::kNumber);
11311  return ReduceResult::Done();
11312 }
11313 
11314 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildConvertHoleToUndefined(ValueNode* node) {
11315  if (!node->is_tagged()) return node;
11316  compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant = TryGetConstant(node);
11317  if (maybe_constant) {
11318  return maybe_constant.value().IsTheHole()
11319  ? GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue)
11320  : node;
11321  }
11322  return AddNewNode<ConvertHoleToUndefined>({node});
11323 }
11324 
11325 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckNotHole(ValueNode* node) {
11326  if (!node->is_tagged()) return ReduceResult::Done();
11327  compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant = TryGetConstant(node);
11328  if (maybe_constant) {
11329  if (maybe_constant.value().IsTheHole()) {
11330  return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kHole);
11331  }
11332  return ReduceResult::Done();
11333  }
11334  AddNewNode<CheckNotHole>({node});
11335  return ReduceResult::Done();
11336 }

11338 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceCallForConstant(
11339  compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args,
11340  const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
11341  if (args.mode() != CallArguments::kDefault) {
11342  // TODO(victorgomes): Maybe inline the spread stub? Or call known function
11343  // directly if arguments list is an array.
11344  return {};
11345  }
11346  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared = target.shared(broker());
11347  ValueNode* target_node = GetConstant(target);
11348  // Do not reduce calls to functions with break points.
11349  if (!shared.HasBreakInfo(broker())) {
11350  if (IsClassConstructor(shared.kind())) {
11351  // If we have a class constructor, we should raise an exception.
11352  return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstructorNonCallableError,
11353  {target_node});
11354  }
11355  DCHECK(IsCallable(*target.object()));
11356  RETURN_IF_DONE(TryReduceBuiltin(target, shared, args, feedback_source));
11357  RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildCallKnownJSFunction(
11358  target, GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue), args,
11359  feedback_source));
11360  }
11361  return BuildGenericCall(target_node, Call::TargetType::kJSFunction, args);
11362 }
11363 
11364 compiler::HolderLookupResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryInferApiHolderValue(
11365  compiler::FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info,
11366  ValueNode* receiver) {
11367  const compiler::HolderLookupResult not_found;
11368 
11369  auto receiver_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(receiver);
11370  if (!receiver_info || !receiver_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
11371  // No info about receiver, can't infer API holder.
11372  return not_found;
11373  }
11374  DCHECK(!receiver_info->possible_maps().is_empty());
11375  compiler::MapRef first_receiver_map = receiver_info->possible_maps()[0];
11376 
11377  // See if we can constant-fold the compatible receiver checks.
11378  compiler::HolderLookupResult api_holder =
11379  function_template_info.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(broker(),
11380  first_receiver_map);
11381  if (api_holder.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderNotFound) {
11382  // Can't infer API holder.
11383  return not_found;
11384  }
11385 
11386  // Check that all {receiver_maps} are actually JSReceiver maps and
11387  // that the {function_template_info} accepts them without access
11388  // checks (even if "access check needed" is set for {receiver}).
11389  //
11390  // API holder might be a receivers's hidden prototype (i.e. the receiver is
11391  // a global proxy), so in this case the map check or stability dependency on
11392  // the receiver guard us from detaching a global object from global proxy.
11393  CHECK(first_receiver_map.IsJSReceiverMap());
11394  CHECK(!first_receiver_map.is_access_check_needed() ||
11395  function_template_info.accept_any_receiver());
11396 
11397  for (compiler::MapRef receiver_map : receiver_info->possible_maps()) {
11398  compiler::HolderLookupResult holder_i =
11399  function_template_info.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(broker(),
11400  receiver_map);
11401 
11402  if (api_holder.lookup != holder_i.lookup) {
11403  // Different API holders, dynamic lookup is required.
11404  return not_found;
11405  }
11406  DCHECK(holder_i.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderFound ||
11407  holder_i.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver);
11408  if (holder_i.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderFound) {
11409  DCHECK(api_holder.holder.has_value() && holder_i.holder.has_value());
11410  if (!api_holder.holder->equals(*holder_i.holder)) {
11411  // Different API holders, dynamic lookup is required.
11412  return not_found;
11413  }
11414  }
11415 
11416  CHECK(receiver_map.IsJSReceiverMap());
11417  CHECK(!receiver_map.is_access_check_needed() ||
11418  function_template_info.accept_any_receiver());
11419  }
11420  return api_holder;
11421 }

11423 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceCallForTarget(
11424  ValueNode* target_node, compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args,
11425  const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
11426  RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckValueByReference(
11427  target_node, target, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget));
11428  return TryReduceCallForConstant(target, args, feedback_source);
11429 }

11431 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceCallForNewClosure(
11432  ValueNode* target_node, ValueNode* target_context,
11433 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
11434  JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle,
11435 #endif
11436  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
11437  compiler::FeedbackCellRef feedback_cell, CallArguments& args,
11438  const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
11439  // Do not reduce calls to functions with break points.
11440  if (args.mode() != CallArguments::kDefault) {
11441  // TODO(victorgomes): Maybe inline the spread stub? Or call known function
11442  // directly if arguments list is an array.
11443  return {};
11444  }
11445  if (!shared.HasBreakInfo(broker())) {
11446  if (IsClassConstructor(shared.kind())) {
11447  // If we have a class constructor, we should raise an exception.
11448  return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstructorNonCallableError,
11449  {target_node});
11450  }
11451  RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildCallKnownJSFunction(
11452  target_context, target_node,
11453  GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue),
11454 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
11455  dispatch_handle,
11456 #endif
11457  shared, feedback_cell, args, feedback_source));
11458  }
11459  return BuildGenericCall(target_node, Call::TargetType::kJSFunction, args);
11460 }
11461 
11462 MaybeReduceResult
11463 MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceFunctionPrototypeApplyCallWithReceiver(
11464  compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_receiver, CallArguments& args,
11465  const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
11466  if (args.mode() != CallArguments::kDefault) return {};
11467 
11468  ValueNode* function = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
11469  if (maybe_receiver.has_value()) {
11470  RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckValueByReference(
11471  function, maybe_receiver.value(), DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget));
11472  function = GetConstant(maybe_receiver.value());
11473  }
11474 
11475  SaveCallSpeculationScope saved(this);
11476  if (args.count() == 0) {
11477  CallArguments empty_args(ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
11478  return ReduceCall(function, empty_args, feedback_source);
11479  }
11480  auto build_call_only_with_new_receiver = [&] {
11481  CallArguments new_args(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny, {args[0]});
11482  return ReduceCall(function, new_args, feedback_source);
11483  };
11484  if (args.count() == 1 || IsNullValue(args[1]) || IsUndefinedValue(args[1])) {
11485  return build_call_only_with_new_receiver();
11486  }
11487  auto build_call_with_array_like = [&] {
11488  CallArguments new_args(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny, {args[0], args[1]},
11489  CallArguments::kWithArrayLike);
11490  return ReduceCallWithArrayLike(function, new_args, feedback_source);
11491  };
11492  if (!known_node_aspects().MayBeNullOrUndefined(broker(), args[1])) {
11493  return build_call_with_array_like();
11494  }
11495  return SelectReduction(
11496  [&](auto& builder) {
11497  return BuildBranchIfUndefinedOrNull(builder, args[1]);
11498  },
11499  build_call_only_with_new_receiver, build_call_with_array_like);
11500 }
11501 
11502 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCallWithFeedback(
11503  ValueNode* target_node, CallArguments& args,
11504  const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
11505  const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& processed_feedback =
11506  broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(feedback_source);
11507  if (processed_feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
11508  return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
11509  DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForCall);
11510  }
11511 
11512  DCHECK_EQ(processed_feedback.kind(), compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kCall);
11513  const compiler::CallFeedback& call_feedback = processed_feedback.AsCall();
11514 
11515  if (call_feedback.target().has_value()) {
11516  if (call_feedback.target()->IsJSFunction()) {
11517  CallFeedbackContent content = call_feedback.call_feedback_content();
11518  compiler::JSFunctionRef feedback_target =
11519  call_feedback.target()->AsJSFunction();
11520  if (content == CallFeedbackContent::kReceiver) {
11521  compiler::NativeContextRef native_context =
11522  broker()->target_native_context();
11523  compiler::JSFunctionRef apply_function =
11524  native_context.function_prototype_apply(broker());
11525  RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckValueByReference(
11526  target_node, apply_function, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget));
11527  PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
11528  TryReduceFunctionPrototypeApplyCallWithReceiver(
11529  feedback_target, args, feedback_source),
11530  SetAccumulator);
11531  feedback_target = apply_function;
11532  } else {
11533  DCHECK_EQ(CallFeedbackContent::kTarget, content);
11534  }
11535  RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckValueByReference(
11536  target_node, feedback_target, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget));
11537  } else if (call_feedback.target()->IsFeedbackCell() &&
11538  args.mode() == CallArguments::kDefault) {
11539  compiler::FeedbackCellRef feedback_cell =
11540  call_feedback.target()->AsFeedbackCell();
11541  compiler::OptionalSharedFunctionInfoRef shared =
11542  feedback_cell.shared_function_info(broker());
11543  if (shared.has_value() && !shared->HasBreakInfo(broker())) {
11544  RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckJSFunction(target_node));
11545  ValueNode* target_feedback_cell =
11546  BuildLoadJSFunctionFeedbackCell(target_node);
11547  RETURN_IF_ABORT(
11548  BuildCheckValueByReference(target_feedback_cell, feedback_cell,
11549  DeoptimizeReason::kWrongFeedbackCell));
11550  if (IsClassConstructor(shared->kind())) {
11551  // If we have a class constructor, we should raise an exception.
11552  return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstructorNonCallableError,
11553  {target_node});
11554  }
11555  ValueNode* context = BuildLoadJSFunctionContext(target_node);
11556  compiler::ScopeInfoRef scope_info = shared->scope_info(broker());
11557  if (scope_info.HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
11558  scope_info = scope_info.OuterScopeInfo(broker());
11559  CHECK(scope_info.HasContext());
11560  graph()->record_scope_info(context, scope_info);
11561  }
11562  PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
11563  TryBuildCallKnownJSFunction(
11564  context, target_node,
11565  GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue),
11566 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
11567  feedback_cell.dispatch_handle(),
11568 #endif
11569  shared.value(), feedback_cell, args, feedback_source),
11570  SetAccumulator);
11571  UNREACHABLE();
11572  }
11573  }
11574  }
11575  PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(ReduceCall(target_node, args, feedback_source),
11576  SetAccumulator);
11577  UNREACHABLE();
11578 }
11579 
11580 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::ReduceCallWithArrayLikeForArgumentsObject(
11581  ValueNode* target_node, CallArguments& args,
11582  VirtualObject* arguments_object,
11583  const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
11584  DCHECK_EQ(args.mode(), CallArguments::kWithArrayLike);
11585  DCHECK(arguments_object->map().IsJSArgumentsObjectMap() ||
11586  arguments_object->map().IsJSArrayMap());
11587  args.PopArrayLikeArgument();
11588  ValueNode* elements_value =
11589  arguments_object->get(JSArgumentsObject::kElementsOffset);
11590  if (elements_value->Is<ArgumentsElements>()) {
11591  Call::TargetType target_type = Call::TargetType::kAny;
11592  // TODO(victorgomes): Add JSFunction node type in KNA and use the info here.
11593  if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant =
11594  TryGetConstant(target_node)) {
11595  if (maybe_constant->IsJSFunction()) {
11596  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared =
11597  maybe_constant->AsJSFunction().shared(broker());
11598  if (!IsClassConstructor(shared.kind())) {
11599  target_type = Call::TargetType::kJSFunction;
11600  }
11601  }
11602  }
11603  int start_index = 0;
11604  if (elements_value->Cast<ArgumentsElements>()->type() ==
11605  CreateArgumentsType::kRestParameter) {
11606  start_index =
11607  elements_value->Cast<ArgumentsElements>()->formal_parameter_count();
11608  }
11609  return AddNewCallNode<CallForwardVarargs>(args, GetTaggedValue(target_node),
11610  GetTaggedValue(GetContext()),
11611  start_index, target_type);
11612  }
11613 
11614  if (elements_value->Is<RootConstant>()) {
11615  // It is a RootConstant, Elements can only be the empty fixed array.
11616  DCHECK_EQ(elements_value->Cast<RootConstant>()->index(),
11617  RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray);
11618  CallArguments new_args(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny, {args.receiver()});
11619  return ReduceCall(target_node, new_args, feedback_source);
11620  }
11621 
11622  if (Constant* constant_value = elements_value->TryCast<Constant>()) {
11623  DCHECK(constant_value->object().IsFixedArray());
11624  compiler::FixedArrayRef elements = constant_value->object().AsFixedArray();
11625  base::SmallVector<ValueNode*, 8> arg_list;
11626  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(args.receiver());
11627  arg_list.push_back(args.receiver());
11628  for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(args.count()); i++) {
11629  arg_list.push_back(args[i]);
11630  }
11631  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < elements.length(); i++) {
11632  arg_list.push_back(GetConstant(*elements.TryGet(broker(), i)));
11633  }
11634  CallArguments new_args(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny, std::move(arg_list));
11635  return ReduceCall(target_node, new_args, feedback_source);
11636  }
11637 
11638  DCHECK(elements_value->Is<InlinedAllocation>());
11639  InlinedAllocation* allocation = elements_value->Cast<InlinedAllocation>();
11640  VirtualObject* elements = allocation->object();
11641 
11642  base::SmallVector<ValueNode*, 8> arg_list;
11643  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(args.receiver());
11644  arg_list.push_back(args.receiver());
11645  for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(args.count()); i++) {
11646  arg_list.push_back(args[i]);
11647  }
11648  DCHECK(elements->get(offsetof(FixedArray, length_))->Is<Int32Constant>());
11649  int length = elements->get(offsetof(FixedArray, length_))
11650  ->Cast<Int32Constant>()
11651  ->value();
11652  for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
11653  arg_list.push_back(elements->get(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i)));
11654  }
11655  CallArguments new_args(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny, std::move(arg_list));
11656  return ReduceCall(target_node, new_args, feedback_source);
11657 }

11659 namespace {
11660 bool IsSloppyMappedArgumentsObject(compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker,
11661  compiler::MapRef map) {
11662  return broker->target_native_context()
11663  .fast_aliased_arguments_map(broker)
11664  .equals(map);
11665 }
11666 } // namespace
11667 
11668 std::optional<VirtualObject*>
11669 MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetNonEscapingArgumentsObject(ValueNode* value) {
11670  if (!value->Is<InlinedAllocation>()) return {};
11671  InlinedAllocation* alloc = value->Cast<InlinedAllocation>();
11672  // Although the arguments object has not been changed so far, since it is not
11673  // escaping, it could be modified after this bytecode if it is inside a loop.
11674  if (IsInsideLoop()) {
11675  if (!is_loop_effect_tracking() ||
11676  !loop_effects_->allocations.contains(alloc)) {
11677  return {};
11678  }
11679  }
11680  // TODO(victorgomes): We can probably loosen the IsNotEscaping requirement if
11681  // we keep track of the arguments object changes so far.
11682  if (alloc->IsEscaping()) return {};
11683  VirtualObject* object = alloc->object();
11684  if (!object->has_static_map()) return {};
11685  // TODO(victorgomes): Support simple JSArray forwarding.
11686  compiler::MapRef map = object->map();
11687  // It is a rest parameter, if it is an array with ArgumentsElements node as
11688  // the elements array.
11689  if (map.IsJSArrayMap() && object->get(JSArgumentsObject::kElementsOffset)
11690  ->Is<ArgumentsElements>()) {
11691  return object;
11692  }
11693  // TODO(victorgomes): We can loosen the IsSloppyMappedArgumentsObject
11694  // requirement if there is no stores to the mapped arguments.
11695  if (map.IsJSArgumentsObjectMap() &&
11696  !IsSloppyMappedArgumentsObject(broker(), map)) {
11697  return object;
11698  }
11699  return {};
11700 }
11701 
11702 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::ReduceCallWithArrayLike(
11703  ValueNode* target_node, CallArguments& args,
11704  const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
11705  DCHECK_EQ(args.mode(), CallArguments::kWithArrayLike);
11706 
11707  // TODO(victorgomes): Add the case for JSArrays and Rest parameter.
11708  if (std::optional<VirtualObject*> arguments_object =
11709  TryGetNonEscapingArgumentsObject(args.array_like_argument())) {
11710  RETURN_IF_DONE(ReduceCallWithArrayLikeForArgumentsObject(
11711  target_node, args, *arguments_object, feedback_source));
11712  }
11713 
11714  // On fallthrough, create a generic call.
11715  return BuildGenericCall(target_node, Call::TargetType::kAny, args);
11716 }
11717 
11718 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::ReduceCall(
11719  ValueNode* target_node, CallArguments& args,
11720  const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
11721  if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant =
11722  TryGetConstant(target_node)) {
11723  if (maybe_constant->IsJSFunction()) {
11724  MaybeReduceResult result = TryReduceCallForTarget(
11725  target_node, maybe_constant->AsJSFunction(), args, feedback_source);
11726  RETURN_IF_DONE(result);
11727  }
11728  }
11729 
11730  // If the implementation here becomes more complex, we could probably
11731  // deduplicate the code for FastCreateClosure and CreateClosure by using
11732  // templates or giving them a shared base class.
11733  if (FastCreateClosure* fast_create_closure =
11734  target_node->TryCast<FastCreateClosure>()) {
11735  MaybeReduceResult result = TryReduceCallForNewClosure(
11736  fast_create_closure, fast_create_closure->context().node(),
11737 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
11738  fast_create_closure->feedback_cell().dispatch_handle(),
11739 #endif
11740  fast_create_closure->shared_function_info(),
11741  fast_create_closure->feedback_cell(), args, feedback_source);
11742  RETURN_IF_DONE(result);
11743  } else if (CreateClosure* create_closure =
11744  target_node->TryCast<CreateClosure>()) {
11745  MaybeReduceResult result = TryReduceCallForNewClosure(
11746  create_closure, create_closure->context().node(),
11747 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
11748  create_closure->feedback_cell().dispatch_handle(),
11749 #endif
11750  create_closure->shared_function_info(), create_closure->feedback_cell(),
11751  args, feedback_source);
11752  RETURN_IF_DONE(result);
11753  }
11754 
11755  // On fallthrough, create a generic call.
11756  return BuildGenericCall(target_node, Call::TargetType::kAny, args);
11757 }
11758 
11759 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCallFromRegisterList(
11760  ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode) {
11761  ValueNode* target = LoadRegister(0);
11762  interpreter::RegisterList reg_list = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
11763  FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(3);
11764  compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source(feedback(), slot);
11765  CallArguments args(receiver_mode, reg_list, current_interpreter_frame_);
11766  return BuildCallWithFeedback(target, args, feedback_source);
11767 }
11768 
11769 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCallFromRegisters(
11770  int arg_count, ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode) {
11771  ValueNode* target = LoadRegister(0);
11772  const int receiver_count =
11773  (receiver_mode == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) ? 0 : 1;
11774  const int reg_count = arg_count + receiver_count;
11775  FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(reg_count + 1);
11776  compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source(feedback(), slot);
11777  switch (reg_count) {
11778  case 0: {
11779  DCHECK_EQ(receiver_mode, ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
11780  CallArguments args(receiver_mode);
11781  return BuildCallWithFeedback(target, args, feedback_source);
11782  }
11783  case 1: {
11784  CallArguments args(receiver_mode, {LoadRegister(1)});
11785  return BuildCallWithFeedback(target, args, feedback_source);
11786  }
11787  case 2: {
11788  CallArguments args(receiver_mode, {LoadRegister(1), LoadRegister(2)});
11789  return BuildCallWithFeedback(target, args, feedback_source);
11790  }
11791  case 3: {
11792  CallArguments args(receiver_mode,
11793  {LoadRegister(1), LoadRegister(2), LoadRegister(3)});
11794  return BuildCallWithFeedback(target, args, feedback_source);
11795  }
11796  default:
11797  UNREACHABLE();
11798  }
11799 }

11839 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallRuntime() {
11840  Runtime::FunctionId function_id = iterator_.GetRuntimeIdOperand(0);
11841  interpreter::RegisterList args = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
11842  ValueNode* context = GetContext();
11843  size_t input_count = args.register_count() + CallRuntime::kFixedInputCount;
11844  CallRuntime* call_runtime = AddNewNode<CallRuntime>(
11845  input_count,
11846  [&](CallRuntime* call_runtime) {
11847  for (int i = 0; i < args.register_count(); ++i) {
11848  call_runtime->set_arg(i, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
11849  }
11850  },
11851  function_id, context);
11852  SetAccumulator(call_runtime);
11853 
11854  if (RuntimeFunctionCanThrow(function_id)) {
11855  return BuildAbort(AbortReason::kUnexpectedReturnFromThrow);
11856  }
11857  return ReduceResult::Done();
11858 }
11859 
11860 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallJSRuntime() {
11861  // Get the function to call from the native context.
11862  compiler::NativeContextRef native_context = broker()->target_native_context();
11863  ValueNode* context = GetConstant(native_context);
11864  uint32_t slot = iterator_.GetNativeContextIndexOperand(0);
11865  ValueNode* callee = LoadAndCacheContextSlot(context, slot, kMutable,
11866  ContextMode::kNoContextCells);
11867  // Call the function.
11868  interpreter::RegisterList reglist = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
11869  CallArguments args(ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined, reglist,
11870  current_interpreter_frame_);
11871  SetAccumulator(BuildGenericCall(callee, Call::TargetType::kJSFunction, args));
11872  return ReduceResult::Done();
11873 }

11875 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallRuntimeForPair() {
11876  Runtime::FunctionId function_id = iterator_.GetRuntimeIdOperand(0);
11877  interpreter::RegisterList args = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
11878  ValueNode* context = GetContext();
11879 
11880  size_t input_count = args.register_count() + CallRuntime::kFixedInputCount;
11881  CallRuntime* call_runtime = AddNewNode<CallRuntime>(
11882  input_count,
11883  [&](CallRuntime* call_runtime) {
11884  for (int i = 0; i < args.register_count(); ++i) {
11885  call_runtime->set_arg(i, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
11886  }
11887  },
11888  function_id, context);
11889  auto result = iterator_.GetRegisterPairOperand(3);
11890  StoreRegisterPair(result, call_runtime);
11891  return ReduceResult::Done();
11892 }

11894 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitInvokeIntrinsic() {
11895  // InvokeIntrinsic <function_id> <first_arg> <arg_count>
11896  Runtime::FunctionId intrinsic_id = iterator_.GetIntrinsicIdOperand(0);
11897  interpreter::RegisterList args = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
11898  switch (intrinsic_id) {
11899 #define CASE(Name, _, arg_count) \
11900  case Runtime::kInline##Name: \
11901  DCHECK_IMPLIES(arg_count != -1, arg_count == args.register_count()); \
11902  return VisitIntrinsic##Name(args);
11903  INTRINSICS_LIST(CASE)
11904 #undef CASE
11905  default:
11906  UNREACHABLE();
11907  }
11908 }

11918 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::
11919  VisitIntrinsicCopyDataPropertiesWithExcludedPropertiesOnStack(
11920  interpreter::RegisterList args) {
11921  SmiConstant* excluded_property_count =
11922  GetSmiConstant(args.register_count() - 1);
11923  int kContext = 1;
11924  int kExcludedPropertyCount = 1;
11925  CallBuiltin* call_builtin = AddNewNode<CallBuiltin>(
11926  args.register_count() + kContext + kExcludedPropertyCount,
11927  [&](CallBuiltin* call_builtin) {
11928  int arg_index = 0;
11929  call_builtin->set_arg(arg_index++, GetTaggedValue(args[0]));
11930  call_builtin->set_arg(arg_index++, excluded_property_count);
11931  for (int i = 1; i < args.register_count(); i++) {
11932  call_builtin->set_arg(arg_index++, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
11933  }
11934  },
11935  Builtin::kCopyDataPropertiesWithExcludedProperties,
11936  GetTaggedValue(GetContext()));
11937  SetAccumulator(call_builtin);
11938  return ReduceResult::Done();
11939 }

12069 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildGenericConstruct(
12070  ValueNode* target, ValueNode* new_target, ValueNode* context,
12071  const CallArguments& args,
12072  const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
12073  size_t input_count = args.count_with_receiver() + Construct::kFixedInputCount;
12074  DCHECK_EQ(args.receiver_mode(), ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
12075  return AddNewNode<Construct>(
12076  input_count,
12077  [&](Construct* construct) {
12078  int arg_index = 0;
12079  // Add undefined receiver.
12080  construct->set_arg(arg_index++,
12081  GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
12082  for (size_t i = 0; i < args.count(); i++) {
12083  construct->set_arg(arg_index++, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
12084  }
12085  },
12086  feedback_source, GetTaggedValue(target), GetTaggedValue(new_target),
12087  GetTaggedValue(context));
12088 }
