13636 
13637 InlinedAllocation* MaglevGraphBuilder::ExtendOrReallocateCurrentAllocationBlock(
13638  AllocationType allocation_type, VirtualObject* vobject) {
13639  DCHECK_LE(vobject->size(), kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize);
13640  if (!current_allocation_block_ || v8_flags.maglev_allocation_folding == 0 ||
13641  current_allocation_block_->allocation_type() != allocation_type ||
13642  !v8_flags.inline_new || is_turbolev()) {
13643  current_allocation_block_ =
13644  AddNewNode<AllocationBlock>({}, allocation_type);
13645  }
13646 
13647  int current_size = current_allocation_block_->size();
13648  if (current_size + vobject->size() > kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize) {
13649  current_allocation_block_ =
13650  AddNewNode<AllocationBlock>({}, allocation_type);
13651  }
13652 
13653  DCHECK_GE(current_size, 0);
13654  InlinedAllocation* allocation =
13655  AddNewNode<InlinedAllocation>({current_allocation_block_}, vobject);
13656  graph()->allocations_escape_map().emplace(allocation, zone());
13657  current_allocation_block_->Add(allocation);
13658  vobject->set_allocation(allocation);
13659  return allocation;
13660 }
13661 
13662 void MaglevGraphBuilder::ClearCurrentAllocationBlock() {
13663  current_allocation_block_ = nullptr;
13664 }
13665 
13666 void MaglevGraphBuilder::AddNonEscapingUses(InlinedAllocation* allocation,
13667  int use_count) {
13668  if (!v8_flags.maglev_escape_analysis) return;
13669  allocation->AddNonEscapingUses(use_count);
13670 }
13671 
13672 void MaglevGraphBuilder::AddDeoptUse(VirtualObject* vobject) {
13673  vobject->ForEachInput([&](ValueNode* value) {
13674  if (InlinedAllocation* nested_allocation =
13675  value->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
13676  VirtualObject* nested_object =
13677  current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects().FindAllocatedWith(
13678  nested_allocation);
13679  CHECK_NOT_NULL(nested_object);
13680  AddDeoptUse(nested_object);
13681  } else if (!IsConstantNode(value->opcode()) &&
13682  value->opcode() != Opcode::kArgumentsElements &&
13683  value->opcode() != Opcode::kArgumentsLength &&
13684  value->opcode() != Opcode::kRestLength) {
13685  AddDeoptUse(value);
13686  }
13687  });
13688 }
13689 
13690 InlinedAllocation* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInlinedAllocationForConsString(
13691  VirtualObject* vobject, AllocationType allocation_type) {
13692  InlinedAllocation* allocation =
13693  ExtendOrReallocateCurrentAllocationBlock(allocation_type, vobject);
13694  DCHECK_EQ(vobject->size(), sizeof(ConsString));
13695  DCHECK_EQ(vobject->cons_string().length->value_representation(),
13696  ValueRepresentation::kInt32);
13697  AddNonEscapingUses(allocation, 5);
13698  BuildInitializeStore(allocation, vobject->cons_string().map,
13699  HeapObject::kMapOffset);
13700  AddNewNode<StoreInt32>(
13701  {allocation, GetInt32Constant(Name::kEmptyHashField)},
13702  static_cast<int>(offsetof(ConsString, raw_hash_field_)));
13703  AddNewNode<StoreInt32>({allocation, vobject->cons_string().length},
13704  static_cast<int>(offsetof(ConsString, length_)));
13705  BuildInitializeStore(allocation, vobject->cons_string().first(),
13706  offsetof(ConsString, first_));
13707  BuildInitializeStore(allocation, vobject->cons_string().second(),
13708  offsetof(ConsString, second_));
13709  if (is_loop_effect_tracking()) {
13710  loop_effects_->allocations.insert(allocation);
13711  }
13712  return allocation;
13713 }
13714 
13715 InlinedAllocation* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInlinedAllocationForHeapNumber(
13716  VirtualObject* vobject, AllocationType allocation_type) {
13717  DCHECK(vobject->map().IsHeapNumberMap());
13718  InlinedAllocation* allocation =
13719  ExtendOrReallocateCurrentAllocationBlock(allocation_type, vobject);
13720  AddNonEscapingUses(allocation, 2);
13721  BuildStoreMap(allocation, broker()->heap_number_map(),
13722  StoreMap::Kind::kInlinedAllocation);
13723  AddNewNode<StoreFloat64>({allocation, GetFloat64Constant(vobject->number())},
13724  static_cast<int>(offsetof(HeapNumber, value_)));
13725  return allocation;
13726 }
13727 
13728 InlinedAllocation*
13729 MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInlinedAllocationForDoubleFixedArray(
13730  VirtualObject* vobject, AllocationType allocation_type) {
13731  DCHECK(vobject->map().IsFixedDoubleArrayMap());
13732  InlinedAllocation* allocation =
13733  ExtendOrReallocateCurrentAllocationBlock(allocation_type, vobject);
13734  int length = vobject->double_elements_length();
13735  AddNonEscapingUses(allocation, length + 2);
13736  BuildStoreMap(allocation, broker()->fixed_double_array_map(),
13737  StoreMap::Kind::kInlinedAllocation);
13738  AddNewNode<StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier>(
13739  {allocation, GetSmiConstant(length)},
13740  static_cast<int>(offsetof(FixedDoubleArray, length_)),
13741  StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
13742  for (int i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
13743  AddNewNode<StoreFloat64>(
13744  {allocation,
13745  GetFloat64Constant(
13746  vobject->double_elements().GetFromImmutableFixedDoubleArray(i))},
13747  FixedDoubleArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i));
13748  }
13749  return allocation;
13750 }
13751 
13752 InlinedAllocation* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInlinedAllocation(
13753  VirtualObject* vobject, AllocationType allocation_type) {
13754  current_interpreter_frame_.add_object(vobject);
13755  InlinedAllocation* allocation;
13756  switch (vobject->type()) {
13757  case VirtualObject::kHeapNumber:
13758  allocation =
13759  BuildInlinedAllocationForHeapNumber(vobject, allocation_type);
13760  break;
13761  case VirtualObject::kFixedDoubleArray:
13762  allocation =
13763  BuildInlinedAllocationForDoubleFixedArray(vobject, allocation_type);
13764  break;
13765  case VirtualObject::kConsString:
13766  allocation =
13767  BuildInlinedAllocationForConsString(vobject, allocation_type);
13768  break;
13769  case VirtualObject::kDefault: {
13770  SmallZoneVector<ValueNode*, 8> values(zone());
13771  vobject->ForEachInput([&](ValueNode*& node) {
13772  ValueNode* value_to_push;
13773  if (node->Is<VirtualObject>()) {
13774  VirtualObject* nested = node->Cast<VirtualObject>();
13775  node = BuildInlinedAllocation(nested, allocation_type);
13776  value_to_push = node;
13777  } else if (node->Is<Float64Constant>()) {
13778  value_to_push = BuildInlinedAllocationForHeapNumber(
13779  CreateHeapNumber(node->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value()),
13780  allocation_type);
13781  } else {
13782  value_to_push = GetTaggedValue(node);
13783  }
13784  values.push_back(value_to_push);
13785  });
13786  allocation =
13787  ExtendOrReallocateCurrentAllocationBlock(allocation_type, vobject);
13788  AddNonEscapingUses(allocation, static_cast<int>(values.size()));
13789  if (vobject->has_static_map()) {
13790  AddNonEscapingUses(allocation, 1);
13791  BuildStoreMap(allocation, vobject->map(),
13792  StoreMap::Kind::kInlinedAllocation);
13793  }
13794  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < values.size(); i++) {
13795  BuildInitializeStore(allocation, values[i], (i + 1) * kTaggedSize);
13796  }
13797  if (is_loop_effect_tracking()) {
13798  loop_effects_->allocations.insert(allocation);
13799  }
13800  break;
13801  }
13802  }
13803  if (v8_flags.maglev_allocation_folding < 2) {
13804  ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
13805  }
13806  return allocation;
13807 }
13808 
13809 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInlinedArgumentsElements(int start_index,
13810  int length) {
13811  DCHECK(is_inline());
13812  if (length == 0) {
13813  return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray);
13814  }
13815  VirtualObject* elements =
13816  CreateFixedArray(broker()->fixed_array_map(), length);
13817  for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
13818  elements->set(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i),
13819  caller_details_->arguments[i + start_index + 1]);
13820  }
13821  return elements;
13822 }
13823 
13824 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInlinedUnmappedArgumentsElements(
13825  int mapped_count) {
13826  int length = argument_count_without_receiver();
13827  if (length == 0) {
13828  return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray);
13829  }
13830  VirtualObject* unmapped_elements =
13831  CreateFixedArray(broker()->fixed_array_map(), length);
13832  int i = 0;
13833  for (; i < mapped_count; i++) {
13834  unmapped_elements->set(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i),
13835  GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTheHoleValue));
13836  }
13837  for (; i < length; i++) {
13838  unmapped_elements->set(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i),
13839  caller_details_->arguments[i + 1]);
13840  }
13841  return unmapped_elements;
13842 }
13843 
13844 template <CreateArgumentsType type>
13845 VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildVirtualArgumentsObject() {
13846  switch (type) {
13847  case CreateArgumentsType::kMappedArguments:
13848  if (parameter_count_without_receiver() == 0) {
13849  // If there is no aliasing, the arguments object elements are not
13850  // special in any way, we can just return an unmapped backing store.
13851  if (is_inline()) {
13852  int length = argument_count_without_receiver();
13853  ValueNode* elements = BuildInlinedArgumentsElements(0, length);
13854  return CreateArgumentsObject(
13855  broker()->target_native_context().sloppy_arguments_map(broker()),
13856  GetInt32Constant(length), elements, GetClosure());
13857  } else {
13858  ArgumentsLength* length = AddNewNode<ArgumentsLength>({});
13859  EnsureType(length, NodeType::kSmi);
13860  ArgumentsElements* elements = AddNewNode<ArgumentsElements>(
13861  {length}, CreateArgumentsType::kUnmappedArguments,
13862  parameter_count_without_receiver());
13863  return CreateArgumentsObject(
13864  broker()->target_native_context().sloppy_arguments_map(broker()),
13865  length, elements, GetClosure());
13866  }
13867  } else {
13868  // If the parameter count is zero, we should have used the unmapped
13869  // backing store.
13870  int param_count = parameter_count_without_receiver();
13871  DCHECK_GT(param_count, 0);
13872  DCHECK(CanAllocateSloppyArgumentElements());
13873  int param_idx_in_ctxt = compilation_unit_->shared_function_info()
13874  .context_parameters_start() +
13875  param_count - 1;
13876  // The {unmapped_elements} correspond to the extra arguments
13877  // (overapplication) that do not need be "mapped" to the actual
13878  // arguments. Mapped arguments are accessed via the context, whereas
13879  // unmapped arguments are simply accessed via this fixed array. See
13880  // SloppyArgumentsElements in src/object/arguments.h.
13881  if (is_inline()) {
13882  int length = argument_count_without_receiver();
13883  int mapped_count = std::min(param_count, length);
13884  ValueNode* unmapped_elements =
13885  BuildInlinedUnmappedArgumentsElements(mapped_count);
13886  VirtualObject* elements = CreateMappedArgumentsElements(
13887  broker()->sloppy_arguments_elements_map(), mapped_count,
13888  GetContext(), unmapped_elements);
13889  for (int i = 0; i < mapped_count; i++, param_idx_in_ctxt--) {
13890  elements->set(SloppyArgumentsElements::OffsetOfElementAt(i),
13891  GetInt32Constant(param_idx_in_ctxt));
13892  }
13893  return CreateArgumentsObject(
13894  broker()->target_native_context().fast_aliased_arguments_map(
13895  broker()),
13896  GetInt32Constant(length), elements, GetClosure());
13897  } else {
13898  ArgumentsLength* length = AddNewNode<ArgumentsLength>({});
13899  EnsureType(length, NodeType::kSmi);
13900  ArgumentsElements* unmapped_elements = AddNewNode<ArgumentsElements>(
13901  {length}, CreateArgumentsType::kMappedArguments, param_count);
13902  VirtualObject* elements = CreateMappedArgumentsElements(
13903  broker()->sloppy_arguments_elements_map(), param_count,
13904  GetContext(), unmapped_elements);
13905  ValueNode* the_hole_value = GetConstant(broker()->the_hole_value());
13906  for (int i = 0; i < param_count; i++, param_idx_in_ctxt--) {
13907  ValueNode* value = Select(
13908  [&](auto& builder) {
13909  return BuildBranchIfInt32Compare(builder,
13910  Operation::kLessThan,
13911  GetInt32Constant(i), length);
13912  },
13913  [&] { return GetSmiConstant(param_idx_in_ctxt); },
13914  [&] { return the_hole_value; });
13915  elements->set(SloppyArgumentsElements::OffsetOfElementAt(i), value);
13916  }
13917  return CreateArgumentsObject(
13918  broker()->target_native_context().fast_aliased_arguments_map(
13919  broker()),
13920  length, elements, GetClosure());
13921  }
13922  }
13923  case CreateArgumentsType::kUnmappedArguments:
13924  if (is_inline()) {
13925  int length = argument_count_without_receiver();
13926  ValueNode* elements = BuildInlinedArgumentsElements(0, length);
13927  return CreateArgumentsObject(
13928  broker()->target_native_context().strict_arguments_map(broker()),
13929  GetInt32Constant(length), elements);
13930  } else {
13931  ArgumentsLength* length = AddNewNode<ArgumentsLength>({});
13932  EnsureType(length, NodeType::kSmi);
13933  ArgumentsElements* elements = AddNewNode<ArgumentsElements>(
13934  {length}, CreateArgumentsType::kUnmappedArguments,
13935  parameter_count_without_receiver());
13936  return CreateArgumentsObject(
13937  broker()->target_native_context().strict_arguments_map(broker()),
13938  length, elements);
13939  }
13940  case CreateArgumentsType::kRestParameter:
13941  if (is_inline()) {
13942  int start_index = parameter_count_without_receiver();
13943  int length =
13944  std::max(0, argument_count_without_receiver() - start_index);
13945  ValueNode* elements =
13946  BuildInlinedArgumentsElements(start_index, length);
13947  return CreateArgumentsObject(
13948  broker()->target_native_context().js_array_packed_elements_map(
13949  broker()),
13950  GetInt32Constant(length), elements);
13951  } else {
13952  ArgumentsLength* length = AddNewNode<ArgumentsLength>({});
13953  EnsureType(length, NodeType::kSmi);
13954  ArgumentsElements* elements = AddNewNode<ArgumentsElements>(
13955  {length}, CreateArgumentsType::kRestParameter,
13956  parameter_count_without_receiver());
13957  RestLength* rest_length =
13958  AddNewNode<RestLength>({}, parameter_count_without_receiver());
13959  return CreateArgumentsObject(
13960  broker()->target_native_context().js_array_packed_elements_map(
13961  broker()),
13962  rest_length, elements);
13963  }
13964  }
13965 }
13966 
13967 template <CreateArgumentsType type>
13968 ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildAndAllocateArgumentsObject() {
13969  auto arguments = BuildVirtualArgumentsObject<type>();
13970  ValueNode* allocation =
13971  BuildInlinedAllocation(arguments, AllocationType::kYoung);
13972  return allocation;
13973 }
13974 
13975 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildFastCreateObjectOrArrayLiteral(
13976  const compiler::LiteralFeedback& feedback) {
13977  compiler::AllocationSiteRef site = feedback.value();
13978  if (!site.boilerplate(broker()).has_value()) return {};
13979  AllocationType allocation_type =
13980  broker()->dependencies()->DependOnPretenureMode(site);
13981 
13982  // First try to extract out the shape and values of the boilerplate, bailing
13983  // out on complex boilerplates.
13984  int max_properties = compiler::kMaxFastLiteralProperties;
13985  std::optional<VirtualObject*> maybe_value = TryReadBoilerplateForFastLiteral(
13986  *site.boilerplate(broker()), allocation_type,
13987  compiler::kMaxFastLiteralDepth, &max_properties);
13988  if (!maybe_value.has_value()) return {};
13989 
13990  // Then, use the collected information to actually create nodes in the graph.
13991  // TODO(leszeks): Add support for unwinding graph modifications, so that we
13992  // can get rid of this two pass approach.
13993  broker()->dependencies()->DependOnElementsKinds(site);
13994  MaybeReduceResult result =
13995  BuildInlinedAllocation(*maybe_value, allocation_type);
13996  return result;
13997 }
13998 
13999 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateObjectLiteral() {
14000  compiler::ObjectBoilerplateDescriptionRef boilerplate_desc =
14001  GetRefOperand<ObjectBoilerplateDescription>(0);
14002  FeedbackSlot slot_index = GetSlotOperand(1);
14003  int bytecode_flags = GetFlag8Operand(2);
14004  int literal_flags =
14005  interpreter::CreateObjectLiteralFlags::FlagsBits::decode(bytecode_flags);
14006  compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source(feedback(), slot_index);
14007 
14008  compiler::ProcessedFeedback const& processed_feedback =
14009  broker()->GetFeedbackForArrayOrObjectLiteral(feedback_source);
14010  if (processed_feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
14011  return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
14012  DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForObjectLiteral);
14013  }
14014 
14015  MaybeReduceResult result =
14016  TryBuildFastCreateObjectOrArrayLiteral(processed_feedback.AsLiteral());
14017  PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(result, SetAccumulator);
14018 
14019  if (interpreter::CreateObjectLiteralFlags::FastCloneSupportedBit::decode(
14020  bytecode_flags)) {
14021  // TODO(victorgomes): CreateShallowObjectLiteral should not need the
14022  // boilerplate descriptor. However the current builtin checks that the
14023  // feedback exists and fallsback to CreateObjectLiteral if it doesn't.
14024  SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<CreateShallowObjectLiteral>(
14025  {}, boilerplate_desc, feedback_source, literal_flags));
14026  } else {
14027  SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<CreateObjectLiteral>(
14028  {}, boilerplate_desc, feedback_source, literal_flags));
14029  }
14030 
14031  return ReduceResult::Done();
14032 }
14033 
14034 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateEmptyObjectLiteral() {
14035  compiler::NativeContextRef native_context = broker()->target_native_context();
14036  compiler::MapRef map =
14037  native_context.object_function(broker()).initial_map(broker());
14038  DCHECK(!map.is_dictionary_map());
14039  DCHECK(!map.IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress());
14040  SetAccumulator(
14041  BuildInlinedAllocation(CreateJSObject(map), AllocationType::kYoung));
14042  return ReduceResult::Done();
14043 }
14044 
14045 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCloneObject() {
14046  // CloneObject <source_idx> <flags> <feedback_slot>
14047  ValueNode* source = LoadRegister(0);
14048  ValueNode* flags =
14049  GetSmiConstant(interpreter::CreateObjectLiteralFlags::FlagsBits::decode(
14050  GetFlag8Operand(1)));
14051  FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(2);
14052  compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
14053  SetAccumulator(BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kCloneObjectIC>(
14054  {GetTaggedValue(source), flags}, feedback_source));
14055  return ReduceResult::Done();
14056 }
14057 
14058 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitGetTemplateObject() {
14059  // GetTemplateObject <descriptor_idx> <literal_idx>
14060  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_function_info =
14061  compilation_unit_->shared_function_info();
14062  ValueNode* description = GetConstant(GetRefOperand<HeapObject>(0));
14063  FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(1);
14064  compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
14065 
14066  const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& feedback =
14067  broker()->GetFeedbackForTemplateObject(feedback_source);
14068  if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
14069  SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<GetTemplateObject>(
14070  {description}, shared_function_info, feedback_source));
14071  return ReduceResult::Done();
14072  }
14073  compiler::JSArrayRef template_object = feedback.AsTemplateObject().value();
14074  SetAccumulator(GetConstant(template_object));
14075  return ReduceResult::Done();
14076 }
14077 
14078 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateClosure() {
14079  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_function_info =
14080  GetRefOperand<SharedFunctionInfo>(0);
14081  compiler::FeedbackCellRef feedback_cell =
14082  feedback().GetClosureFeedbackCell(broker(), iterator_.GetIndexOperand(1));
14083  uint32_t flags = GetFlag8Operand(2);
14084 
14085  if (interpreter::CreateClosureFlags::FastNewClosureBit::decode(flags)) {
14086  SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<FastCreateClosure>(
14087  {GetContext()}, shared_function_info, feedback_cell));
14088  } else {
14089  bool pretenured =
14090  interpreter::CreateClosureFlags::PretenuredBit::decode(flags);
14091  SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<CreateClosure>(
14092  {GetContext()}, shared_function_info, feedback_cell, pretenured));
14093  }
14094  return ReduceResult::Done();
14095 }
14096 
14097 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildInlinedAllocatedContext(
14098  compiler::MapRef map, compiler::ScopeInfoRef scope, int context_length) {
14099  const int kContextAllocationLimit = 16;
14100  if (context_length > kContextAllocationLimit) return {};
14101  DCHECK_GE(context_length, Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS);
14102  auto context = CreateContext(map, context_length, scope, GetContext());
14103  ValueNode* result = BuildInlinedAllocation(context, AllocationType::kYoung);
14104  return result;
14105 }
14106 
14107 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateBlockContext() {
14108  // CreateBlockContext <scope_info_idx>
14109  compiler::ScopeInfoRef scope_info = GetRefOperand<ScopeInfo>(0);
14110  compiler::MapRef map =
14111  broker()->target_native_context().block_context_map(broker());
14112 
14113  auto done = [&](ValueNode* res) {
14114  graph()->record_scope_info(res, scope_info);
14115  SetAccumulator(res);
14116  };
14117 
14118  PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildInlinedAllocatedContext(
14119  map, scope_info, scope_info.ContextLength()),
14120  done);
14121  // Fallback.
14122  done(BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kPushBlockContext, {GetConstant(scope_info)})
14123  .value());
14124  return ReduceResult::Done();
14125 }
14126 
14127 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateCatchContext() {
14128  // CreateCatchContext <exception> <scope_info_idx>
14129  ValueNode* exception = LoadRegister(0);
14130  compiler::ScopeInfoRef scope_info = GetRefOperand<ScopeInfo>(1);
14131  auto context = CreateContext(
14132  broker()->target_native_context().catch_context_map(broker()),
14133  Context::MIN_CONTEXT_EXTENDED_SLOTS, scope_info, GetContext(), exception);
14134  SetAccumulator(BuildInlinedAllocation(context, AllocationType::kYoung));
14135  graph()->record_scope_info(GetAccumulator(), scope_info);
14136  return ReduceResult::Done();
14137 }
14138 
14139 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateFunctionContext() {
14140  compiler::ScopeInfoRef info = GetRefOperand<ScopeInfo>(0);
14141  uint32_t slot_count = iterator_.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(1);
14142  compiler::MapRef map =
14143  broker()->target_native_context().function_context_map(broker());
14144 
14145  auto done = [&](ValueNode* res) {
14146  graph()->record_scope_info(res, info);
14147  SetAccumulator(res);
14148  };
14149 
14150  PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
14151  TryBuildInlinedAllocatedContext(map, info,
14152  slot_count + Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS),
14153  done);
14154  // Fallback.
14155  done(AddNewNode<CreateFunctionContext>({GetContext()}, info, slot_count,
14156  ScopeType::FUNCTION_SCOPE));
14157  return ReduceResult::Done();
14158 }
14159 
14160 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateFunctionContextWithCells() {
14161  return VisitCreateFunctionContext();
14162 }
14163 
14164 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateEvalContext() {
14165  compiler::ScopeInfoRef info = GetRefOperand<ScopeInfo>(0);
14166  uint32_t slot_count = iterator_.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(1);
14167  compiler::MapRef map =
14168  broker()->target_native_context().eval_context_map(broker());
14169 
14170  auto done = [&](ValueNode* res) {
14171  graph()->record_scope_info(res, info);
14172  SetAccumulator(res);
14173  };
14174 
14175  PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
14176  TryBuildInlinedAllocatedContext(map, info,
14177  slot_count + Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS),
14178  done);
14179  if (slot_count <= static_cast<uint32_t>(
14180  ConstructorBuiltins::MaximumFunctionContextSlots())) {
14181  done(AddNewNode<CreateFunctionContext>({GetContext()}, info, slot_count,
14182  ScopeType::EVAL_SCOPE));
14183  } else {
14184  done(BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kNewFunctionContext, {GetConstant(info)})
14185  .value());
14186  }
14187  return ReduceResult::Done();
14188 }

14190 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateWithContext() {
14191  // CreateWithContext <register> <scope_info_idx>
14192  ValueNode* object = LoadRegister(0);
14193  compiler::ScopeInfoRef scope_info = GetRefOperand<ScopeInfo>(1);
14194  auto context = CreateContext(
14195  broker()->target_native_context().with_context_map(broker()),
14196  Context::MIN_CONTEXT_EXTENDED_SLOTS, scope_info, GetContext(), object);
14197  SetAccumulator(BuildInlinedAllocation(context, AllocationType::kYoung));
14198  graph()->record_scope_info(GetAccumulator(), scope_info);
14199  return ReduceResult::Done();
14200 }

14202 bool MaglevGraphBuilder::CanAllocateSloppyArgumentElements() {
14203  return SloppyArgumentsElements::SizeFor(parameter_count()) <=
14204  kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize;
14205 }
14206 
14207 bool MaglevGraphBuilder::CanAllocateInlinedArgumentElements() {
14208  DCHECK(is_inline());
14209  return FixedArray::SizeFor(argument_count_without_receiver()) <=
14210  kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize;
14211 }
14212 
14213 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateMappedArguments() {
14214  compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared =
14215  compilation_unit_->shared_function_info();
14216  if (!shared.object()->has_duplicate_parameters()) {
14217  if (((is_inline() && CanAllocateInlinedArgumentElements()) ||
14218  (!is_inline() && CanAllocateSloppyArgumentElements()))) {
14219  SetAccumulator(BuildAndAllocateArgumentsObject<
14220  CreateArgumentsType::kMappedArguments>());
14221  return ReduceResult::Done();
14222  } else if (!is_inline()) {
14223  SetAccumulator(
14224  BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kFastNewSloppyArguments>({GetClosure()}));
14225  return ReduceResult::Done();
14226  }
14227  }
14228  // Generic fallback.
14229  SetAccumulator(
14230  BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kNewSloppyArguments, {GetClosure()}).value());
14231  return ReduceResult::Done();
14232 }
14233 
14234 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateUnmappedArguments() {
14235  if (!is_inline() || CanAllocateInlinedArgumentElements()) {
14236  SetAccumulator(BuildAndAllocateArgumentsObject<
14237  CreateArgumentsType::kUnmappedArguments>());
14238  return ReduceResult::Done();
14239  }
14240  // Generic fallback.
14241  SetAccumulator(
14242  BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kNewStrictArguments, {GetClosure()}).value());
14243  return ReduceResult::Done();
14244 }
14245 
14246 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateRestParameter() {
14247  if (!is_inline() || CanAllocateInlinedArgumentElements()) {
14248  SetAccumulator(
14249  BuildAndAllocateArgumentsObject<CreateArgumentsType::kRestParameter>());
14250  return ReduceResult::Done();
14251  }
14252  // Generic fallback.
14253  SetAccumulator(
14254  BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kNewRestParameter, {GetClosure()}).value());
14255  return ReduceResult::Done();
14256 }
14257 
14258 void MaglevGraphBuilder::PeelLoop() {
14259  int loop_header = iterator_.current_offset();
14260  DCHECK(loop_headers_to_peel_.Contains(loop_header));
14261  DCHECK(!in_peeled_iteration());
14262  peeled_iteration_count_ = v8_flags.maglev_optimistic_peeled_loops ? 2 : 1;
14263  any_peeled_loop_ = true;
14264  allow_loop_peeling_ = false;
14265 
14266  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
14267  std::cout << " * Begin loop peeling...." << std::endl;
14268  }
14269 
14270  while (in_peeled_iteration()) {
14271  BuildLoopForPeeling();
14272  }
14273  // Emit the actual (not peeled) loop if needed.
14274  if (loop_header == iterator_.current_offset()) {
14275  BuildLoopForPeeling();
14276  }
14277  allow_loop_peeling_ = true;
14278 }
14279 
14280 BasicBlock* MaglevGraphBuilder::FinishInlinedBlockForCaller(
14281  ControlNode* control_node, ZoneVector<Node*> rem_nodes_in_call_block) {
14282  BasicBlock* result = current_block_;
14283  result->nodes().reserve(node_buffer().size() +
14284  rem_nodes_in_call_block.size());
14285  FlushNodesToBlock();
14286  current_block_ = nullptr;
14287  for (Node* n : rem_nodes_in_call_block) {
14288  n->set_owner(result);
14289  result->nodes().push_back(n);
14290  }
14291  control_node->set_owner(result);
14292  CHECK_NULL(result->control_node());
14293  result->set_control_node(control_node);
14294 
14295  // Add the final block to the graph.
14296  graph_->Add(result);
14297  return result;
14298 }
14299 
14300 void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoopForPeeling() {
14301  int loop_header = iterator_.current_offset();
14302  DCHECK(loop_headers_to_peel_.Contains(loop_header));
14303 
14304  // Since peeled loops do not start with a loop merge state, we need to
14305  // explicitly enter e loop effect tracking scope for the peeled iteration.
14306  bool track_peeled_effects =
14307  v8_flags.maglev_optimistic_peeled_loops && peeled_iteration_count_ == 2;
14308  if (track_peeled_effects) {
14309  BeginLoopEffects(loop_header);
14310  }
14311 
14312 #ifdef DEBUG
14313  bool was_in_peeled_iteration = in_peeled_iteration();
14314 #endif // DEBUG
14315 
14316  while (iterator_.current_bytecode() != interpreter::Bytecode::kJumpLoop) {
14317  local_isolate_->heap()->Safepoint();
14318  VisitSingleBytecode();
14319  iterator_.Advance();
14320  }
14321 
14322  VisitSingleBytecode(); // VisitJumpLoop
14323 
14324  DCHECK_EQ(was_in_peeled_iteration, in_peeled_iteration());
14325  if (!in_peeled_iteration()) {
14326  return;
14327  }
14328 
14329  // In case the peeled iteration was mergeable (see TryMergeLoop) or the
14330  // JumpLoop was dead, we are done.
14331  if (!current_block_) {
14332  decremented_predecessor_offsets_.clear();
14333  KillPeeledLoopTargets(peeled_iteration_count_);
14334  peeled_iteration_count_ = 0;
14335  if (track_peeled_effects) {
14336  EndLoopEffects(loop_header);
14337  }
14338  return;
14339  }
14340 
14341  peeled_iteration_count_--;
14342 
14343  // After processing the peeled iteration and reaching the `JumpLoop`, we
14344  // re-process the loop body. For this, we need to reset the graph building
14345  // state roughly as if we didn't process it yet.
14346 
14347  // Reset position in exception handler table to before the loop.
14348  HandlerTable table(*bytecode().object());
14349  while (next_handler_table_index_ > 0) {
14350  next_handler_table_index_--;
14351  int start = table.GetRangeStart(next_handler_table_index_);
14352  if (start < loop_header) break;
14353  }
14354 
14355  // Re-create catch handler merge states.
14356  for (int offset = loop_header; offset <= iterator_.current_offset();
14357  ++offset) {
14358  if (auto& merge_state = merge_states_[offset]) {
14359  if (merge_state->is_exception_handler()) {
14360  merge_state = MergePointInterpreterFrameState::NewForCatchBlock(
14361  *compilation_unit_, merge_state->frame_state().liveness(), offset,
14362  merge_state->exception_handler_was_used(),
14363  merge_state->catch_block_context_register(), graph_);
14364  } else {
14365  // We only peel innermost loops.
14366  DCHECK(!merge_state->is_loop());
14367  merge_state = nullptr;
14368  }
14369  }
14370  new (&jump_targets_[offset]) BasicBlockRef();
14371  }
14372 
14373  // Reset predecessors as if the loop body had not been visited.
14374  for (int offset : decremented_predecessor_offsets_) {
14375  DCHECK_GE(offset, loop_header);
14376  if (offset <= iterator_.current_offset()) {
14377  UpdatePredecessorCount(offset, 1);
14378  }
14379  }
14380  decremented_predecessor_offsets_.clear();
14381 
14382  DCHECK(current_block_);
14383  // After resetting, the actual loop header always has exactly 2
14384  // predecessors: the two copies of `JumpLoop`.
14385  InitializePredecessorCount(loop_header, 2);
14386  merge_states_[loop_header] = MergePointInterpreterFrameState::NewForLoop(
14387  current_interpreter_frame_, graph_, *compilation_unit_, loop_header, 2,
14388  GetInLivenessFor(loop_header),
14389  &bytecode_analysis_.GetLoopInfoFor(loop_header),
14390  /* has_been_peeled */ true);
14391 
14392  BasicBlock* block = FinishBlock<Jump>({}, &jump_targets_[loop_header]);
14393  // If we ever want more peelings, we should ensure that only the last one
14394  // creates a loop header.
14395  DCHECK_LE(peeled_iteration_count_, 1);
14396  DCHECK_IMPLIES(in_peeled_iteration(),
14397  v8_flags.maglev_optimistic_peeled_loops);
14398  merge_states_[loop_header]->InitializeLoop(
14399  this, *compilation_unit_, current_interpreter_frame_, block,
14400  in_peeled_iteration(), loop_effects_);
14401 
14402  if (track_peeled_effects) {
14403  EndLoopEffects(loop_header);
14404  }
14405  DCHECK_NE(iterator_.current_offset(), loop_header);
14406  iterator_.SetOffset(loop_header);
14407 }
14408 
14409 void MaglevGraphBuilder::OsrAnalyzePrequel() {
14410  DCHECK_EQ(compilation_unit_->info()->toplevel_compilation_unit(),
14411  compilation_unit_);
14412 
14413  // TODO(olivf) We might want to start collecting known_node_aspects_ here.
14414  for (iterator_.SetOffset(0); iterator_.current_offset() != entrypoint_;
14415  iterator_.Advance()) {
14416  switch (iterator_.current_bytecode()) {
14417  case interpreter::Bytecode::kPushContext: {
14418  graph()->record_scope_info(GetContext(), {});
14419  // Nothing left to analyze...
14420  return;
14421  }
14422  default:
14423  continue;
14424  }
14425  }
14426 }
14427 
14428 void MaglevGraphBuilder::BeginLoopEffects(int loop_header) {
14429  loop_effects_stack_.push_back(zone()->New<LoopEffects>(loop_header, zone()));
14430  loop_effects_ = loop_effects_stack_.back();
14431 }
14432 
14433 void MaglevGraphBuilder::EndLoopEffects(int loop_header) {
14434  DCHECK_EQ(loop_effects_, loop_effects_stack_.back());
14435  DCHECK_EQ(loop_effects_->loop_header, loop_header);
14436  // TODO(olivf): Update merge states dominated by the loop header with
14437  // information we know to be unaffected by the loop.
14438  if (merge_states_[loop_header] && merge_states_[loop_header]->is_loop()) {
14439  merge_states_[loop_header]->set_loop_effects(loop_effects_);
14440  }
14441  if (loop_effects_stack_.size() > 1) {
14442  LoopEffects* inner_effects = loop_effects_;
14443  loop_effects_ = *(loop_effects_stack_.end() - 2);
14444  loop_effects_->Merge(inner_effects);
14445  } else {
14446  loop_effects_ = nullptr;
14447  }
14448  loop_effects_stack_.pop_back();
14449 }
14450 
14451 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpLoop() {
14452  const uint32_t relative_jump_bytecode_offset =
14453  iterator_.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(0);
14454  const int32_t loop_offset = iterator_.GetImmediateOperand(1);
14455  const FeedbackSlot feedback_slot = iterator_.GetSlotOperand(2);
14456  int target = iterator_.GetJumpTargetOffset();
14457 
14458  if (ShouldEmitInterruptBudgetChecks()) {
14459  int reduction = relative_jump_bytecode_offset *
14460  v8_flags.osr_from_maglev_interrupt_scale_factor;
14461  AddNewNode<ReduceInterruptBudgetForLoop>({GetFeedbackCell()},
14462  reduction > 0 ? reduction : 1);
14463  } else {
14464  AddNewNode<HandleNoHeapWritesInterrupt>({});
14465  }
14466 
14467  if (ShouldEmitOsrInterruptBudgetChecks()) {
14468  AddNewNode<TryOnStackReplacement>(
14469  {GetClosure()}, loop_offset, feedback_slot,
14470  BytecodeOffset(iterator_.current_offset()), compilation_unit_);
14471  }
14472 
14473  bool is_peeled_loop = loop_headers_to_peel_.Contains(target);
14474  auto FinishLoopBlock = [&]() {
14475  return FinishBlock<JumpLoop>({}, jump_targets_[target].block_ptr());
14476  };
14477  if (is_peeled_loop && in_peeled_iteration()) {
14478  ClobberAccumulator();
14479  if (in_optimistic_peeling_iteration()) {
14480  // Let's see if we can finish this loop without peeling it.
14481  if (!merge_states_[target]->TryMergeLoop(this, current_interpreter_frame_,
14482  FinishLoopBlock)) {
14483  merge_states_[target]->MergeDeadLoop(*compilation_unit());
14484  }
14485  if (is_loop_effect_tracking_enabled()) {
14486  EndLoopEffects(target);
14487  }
14488  }
14489  } else {
14490  BasicBlock* block = FinishLoopBlock();
14491  merge_states_[target]->MergeLoop(this, current_interpreter_frame_, block);
14492  block->set_predecessor_id(merge_states_[target]->predecessor_count() - 1);
14493  if (is_peeled_loop) {
14494  DCHECK(!in_peeled_iteration());
14495  }
14496  if (is_loop_effect_tracking_enabled()) {
14497  EndLoopEffects(target);
14498  }
14499  }
14500  return ReduceResult::Done();
14501 }
14502 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJump() {
14503  BasicBlock* block =
14504  FinishBlock<Jump>({}, &jump_targets_[iterator_.GetJumpTargetOffset()]);
14505  MergeIntoFrameState(block, iterator_.GetJumpTargetOffset());
14506  DCHECK_EQ(current_block_, nullptr);
14507  DCHECK_LT(next_offset(), bytecode().length());
14508  return ReduceResult::Done();
14509 }
14510 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpConstant() { return VisitJump(); }
14511 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfNullConstant() {
14512  return VisitJumpIfNull();
14513 }

14521  return VisitJumpIfNotUndefined();
14522 }

14524  return VisitJumpIfUndefinedOrNull();
14525 }

14544 
14545 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MergeIntoFrameState(BasicBlock* predecessor,
14546  int target) {
14547  if (merge_states_[target] == nullptr) {
14548  bool jumping_to_peeled_iteration = bytecode_analysis().IsLoopHeader(target);
14549  DCHECK_EQ(jumping_to_peeled_iteration,
14550  loop_headers_to_peel_.Contains(target));
14551  const compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness = GetInLivenessFor(target);
14552  if (jumping_to_peeled_iteration) {
14553  // The peeled iteration is missing the backedge.
14554  DecrementDeadPredecessorAndAccountForPeeling(target);
14555  }
14556  // If there's no target frame state, allocate a new one.
14557  merge_states_[target] = MergePointInterpreterFrameState::New(
14558  *compilation_unit_, current_interpreter_frame_, target,
14559  predecessor_count(target), predecessor, liveness);
14560  } else {
14561  // If there already is a frame state, merge.
14562  merge_states_[target]->Merge(this, current_interpreter_frame_, predecessor);
14563  }
14564 }
14565 
14566 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MergeDeadIntoFrameState(int target) {
14567  // If there already is a frame state, merge.
14568  if (merge_states_[target]) {
14569  DCHECK_EQ(merge_states_[target]->predecessor_count(),
14570  predecessor_count(target));
14571  merge_states_[target]->MergeDead(*compilation_unit_);
14572  // If this merge is the last one which kills a loop merge, remove that
14573  // merge state.
14574  if (merge_states_[target]->is_unmerged_unreachable_loop()) {
14575  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
14576  std::cout << "! Killing loop merge state at @" << target << std::endl;
14577  }
14578  merge_states_[target] = nullptr;
14579  }
14580  }
14581  // If there is no merge state yet, don't create one, but just reduce the
14582  // number of possible predecessors to zero.
14583  DecrementDeadPredecessorAndAccountForPeeling(target);
14584 }
14585 
14586 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MergeDeadLoopIntoFrameState(int target) {
14587  // Check if the Loop entry is dead already (e.g. an outer loop from OSR).
14588  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!merge_states_[target]) && predecessor_count(target) == 0) {
14589  static_assert(kLoopsMustBeEnteredThroughHeader);
14590  return;
14591  }
14592  // If there already is a frame state, merge.
14593  if (V8_LIKELY(merge_states_[target])) {
14594  DCHECK_EQ(merge_states_[target]->predecessor_count(),
14595  predecessor_count(target));
14596  if (is_loop_effect_tracking_enabled() &&
14597  !merge_states_[target]->is_unmerged_unreachable_loop()) {
14598  EndLoopEffects(target);
14599  }
14600  merge_states_[target]->MergeDeadLoop(*compilation_unit_);
14601  }
14602  // If there is no merge state yet, don't create one, but just reduce the
14603  // number of possible predecessors to zero.
14604  DecrementDeadPredecessorAndAccountForPeeling(target);
14605 }
14606 
14607 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MergeIntoInlinedReturnFrameState(
14608  BasicBlock* predecessor) {
14609  int target = inline_exit_offset();
14610  if (merge_states_[target] == nullptr) {
14611  // All returns should have the same liveness, which is that only the
14612  // accumulator is live.
14613  const compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness = GetInLiveness();
14614  DCHECK(liveness->AccumulatorIsLive());
14615  DCHECK_EQ(liveness->live_value_count(), 1);
14616 
14617  // If there's no target frame state, allocate a new one.
14618  merge_states_[target] = MergePointInterpreterFrameState::New(
14619  *compilation_unit_, current_interpreter_frame_, target,
14620  predecessor_count(target), predecessor, liveness);
14621  } else {
14622  // Again, all returns should have the same liveness, so double check this.
14623  DCHECK(GetInLiveness()->Equals(
14624  *merge_states_[target]->frame_state().liveness()));
14625  merge_states_[target]->Merge(this, current_interpreter_frame_, predecessor);
14626  }
14627 }
14628 
14629 MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult
14630 MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfReferenceEqual(BranchBuilder& builder,
14631  ValueNode* lhs,
14632  ValueNode* rhs) {
14633  if (RootConstant* root_constant = rhs->TryCast<RootConstant>()) {
14634  return builder.Build<BranchIfRootConstant>({lhs}, root_constant->index());
14635  }
14636  if (RootConstant* root_constant = lhs->TryCast<RootConstant>()) {
14637  return builder.Build<BranchIfRootConstant>({rhs}, root_constant->index());
14638  }
14639  if (InlinedAllocation* alloc_lhs = lhs->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
14640  if (InlinedAllocation* alloc_rhs = rhs->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
14641  return builder.FromBool(alloc_lhs == alloc_rhs);
14642  }
14643  }
14644 
14645  return builder.Build<BranchIfReferenceEqual>({lhs, rhs});
14646 }
14647 
14648 void MaglevGraphBuilder::MarkBranchDeadAndJumpIfNeeded(bool is_jump_taken) {
14649  int jump_offset = iterator_.GetJumpTargetOffset();
14650  if (is_jump_taken) {
14651  BasicBlock* block = FinishBlock<Jump>({}, &jump_targets_[jump_offset]);
14652  MergeDeadIntoFrameState(next_offset());
14653  MergeIntoFrameState(block, jump_offset);
14654  } else {
14655  MergeDeadIntoFrameState(jump_offset);
14656  }
14657 }

14659 #ifdef DEBUG
14660 namespace {
14661 bool IsNumberRootConstant(RootIndex root_index) {
14662  switch (root_index) {
14663 #define CASE(type, name, label) case RootIndex::k##label:
14664  SMI_ROOT_LIST(CASE)
14665  STRONG_READ_ONLY_HEAP_NUMBER_ROOT_LIST(CASE)
14666  return true;
14667  default:
14668  return false;
14669  }
14670 #undef CASE
14671 }
14672 } // namespace
14673 #endif
14674 
14675 MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfRootConstant(
14676  BranchBuilder& builder, ValueNode* node, RootIndex root_index) {
14677  // We assume that Maglev never emits a comparison to a root number.
14678  DCHECK(!IsNumberRootConstant(root_index));
14679 
14680  // If the node we're checking is in the accumulator, swap it in the branch
14681  // with the checked value. Cache whether we want to swap, since after we've
14682  // swapped the accumulator isn't the original node anymore.
14683  BranchBuilder::PatchAccumulatorInBranchScope scope(builder, node, root_index);
14684 
14685  if (node->properties().value_representation() ==
14686  ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) {
14687  if (root_index == RootIndex::kUndefinedValue) {
14688 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
14689  return builder.Build<BranchIfFloat64IsUndefinedOrHole>({node});
14690 #else
14691  return builder.Build<BranchIfFloat64IsHole>({node});
14692 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
14693  }
14694  return builder.AlwaysFalse();
14695  }
14696 
14697  if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kNumber)) {
14698  return builder.AlwaysFalse();
14699  }
14700  CHECK(node->is_tagged());
14701 
14702  if (root_index != RootIndex::kTrueValue &&
14703  root_index != RootIndex::kFalseValue &&
14704  CheckType(node, NodeType::kBoolean)) {
14705  return builder.AlwaysFalse();
14706  }
14707 
14708  while (LogicalNot* logical_not = node->TryCast<LogicalNot>()) {
14709  // Bypassing logical not(s) on the input and swapping true/false
14710  // destinations.
14711  node = logical_not->value().node();
14712  builder.SwapTargets();
14713  }
14714 
14715  if (RootConstant* constant = node->TryCast<RootConstant>()) {
14716  return builder.FromBool(constant->index() == root_index);
14717  }
14718 
14719  if (root_index == RootIndex::kUndefinedValue) {
14720  if (Constant* constant = node->TryCast<Constant>()) {
14721  return builder.FromBool(constant->object().IsUndefined());
14722  }
14723  }
14724 
14725  if (root_index != RootIndex::kTrueValue &&
14726  root_index != RootIndex::kFalseValue) {
14727  return builder.Build<BranchIfRootConstant>({node}, root_index);
14728  }
14729  if (root_index == RootIndex::kFalseValue) {
14730  builder.SwapTargets();
14731  }
14732  switch (node->opcode()) {
14733  case Opcode::kTaggedEqual:
14734  return BuildBranchIfReferenceEqual(
14735  builder, node->Cast<TaggedEqual>()->lhs().node(),
14736  node->Cast<TaggedEqual>()->rhs().node());
14737  case Opcode::kTaggedNotEqual:
14738  // Swapped true and false targets.
14739  builder.SwapTargets();
14740  return BuildBranchIfReferenceEqual(
14741  builder, node->Cast<TaggedNotEqual>()->lhs().node(),
14742  node->Cast<TaggedNotEqual>()->rhs().node());
14743  case Opcode::kInt32Compare:
14744  return builder.Build<BranchIfInt32Compare>(
14745  {node->Cast<Int32Compare>()->left_input().node(),
14746  node->Cast<Int32Compare>()->right_input().node()},
14747  node->Cast<Int32Compare>()->operation());
14748  case Opcode::kFloat64Compare:
14749  return builder.Build<BranchIfFloat64Compare>(
14750  {node->Cast<Float64Compare>()->left_input().node(),
14751  node->Cast<Float64Compare>()->right_input().node()},
14752  node->Cast<Float64Compare>()->operation());
14753  case Opcode::kInt32ToBoolean:
14754  if (node->Cast<Int32ToBoolean>()->flip()) {
14755  builder.SwapTargets();
14756  }
14757  return builder.Build<BranchIfInt32ToBooleanTrue>(
14758  {node->Cast<Int32ToBoolean>()->value().node()});
14759  case Opcode::kIntPtrToBoolean:
14760  if (node->Cast<IntPtrToBoolean>()->flip()) {
14761  builder.SwapTargets();
14762  }
14763  return builder.Build<BranchIfIntPtrToBooleanTrue>(
14764  {node->Cast<IntPtrToBoolean>()->value().node()});
14765  case Opcode::kFloat64ToBoolean:
14766  if (node->Cast<Float64ToBoolean>()->flip()) {
14767  builder.SwapTargets();
14768  }
14769  return builder.Build<BranchIfFloat64ToBooleanTrue>(
14770  {node->Cast<Float64ToBoolean>()->value().node()});
14771  case Opcode::kTestUndetectable:
14772  return builder.Build<BranchIfUndetectable>(
14773  {node->Cast<TestUndetectable>()->value().node()},
14774  node->Cast<TestUndetectable>()->check_type());
14775  case Opcode::kHoleyFloat64IsHole:
14776  return builder.Build<BranchIfFloat64IsHole>(
14777  {node->Cast<HoleyFloat64IsHole>()->input().node()});
14778  default:
14779  return builder.Build<BranchIfRootConstant>({node}, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
14780  }
14781 }
14782 
14783 MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfTrue(
14784  BranchBuilder& builder, ValueNode* node) {
14785  builder.SetBranchSpecializationMode(BranchSpecializationMode::kAlwaysBoolean);
14786  return BuildBranchIfRootConstant(builder, node, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
14787 }

14789 MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfNull(
14790  BranchBuilder& builder, ValueNode* node) {
14791  return BuildBranchIfRootConstant(builder, node, RootIndex::kNullValue);
14792 }

14794 MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfUndefined(
14795  BranchBuilder& builder, ValueNode* node) {
14796  return BuildBranchIfRootConstant(builder, node, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
14797 }
14798 
14799 MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult
14800 MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfUndefinedOrNull(BranchBuilder& builder,
14801  ValueNode* node) {
14802  compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant = TryGetConstant(node);
14803  if (maybe_constant.has_value()) {
14804  return builder.FromBool(maybe_constant->IsNullOrUndefined());
14805  }
14806  if (!node->is_tagged()) {
14807  if (node->properties().value_representation() ==
14808  ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) {
14809  return BuildBranchIfFloat64IsHole(builder, node);
14810  }
14811  return builder.AlwaysFalse();
14812  }
14813  if (HasDisjointType(node, NodeType::kOddball)) {
14814  return builder.AlwaysFalse();
14815  }
14816  return builder.Build<BranchIfUndefinedOrNull>({node});
14817 }
14818 
14819 MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfToBooleanTrue(
14820  BranchBuilder& builder, ValueNode* node) {
14821  // If this is a known boolean, use the non-ToBoolean version.
14822  if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kBoolean)) {
14823  return BuildBranchIfTrue(builder, node);
14824  }
14825 
14826  // There shouldn't be any LogicalNots here, for swapping true/false, since
14827  // these are known to be boolean and should have gone throught the
14828  // non-ToBoolean path.
14829  DCHECK(!node->Is<LogicalNot>());
14830 
14831  bool known_to_boolean_value = false;
14832  bool direction_is_true = true;
14833  if (IsConstantNode(node->opcode())) {
14834  known_to_boolean_value = true;
14835  direction_is_true = FromConstantToBool(local_isolate(), node);
14836  } else {
14837  // TODO(victorgomes): Unify this with TestUndetectable?
14838  // JSReceivers are true iff they are not marked as undetectable. Check if
14839  // all maps have the same detectability, and if yes, the boolean value is
14840  // known.
14841  NodeInfo* node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(node);
14842  if (node_info && NodeTypeIs(node_info->type(), NodeType::kJSReceiver) &&
14843  node_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
14844  bool all_detectable = true;
14845  bool all_undetectable = true;
14846  for (compiler::MapRef map : node_info->possible_maps()) {
14847  bool is_undetectable = map.is_undetectable();
14848  all_detectable &= !is_undetectable;
14849  all_undetectable &= is_undetectable;
14850  }
14851  if (all_detectable || all_undetectable) {
14852  known_to_boolean_value = true;
14853  direction_is_true = all_detectable;
14854  }
14855  }
14856  }
14857  if (known_to_boolean_value) {
14858  return builder.FromBool(direction_is_true);
14859  }
14860 
14861  switch (node->value_representation()) {
14862  // The ToBoolean of both the_hole and NaN is false, so we can use the
14863  // same operation for HoleyFloat64 and Float64.
14864  case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
14865  case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
14866  return BuildBranchIfFloat64ToBooleanTrue(builder, node);
14867 
14868  case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
14869  // Uint32 has the same logic as Int32 when converting ToBoolean, namely
14870  // comparison against zero, so we can cast it and ignore the signedness.
14871  node = AddNewNode<TruncateUint32ToInt32>({node});
14872  [[fallthrough]];
14873  case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
14874  return BuildBranchIfInt32ToBooleanTrue(builder, node);
14875 
14876  case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
14877  return BuildBranchIfIntPtrToBooleanTrue(builder, node);
14878 
14879  case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
14880  break;
14881  }
14882 
14883  NodeInfo* node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(node);
14884  if (node_info) {
14885  if (ValueNode* as_int32 = node_info->alternative().int32()) {
14886  return BuildBranchIfInt32ToBooleanTrue(builder, as_int32);
14887  }
14888  if (ValueNode* as_float64 = node_info->alternative().float64()) {
14889  return BuildBranchIfFloat64ToBooleanTrue(builder, as_float64);
14890  }
14891  }
14892 
14893  NodeType old_type;
14894  if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kBoolean, &old_type)) {
14895  return builder.Build<BranchIfRootConstant>({node}, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
14896  }
14897  if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kSmi)) {
14898  builder.SwapTargets();
14899  return builder.Build<BranchIfReferenceEqual>({node, GetSmiConstant(0)});
14900  }
14901  if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kString)) {
14902  builder.SwapTargets();
14903  return builder.Build<BranchIfRootConstant>({node},
14904  RootIndex::kempty_string);
14905  }
14906  // TODO(verwaest): Number or oddball.
14907  return builder.Build<BranchIfToBooleanTrue>({node}, GetCheckType(old_type));
14908 }
14909

14913  // TODO(victorgomes): Optimize.

14983 MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfJSReceiver(
14984  BranchBuilder& builder, ValueNode* value) {
14985  if (!value->is_tagged() && value->properties().value_representation() !=
14986  ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) {
14987  return builder.AlwaysFalse();
14988  }
14989  if (CheckType(value, NodeType::kJSReceiver)) {
14990  return builder.AlwaysTrue();
14991  } else if (HasDisjointType(value, NodeType::kJSReceiver)) {
14992  return builder.AlwaysFalse();
14993  }
14994  return builder.Build<BranchIfJSReceiver>({value});
14995 }
14996 
14997 MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfInt32Compare(
14998  BranchBuilder& builder, Operation op, ValueNode* lhs, ValueNode* rhs) {
14999  auto lhs_const = TryGetInt32Constant(lhs);
15000  if (lhs_const) {
15001  auto rhs_const = TryGetInt32Constant(rhs);
15002  if (rhs_const) {
15003  return builder.FromBool(
15004  CompareInt32(lhs_const.value(), rhs_const.value(), op));
15005  }
15006  }
15007  return builder.Build<BranchIfInt32Compare>({lhs, rhs}, op);
15008 }
15009 
15010 MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfUint32Compare(
15011  BranchBuilder& builder, Operation op, ValueNode* lhs, ValueNode* rhs) {
15012  auto lhs_const = TryGetUint32Constant(lhs);
15013  if (lhs_const) {
15014  auto rhs_const = TryGetUint32Constant(rhs);
15015  if (rhs_const) {
15016  return builder.FromBool(
15017  CompareUint32(lhs_const.value(), rhs_const.value(), op));
15018  }
15019  }
15020  return builder.Build<BranchIfUint32Compare>({lhs, rhs}, op);
15021 }

15023 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfJSReceiver() {
15024  auto branch_builder = CreateBranchBuilder();
15025  BuildBranchIfJSReceiver(branch_builder, GetAccumulator());
15026  return ReduceResult::Done();
15027 }

15029 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfForInDone() {
15030  // JumpIfForInDone <target> <index> <cache_length>
15031  ValueNode* index = LoadRegister(1);
15032  ValueNode* cache_length = LoadRegister(2);
15033  auto branch_builder = CreateBranchBuilder();
15034  BuildBranchIfInt32Compare(branch_builder, Operation::kEqual, index,
15035  cache_length);
15036  return ReduceResult::Done();
15037 }
15038 
15039 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitSwitchOnSmiNoFeedback() {
15040  // SwitchOnSmiNoFeedback <table_start> <table_length> <case_value_base>
15041  interpreter::JumpTableTargetOffsets offsets =
15042  iterator_.GetJumpTableTargetOffsets();
15043 
15044  if (offsets.size() == 0) return ReduceResult::Done();
15045 
15046  int case_value_base = (*offsets.begin()).case_value;
15047  BasicBlockRef* targets = zone()->AllocateArray<BasicBlockRef>(offsets.size());
15048  for (interpreter::JumpTableTargetOffset offset : offsets) {
15049  BasicBlockRef* ref = &targets[offset.case_value - case_value_base];
15050  new (ref) BasicBlockRef(&jump_targets_[offset.target_offset]);
15051  }
15052 
15053  ValueNode* case_value = GetAccumulator();
15054  BasicBlock* block =
15055  FinishBlock<Switch>({case_value}, case_value_base, targets,
15056  offsets.size(), &jump_targets_[next_offset()]);
15057  for (interpreter::JumpTableTargetOffset offset : offsets) {
15058  MergeIntoFrameState(block, offset.target_offset);
15059  }
15060  StartFallthroughBlock(next_offset(), block);
15061  return ReduceResult::Done();
15062 }
15063 
15064 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitForInEnumerate() {
15065  // ForInEnumerate <receiver>
15066  ValueNode* receiver = LoadRegister(0);
15067  // Pass receiver to ForInPrepare.
15068  current_for_in_state.receiver = receiver;
15069  SetAccumulator(
15070  BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kForInEnumerate>({GetTaggedValue(receiver)}));
15071  return ReduceResult::Done();
15072 }
15073 
15074 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitForInPrepare() {
15075  // ForInPrepare <cache_info_triple>
15076  ValueNode* enumerator = GetAccumulator();
15077  // Catch the receiver value passed from ForInEnumerate.
15078  ValueNode* receiver = current_for_in_state.receiver;
15079  FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(1);
15080  compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
15081  // TODO(v8:7700): Use feedback and create fast path.
15082  ValueNode* context = GetContext();
15083  interpreter::Register cache_type_reg = iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(0);
15084  interpreter::Register cache_array_reg{cache_type_reg.index() + 1};
15085  interpreter::Register cache_length_reg{cache_type_reg.index() + 2};
15086 
15087  ForInHint hint = broker()->GetFeedbackForForIn(feedback_source);
15088 
15089  current_for_in_state = ForInState();
15090  switch (hint) {
15091  case ForInHint::kNone:
15092  case ForInHint::kEnumCacheKeysAndIndices:
15093  case ForInHint::kEnumCacheKeys: {
15094  // Check that the {enumerator} is a Map.
15095  // The direct IsMap check requires reading of an instance type, so in
15096  // order to avoid additional load we compare the {enumerator} against
15097  // receiver's Map instead (by definition, the {enumerator} is either
15098  // the receiver's Map or a FixedArray).
15099  auto* receiver_map =
15100  BuildLoadTaggedField(receiver, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
15101  AddNewNode<CheckDynamicValue>({receiver_map, enumerator},
15102  DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMapDynamic);
15103 
15104  auto* descriptor_array =
15105  BuildLoadTaggedField(enumerator, Map::kInstanceDescriptorsOffset);
15106  auto* enum_cache = BuildLoadTaggedField(
15107  descriptor_array, DescriptorArray::kEnumCacheOffset);
15108  auto* cache_array =
15109  BuildLoadTaggedField(enum_cache, EnumCache::kKeysOffset);
15110 
15111  auto* cache_length = AddNewNode<LoadEnumCacheLength>({enumerator});
15112 
15113  if (hint == ForInHint::kEnumCacheKeysAndIndices) {
15114  auto* cache_indices =
15115  BuildLoadTaggedField(enum_cache, EnumCache::kIndicesOffset);
15116  current_for_in_state.enum_cache_indices = cache_indices;
15117  AddNewNode<CheckCacheIndicesNotCleared>({cache_indices, cache_length});
15118  } else {
15119  current_for_in_state.enum_cache_indices = nullptr;
15120  }
15121 
15122  MoveNodeBetweenRegisters(interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator(),
15123  cache_type_reg);
15124  StoreRegister(cache_array_reg, cache_array);
15125  StoreRegister(cache_length_reg, cache_length);
15126  break;
15127  }
15128  case ForInHint::kAny: {
15129  // The result of the bytecode is output in registers |cache_info_triple|
15130  // to |cache_info_triple + 2|, with the registers holding cache_type,
15131  // cache_array, and cache_length respectively.
15132  //
15133  // We set the cache type first (to the accumulator value), and write
15134  // the other two with a ForInPrepare builtin call. This can lazy deopt,
15135  // which will write to cache_array and cache_length, with cache_type
15136  // already set on the translation frame.
15137 
15138  // This move needs to happen before ForInPrepare to avoid lazy deopt
15139  // extending the lifetime of the {cache_type} register.
15140  MoveNodeBetweenRegisters(interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator(),
15141  cache_type_reg);
15142  ForInPrepare* result =
15143  AddNewNode<ForInPrepare>({context, enumerator}, feedback_source);
15144  StoreRegisterPair({cache_array_reg, cache_length_reg}, result);
15145  // Force a conversion to Int32 for the cache length value.
15146  EnsureInt32(cache_length_reg);
15147  break;
15148  }
15149  }
15150  return ReduceResult::Done();
15151 }
15152 
15153 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitForInNext() {
15154  // ForInNext <receiver> <index> <cache_info_pair>
15155  ValueNode* receiver = LoadRegister(0);
15156  interpreter::Register cache_type_reg, cache_array_reg;
15157  std::tie(cache_type_reg, cache_array_reg) =
15158  iterator_.GetRegisterPairOperand(2);
15159  ValueNode* cache_type = current_interpreter_frame_.get(cache_type_reg);
15160  ValueNode* cache_array = current_interpreter_frame_.get(cache_array_reg);
15161  FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(3);
15162  compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
15163 
15164  ForInHint hint = broker()->GetFeedbackForForIn(feedback_source);
15165 
15166  switch (hint) {
15167  case ForInHint::kNone:
15168  case ForInHint::kEnumCacheKeysAndIndices:
15169  case ForInHint::kEnumCacheKeys: {
15170  ValueNode* index = LoadRegister(1);
15171  // Ensure that the expected map still matches that of the {receiver}.
15172  auto* receiver_map =
15173  BuildLoadTaggedField(receiver, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
15174  AddNewNode<CheckDynamicValue>({receiver_map, cache_type},
15175  DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMapDynamic);
15176  auto* key = BuildLoadFixedArrayElement(cache_array, index);
15177  EnsureType(key, NodeType::kInternalizedString);
15178  SetAccumulator(key);
15179 
15180  current_for_in_state.receiver = receiver;
15181  if (ToObject* to_object =
15182  current_for_in_state.receiver->TryCast<ToObject>()) {
15183  current_for_in_state.receiver = to_object->value_input().node();
15184  }
15185  current_for_in_state.receiver_needs_map_check = false;
15186  current_for_in_state.cache_type = cache_type;
15187  current_for_in_state.key = key;
15188  if (hint == ForInHint::kEnumCacheKeysAndIndices) {
15189  current_for_in_state.index = index;
15190  }
15191  // We know that the enum cache entry is not undefined, so skip over the
15192  // next JumpIfUndefined.
15193  DCHECK(iterator_.next_bytecode() ==
15194  interpreter::Bytecode::kJumpIfUndefined ||
15195  iterator_.next_bytecode() ==
15196  interpreter::Bytecode::kJumpIfUndefinedConstant);
15197  iterator_.Advance();
15198  MergeDeadIntoFrameState(iterator_.GetJumpTargetOffset());
15199  break;
15200  }
15201  case ForInHint::kAny: {
15202  ValueNode* index = LoadRegister(1);
15203  ValueNode* context = GetContext();
15204  SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<ForInNext>(
15205  {context, receiver, cache_array, cache_type, index},
15206  feedback_source));
15207  break;
15208  };
15209  }
15210  return ReduceResult::Done();
15211 }
15212 
15213 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitForInStep() {
15214  interpreter::Register index_reg = iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(0);
15215  ValueNode* index = current_interpreter_frame_.get(index_reg);
15216  StoreRegister(index_reg,
15217  AddNewNode<Int32NodeFor<Operation::kIncrement>>({index}));
15218  if (!in_peeled_iteration()) {
15219  // With loop peeling, only the `ForInStep` in the non-peeled loop body marks
15220  // the end of for-in.
15221  current_for_in_state = ForInState();
15222  }
15223  return ReduceResult::Done();
15224 }

15226 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitSetPendingMessage() {
15227  ValueNode* message = GetAccumulator();
15228  SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<SetPendingMessage>({message}));
15229  return ReduceResult::Done();
15230 }

15232 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitThrow() {
15233  ValueNode* exception = GetAccumulator();
15234  return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrow, {exception});
15235 }
15236 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitReThrow() {
15237  ValueNode* exception = GetAccumulator();
15238  return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kReThrow, {exception});
15239 }
15240 
15241 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitReturn() {
15242  // See also: InterpreterAssembler::UpdateInterruptBudgetOnReturn.
15243  const uint32_t relative_jump_bytecode_offset = iterator_.current_offset();
15244  if (ShouldEmitInterruptBudgetChecks() && relative_jump_bytecode_offset > 0) {
15245  AddNewNode<ReduceInterruptBudgetForReturn>({GetFeedbackCell()},
15246  relative_jump_bytecode_offset);
15247  }
15248 
15249  if (!is_inline()) {
15250  FinishBlock<Return>({GetAccumulator()});
15251  return ReduceResult::Done();
15252  }
15253 
15254  // All inlined function returns instead jump to one past the end of the
15255  // bytecode, where we'll later create a final basic block which resumes
15256  // execution of the caller. If there is only one return, at the end of the
15257  // function, we can elide this jump and just continue in the same basic block.
15258  if (iterator_.next_offset() != inline_exit_offset() ||
15259  predecessor_count(inline_exit_offset()) > 1) {
15260  BasicBlock* block =
15261  FinishBlock<Jump>({}, &jump_targets_[inline_exit_offset()]);
15262  // The context is dead by now, set it to optimized out to avoid creating
15263  // unnecessary phis.
15264  SetContext(GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kOptimizedOut));
15265  MergeIntoInlinedReturnFrameState(block);
15266  }
15267  return ReduceResult::Done();
15268 }
15269 
15270 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitThrowReferenceErrorIfHole() {
15271  // ThrowReferenceErrorIfHole <variable_name>
15272  compiler::NameRef name = GetRefOperand<Name>(0);
15273  ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
15274 
15275  // Avoid the check if we know it is not the hole.
15276  if (IsConstantNode(value->opcode())) {
15277  if (IsTheHoleValue(value)) {
15278  ValueNode* constant = GetConstant(name);
15279  return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowAccessedUninitializedVariable,
15280  {constant});
15281  }
15282  return ReduceResult::Done();
15283  }
15284 
15285  // Avoid the check if {value}'s representation doesn't allow the hole.
15286  switch (value->value_representation()) {
15287  case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
15288  case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
15289  case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
15290  case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
15291  case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
15292  // Can't be the hole.
15293  // Note that HoleyFloat64 when converted to Tagged becomes Undefined
15294  // rather than the_hole, hence the early return for HoleyFloat64.
15295  return ReduceResult::Done();
15296 
15297  case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
15298  // Could be the hole.
15299  break;
15300  }
15301 
15302  // Avoid the check if {value} has an alternative whose representation doesn't
15303  // allow the hole.
15304  if (const NodeInfo* info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(value)) {
15305  auto& alt = info->alternative();
15306  if (alt.int32() || alt.truncated_int32_to_number() || alt.float64()) {
15307  return ReduceResult::Done();
15308  }
15309  }
15310 
15311  DCHECK(value->value_representation() == ValueRepresentation::kTagged);
15312  AddNewNode<ThrowReferenceErrorIfHole>({value}, name);
15313  return ReduceResult::Done();
15314 }
15315 
15316 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitThrowSuperNotCalledIfHole() {
15317  // ThrowSuperNotCalledIfHole
15318  ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
15319  if (CheckType(value, NodeType::kJSReceiver)) return ReduceResult::Done();
15320  // Avoid the check if we know it is not the hole.
15321  if (IsConstantNode(value->opcode())) {
15322  if (IsTheHoleValue(value)) {
15323  return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowSuperNotCalled, {});
15324  }
15325  return ReduceResult::Done();
15326  }
15327  AddNewNode<ThrowSuperNotCalledIfHole>({value});
15328  return ReduceResult::Done();
15329 }
15330 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitThrowSuperAlreadyCalledIfNotHole() {
15331  // ThrowSuperAlreadyCalledIfNotHole
15332  ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
15333  // Avoid the check if we know it is the hole.
15334  if (IsConstantNode(value->opcode())) {
15335  if (!IsTheHoleValue(value)) {
15336  return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowSuperAlreadyCalledError, {});
15337  }
15338  return ReduceResult::Done();
15339  }
15340  AddNewNode<ThrowSuperAlreadyCalledIfNotHole>({value});
15341  return ReduceResult::Done();
15342 }
15343 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitThrowIfNotSuperConstructor() {
15344  // ThrowIfNotSuperConstructor <constructor>
15345  ValueNode* constructor = LoadRegister(0);
15346  ValueNode* function = GetClosure();
15347  AddNewNode<ThrowIfNotSuperConstructor>({constructor, function});
15348  return ReduceResult::Done();
15349 }
15350 
15351 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitSwitchOnGeneratorState() {
15352  // SwitchOnGeneratorState <generator> <table_start> <table_length>
15353  // It should be the first bytecode in the bytecode array.
15354  DCHECK_EQ(iterator_.current_offset(), 0);
15355  int generator_prologue_block_offset = 1;
15356  DCHECK_LT(generator_prologue_block_offset, next_offset());
15357 
15358  interpreter::JumpTableTargetOffsets offsets =
15359  iterator_.GetJumpTableTargetOffsets();
15360  // If there are no jump offsets, then this generator is not resumable, which
15361  // means we can skip checking for it and switching on its state.
15362  if (offsets.size() == 0) return ReduceResult::Done();
15363 
15364  graph()->set_has_resumable_generator();
15365 
15366  // We create an initial block that checks if the generator is undefined.
15367  ValueNode* maybe_generator = LoadRegister(0);
15368  // Neither the true nor the false path jump over any bytecode
15369  BasicBlock* block_is_generator_undefined = FinishBlock<BranchIfRootConstant>(
15370  {maybe_generator}, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue,
15371  &jump_targets_[next_offset()],
15372  &jump_targets_[generator_prologue_block_offset]);
15373  MergeIntoFrameState(block_is_generator_undefined, next_offset());
15374 
15375  // We create the generator prologue block.
15376  StartNewBlock(generator_prologue_block_offset, block_is_generator_undefined);
15377 
15378  // Generator prologue.
15379  ValueNode* generator = maybe_generator;
15380  ValueNode* state =
15381  BuildLoadTaggedField(generator, JSGeneratorObject::kContinuationOffset);
15382  ValueNode* new_state = GetSmiConstant(JSGeneratorObject::kGeneratorExecuting);
15383  BuildStoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(generator, new_state,
15384  JSGeneratorObject::kContinuationOffset,
15385  StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
15386  ValueNode* context =
15387  BuildLoadTaggedField(generator, JSGeneratorObject::kContextOffset);
15388  EnsureType(context, NodeType::kContext);
15389  graph()->record_scope_info(context, {});
15390  SetContext(context);
15391 
15392  // Guarantee that we have something in the accumulator.
15393  MoveNodeBetweenRegisters(iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(0),
15394  interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator());
15395 
15396  // Switch on generator state.
15397  int case_value_base = (*offsets.begin()).case_value;
15398  BasicBlockRef* targets = zone()->AllocateArray<BasicBlockRef>(offsets.size());
15399  for (interpreter::JumpTableTargetOffset offset : offsets) {
15400  BasicBlockRef* ref = &targets[offset.case_value - case_value_base];
15401  new (ref) BasicBlockRef(&jump_targets_[offset.target_offset]);
15402  }
15403  ValueNode* case_value =
15404  state->is_tagged() ? AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiUntag>({state}) : state;
15405  BasicBlock* generator_prologue_block = FinishBlock<Switch>(
15406  {case_value}, case_value_base, targets, offsets.size());
15407  for (interpreter::JumpTableTargetOffset offset : offsets) {
15408  MergeIntoFrameState(generator_prologue_block, offset.target_offset);
15409  }
15410  return ReduceResult::Done();
15411 }
15412 
15413 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitSuspendGenerator() {
15414  // SuspendGenerator <generator> <first input register> <register count>
15415  // <suspend_id>
15416  ValueNode* generator = LoadRegister(0);
15417  ValueNode* context = GetContext();
15418  interpreter::RegisterList args = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
15419  uint32_t suspend_id = iterator_.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(3);
15420 
15421  int input_count = parameter_count_without_receiver() + args.register_count() +
15422  GeneratorStore::kFixedInputCount;
15423  int debug_pos_offset = iterator_.current_offset() +
15424  (BytecodeArray::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag);
15425  AddNewNode<GeneratorStore>(
15426  input_count,
15427  [&](GeneratorStore* node) {
15428  int arg_index = 0;
15429  for (int i = 1 /* skip receiver */; i < parameter_count(); ++i) {
15430  node->set_parameters_and_registers(arg_index++,
15431  GetTaggedValue(GetArgument(i)));
15432  }
15433  const compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness = GetOutLiveness();
15434  for (int i = 0; i < args.register_count(); ++i) {
15435  ValueNode* value = liveness->RegisterIsLive(args[i].index())
15436  ? GetTaggedValue(args[i])
15437  : GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kOptimizedOut);
15438  node->set_parameters_and_registers(arg_index++, value);
15439  }
15440  },
15441 
15442  context, generator, suspend_id, debug_pos_offset);
15443 
15444  FinishBlock<Return>({GetAccumulator()});
15445  return ReduceResult::Done();
15446 }
15447 
15448 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitResumeGenerator() {
15449  // ResumeGenerator <generator> <first output register> <register count>
15450  ValueNode* generator = LoadRegister(0);
15451  ValueNode* array = BuildLoadTaggedField(
15452  generator, JSGeneratorObject::kParametersAndRegistersOffset);
15453  interpreter::RegisterList registers = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
15454 
15455  if (v8_flags.maglev_assert) {
15456  // Check if register count is invalid, that is, larger than the
15457  // register file length.
15458  ValueNode* array_length = BuildLoadFixedArrayLength(array);
15459  ValueNode* register_size = GetInt32Constant(
15460  parameter_count_without_receiver() + registers.register_count());
15461  AddNewNode<AssertInt32>(
15462  {register_size, array_length}, AssertCondition::kLessThanEqual,
15463  AbortReason::kInvalidParametersAndRegistersInGenerator);
15464  }
15465 
15466  const compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness =
15467  GetOutLivenessFor(next_offset());
15468  RootConstant* stale = GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kStaleRegister);
15469  for (int i = 0; i < registers.register_count(); ++i) {
15470  interpreter::Register reg = registers[i];
15471  if (liveness->RegisterIsLive(reg.index())) {
15472  int array_index = parameter_count_without_receiver() + i;
15473  ValueNode* value =
15474  AddNewNode<GeneratorRestoreRegister>({array, stale}, array_index);
15475  StoreRegister(registers[i], value);
15476  if (reg == interpreter::Register::current_context()) {
15477  EnsureType(value, NodeType::kContext);
15478  }
15479  }
15480  }
15481  SetAccumulator(BuildLoadTaggedField(
15482  generator, JSGeneratorObject::kInputOrDebugPosOffset));
15483  return ReduceResult::Done();
15484 }
15485 
15486 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceGetIterator(
15487  ValueNode* receiver, int load_slot_index, int call_slot_index) {
15488  // Load iterator method property.
15489  FeedbackSlot load_slot = FeedbackVector::ToSlot(load_slot_index);
15490  compiler::FeedbackSource load_feedback{feedback(), load_slot};
15491  compiler::NameRef iterator_symbol = broker()->iterator_symbol();
15492  ValueNode* iterator_method;
15493  {
15494  DeoptFrameScope deopt_continuation(
15495  this, Builtin::kGetIteratorWithFeedbackLazyDeoptContinuation, {},
15496  base::VectorOf<ValueNode*>({receiver, GetSmiConstant(call_slot_index),
15497  GetConstant(feedback())}));
15498  MaybeReduceResult result_load =
15499  TryBuildLoadNamedProperty(receiver, iterator_symbol, load_feedback);
15500  if (result_load.IsDoneWithAbort() || result_load.IsFail()) {
15501  return result_load;
15502  }
15503  DCHECK(result_load.IsDoneWithValue());
15504  iterator_method = result_load.value();
15505  }
15506  auto throw_iterator_error = [&] {
15507  return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowIteratorError, {receiver});
15508  };
15509  if (!iterator_method->is_tagged()) {
15510  return throw_iterator_error();
15511  }
15512  auto throw_symbol_iterator_invalid = [&] {
15513  return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowSymbolIteratorInvalid, {});
15514  };
15515  auto call_iterator_method = [&] {
15516  DeoptFrameScope deopt_continuation(
15517  this, Builtin::kCallIteratorWithFeedbackLazyDeoptContinuation);
15518 
15519  FeedbackSlot call_slot = FeedbackVector::ToSlot(call_slot_index);
15520  compiler::FeedbackSource call_feedback{feedback(), call_slot};
15521  CallArguments args(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny, {receiver});
15522  MaybeReduceResult result_call =
15523  ReduceCall(iterator_method, args, call_feedback);
15524 
15525  if (result_call.IsDoneWithAbort()) return result_call;
15526  DCHECK(result_call.IsDoneWithValue());
15527  return SelectReduction(
15528  [&](auto& builder) {
15529  return BuildBranchIfJSReceiver(builder, result_call.value());
15530  },
15531  [&] { return result_call; }, throw_symbol_iterator_invalid);
15532  };
15533  // Check if the iterator_method is undefined and call the method otherwise.
15534  return SelectReduction(
15535  [&](auto& builder) {
15536  return BuildBranchIfUndefined(builder, iterator_method);
15537  },
15538  throw_iterator_error, call_iterator_method);
15539 }
15540 
15541 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitGetIterator() {
15542  // GetIterator <object>
15543  ValueNode* receiver = LoadRegister(0);
15544  int load_slot = iterator_.GetIndexOperand(1);
15545  int call_slot = iterator_.GetIndexOperand(2);
15546  PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
15547  TryReduceGetIterator(receiver, load_slot, call_slot), SetAccumulator);
15548  // Fallback to the builtin.
15549  ValueNode* context = GetContext();
15550  SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<GetIterator>({context, receiver}, load_slot,
15551  call_slot, feedback()));
15552  return ReduceResult::Done();
15553 }
15554 
15555 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitDebugger() {
15556  return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kHandleDebuggerStatement, {});
15557 }
15558 
15559 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitIncBlockCounter() {
15560  ValueNode* closure = GetClosure();
15561  ValueNode* coverage_array_slot = GetSmiConstant(iterator_.GetIndexOperand(0));
15562  BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kIncBlockCounter>(
15563  {GetTaggedValue(closure), coverage_array_slot});
15564  return ReduceResult::Done();
15565 }
15566 
15567 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitAbort() {
15568  AbortReason reason = static_cast<AbortReason>(GetFlag8Operand(0));
15569  return BuildAbort(reason);
15570 }
15571 
15572 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitWide() { UNREACHABLE(); }
15573 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitExtraWide() { UNREACHABLE(); }
15574 #define DEBUG_BREAK(Name, ...) \
15575  ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::Visit##Name() { UNREACHABLE(); }
15576 DEBUG_BREAK_BYTECODE_LIST(DEBUG_BREAK)
15577 #undef DEBUG_BREAK
15578 ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitIllegal() { UNREACHABLE(); }
15579
